  (25137, 42, 5, 18, 'And, behold, men brought in a bed a man which was taken with a palsy: and they sought means to bring him in, and to lay him before him.', '0~2532~, 1~2400~, 2~435~ 3~5342~ 4~1909~ 6~2825~ 8~444~ 9~3739~ 10~2258~ 14~3886~: 15~2532~ 17~2212~ [18] 20~1533~ 21~846~ 22~1533~, 23~2532~ 25~5087~ [26] 27~1799~ 28~846~.'),
  (16703, 20, 11, 6, 'The righteousness of the upright shall deliver them: but transgressors shall be taken in their own naughtiness.', '1~06666~ 4~03477~ 6~05337~ 9~0898~ 12~03920~ [14 15] 16~01942~.'),
  (22179, 28, 6, 3, 'Then shall we know, if we follow on to know the LORD: his going forth is prepared as the morning; and he shall come unto us as the rain, as the latter and former rain unto the earth.', '3~03045~, [4] 6~07291~ 9~03045~ 11~03068~: 14~04161~ 16~03559~ 19~07837~; 23~0935~ 28~01653~, 31~04456~ [32] 34~03384~ 37~0776~.'),
  (10132, 12, 21, 5, 'And he built altars for all the host of heaven in the two courts of the house of the LORD.', '2~01129~ 3~04196~ 7~06635~ 9~08064~ 12~08147~ 13~02691~ 16~01004~ 19~03068~.'),
  (1627, 2, 4, 21, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, When thou goest to return into Egypt, see that thou do all those wonders before Pharaoh, which I have put in thine hand: but I will harden his heart, that he shall not let the people go.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 8~03212~ 10~07725~ 12~04714~, 13~07200~ 16~06213~ 19~04159~ 20~06440~ 21~06547~, 25~07760~ 28~03027~: 32~02388~ 34~03820~, 41~05971~ 42~07971~.'),
  (16548, 20, 5, 22, 'His own iniquities shall take the wicked himself, and he shall be holden with the cords of his sins.', '2~05771~ 4~03920~ 6~07563~ 12~08551~ 15~02256~ 18~02403~.'),
  (7954, 9, 28, 5, 'And when Saul saw the host of the Philistines, he was afraid, and his heart greatly trembled.', '2~07586~ 3~07200~ 5~04264~ 8~06430~, 11~03372~, 14~03820~ 15~03966~ 16~02729~.'),
  (29783, 54, 5, 4, 'But if any widow have children or nephews, let them learn first to shew piety at home, and to requite their parents: for that is good and acceptable before God.', '0~1161~ 2~1536~ 3~5503~ 4~2192~ 5~5043~ 6~2228~ 7~1549~, 10~3129~ 11~4412~ 14~2151~ 16~3624~ 17~2398~,* 18~2532~ 20~591~ 21~287~* 23~4269~: 24~1063~ 25~5124~ 26~2076~ 27~2570~ 28~2532~ 29~587~ 30~1799~ 31~2316~.'),
  (13308, 18, 19, 2, 'How long will ye vex my soul, and break me in pieces with words?', '4~03013~ 6~05315~, 8~01792~ 13~04405~?'),
  (1663, 2, 6, 3, 'And I appeared unto Abraham, unto Isaac, and unto Jacob, by the name of God Almighty, but by my name JEHOVAH was I not known to them.', '2~07200~ 4~085~, 6~03327~, 9~03290~, [11 13] 14~0410~ 15~07706~, 19~08034~ 20~03068~ 24~03045~'),
  (8730, 11, 1, 5, 'Then Adonijah the son of Haggith exalted himself, saying, I will be king: and he prepared him chariots and horsemen, and fifty men to run before him.', '&para; 1~0138~ 3~01121~ 5~02294~ 6~04984~ 8~0559~, 12~04427~: 15~06213~ 17~07393~ 19~06571~, 21~02572~ 22~0376~ 24~07323~ 25~06440~'),
  (29785, 54, 5, 6, 'But she that liveth in pleasure is dead while she liveth.', '0~1161~ 5~4684~ 7~2348~ 10~2198~.'),
  (8464, 10, 17, 8, 'For, said Hushai, thou knowest thy father and his men, that they be mighty men, and they be chafed in their minds, as a bear robbed of her whelps in the field: and thy father is a man of war, and will not lodge with the people.', '1~0559~ 2~02365~, 4~03045~ 6~01~ 9~0582~, [12] 14~01368~, [17] 18~04751~ 21~05315~, 24~01677~ 25~07909~ 31~07704~: 34~01~ [35] 37~0376~ 39~04421~, 43~03885~ 46~05971~.'),
  (24016, 40, 24, 49, 'And shall begin to smite his fellowservants, and to eat and drink with the drunken;', '0~2532~ 2~756~ 4~5180~ [5] 6~4889~, 7~1161~ 9~2068~ 10~2532~ 11~4095~ 12~3326~ 14~3184~;'),
  (28167, 45, 8, 35, 'Who shall separate us from the love of Christ? shall tribulation, or distress, or persecution, or famine, or nakedness, or peril, or sword?', '0~5101~ 2~5563~ 3~2248~ 4~575~ 6~26~ 8~5547~? [9] 10~2347~, 11~2228~ 12~4730~, 13~2228~ 14~1375~, 15~2228~ 16~3042~, 17~2228~ 18~1132~, 19~2228~ 20~2794~, 21~2228~ 22~3162~?'),
  (2191, 2, 24, 9, 'Then went up Moses, and Aaron, Nadab, and Abihu, and seventy of the elders of Israel:', '&para; 2~05927~ 3~04872~, 5~0175~, 6~05070~, 8~030~, 10~07657~ 13~02205~ 15~03478~:'),
  (11821, 14, 29, 21, 'And they brought seven bullocks, and seven rams, and seven lambs, and seven he goats, for a sin offering for the kingdom, and for the sanctuary, and for Judah. And he commanded the priests the sons of Aaron to offer them on the altar of the LORD.', '2~0935~ 3~07651~ 4~06499~, 6~07651~ 7~0352~, 9~07651~ 10~03532~, 12~07651~ 13~06842~ 14~05795~, 18~02403~ 21~04467~, 25~04720~, 28~03063~. 31~0559~ 33~03548~ 35~01121~ 37~0175~ 39~05927~ [40] 43~04196~ 46~03068~.'),
  (19169, 24, 8, 7, 'Yea, the stork in the heaven knoweth her appointed times; and the turtle and the crane and the swallow observe the time of their coming; but my people know not the judgment of the LORD.', '2~02624~ 5~08064~ 6~03045~ 9~04150~; 12~08449~ 15~05483~ 18~05693~ 19~08104~ 21~06256~ 24~0935~; 27~05971~ 28~03045~ 31~04941~ 34~03068~.'),
  (8165, 10, 6, 1, 'Again, David gathered together all the chosen men of Israel, thirty thousand.', '&para; 1~01732~ 3~0622~ [5] 6~0977~ [7] 9~03478~, 10~07970~ 11~0505~.'),
  (3029, 3, 11, 27, 'And whatsoever goeth upon his paws, among all manner of beasts that go on all four, those are unclean unto you: whoso toucheth their carcase shall be unclean until the even.', '1~01992~ 2~03605~* 3~01980~ 6~03709~, 11~02416~ 13~01980~ [15] 16~0702~, [18] 19~02931~ 23~05060~ 25~05038~ 28~02930~ 31~06153~.'),
  (15564, 19, 103, 6, 'The LORD executeth righteousness and judgment for all that are oppressed.', '&para; 1~03068~ 2~06213~ 3~06666~ 5~04941~ 10~06231~.'),
  (6704, 7, 7, 3, 'Now therefore go to, proclaim in the ears of the people, saying, Whosoever is fearful and afraid, let him return and depart early from mount Gilead. And there returned of the people twenty and two thousand; and there remained ten thousand.', '3~04994~, 4~07121~ 7~0241~ 10~05971~, 11~0559~, [13] 14~03373~ 16~02730~, 19~07725~ 22~06852~ 24~02022~ 25~01568~. 28~07725~ 31~05971~ 32~06242~ 34~08147~ 35~0505~; 38~07604~ 39~06235~ 40~0505~.'),
  (17876, 23, 10, 17, 'And the light of Israel shall be for a fire, and his Holy One for a flame: and it shall burn and devour his thorns and his briers in one day;', '2~0216~ 4~03478~ 9~0784~, 13~06918~ 16~03852~: 20~01197~ 22~0398~ 24~07898~ 27~08068~ 29~0259~ 30~03117~;'),
  (11913, 14, 32, 29, 'Moreover he provided him cities, and possessions of flocks and herds in abundance: for God had given him substance very much.', '2~06213~ 4~05892~, 6~04735~ 8~06629~ 10~01241~ 12~07230~: 14~0430~ 16~05414~ 18~07399~ 19~03966~ 20~07227~.'),
  (23911, 40, 22, 29, 'Jesus answered and said unto them, Ye do err, not knowing the scriptures, nor the power of God.', '0~2424~ 1~611~ 2~1161~ 3~2036~ 5~846~, 8~4105~, 9~3361~ 10~1492~ 12~1124~, 13~3366~ 15~1411~ 17~2316~.'),
  (2418, 2, 30, 31, 'And thou shalt speak unto the children of Israel, saying, This shall be an holy anointing oil unto me throughout your generations.', '3~01696~ 6~01121~ 8~03478~, 9~0559~, 14~06944~ 15~04888~ 16~08081~ 21~01755~.'),
  (15170, 19, 78, 48, 'He gave up their cattle also to the hail, and their flocks to hot thunderbolts.', '2~05462~ 4~01165~ 8~01259~, 11~04735~ 14~07565~.'),
  (9121, 11, 11, 5, 'For Solomon went after Ashtoreth the goddess of the Zidonians, and after Milcom the abomination of the Ammonites.', '1~08010~ 2~03212~ 3~0310~ 4~06253~ 6~0430~ 9~06722~, 11~0310~ 12~04445~ 14~08251~ 17~05984~.'),
  (7524, 9, 14, 9, 'If they say thus unto us, Tarry until we come to you; then we will stand still in our place, and will not go up unto them.', '2~0559~ 6~01826~ 9~05060~ 16~05975~ 24~05927~'),
  (26377, 43, 7, 34, 'Ye shall seek me, and shall not find me: and where I am, thither ye cannot come.', '2~2212~ 3~3165~, 4~2532~ 5~2147~ 6~3756~ 7~2147~ [8] 9~2532~ 10~3699~ 11~1473~ 12~1510~, [13] 14~5210~ 15~1410~ 16~3756~* 17~2064~.'),
  (4010, 4, 10, 17, 'And the tabernacle was taken down; and the sons of Gershon and the sons of Merari set forward, bearing the tabernacle.', '2~04908~ 5~03381~; 8~01121~ 10~01648~ 13~01121~ 15~04847~ 17~05265~, 18~05375~ 20~04908~.'),
  (23830, 40, 20, 28, 'Even as the Son of man came not to be ministered unto, but to minister, and to give his life a ransom for many.', '1~5618~ 3~5207~ 5~444~ 6~2064~ 7~3756~ 11~1247~, 12~235~ 14~1247~, 15~2532~ 17~1325~ 18~846~ 19~5590~ 21~3083~ 22~473~ 23~4183~.'),
  (13787, 18, 37, 9, 'Out of the south cometh the whirlwind: and cold out of the north.', '3~02315~ 4~0935~ 6~05492~: 8~07135~ 12~04215~.'),
  (2774, 3, 2, 7, 'And if thy oblation be a meat offering baken in the fryingpan, it shall be made of fine flour with oil.', '3~07133~ [4] 7~04503~ [8] 11~04802~, 15~06213~ [16] 18~05560~ 20~08081~.'),
  (3598, 3, 27, 23, 'Then the priest shall reckon unto him the worth of thy estimation, even unto the year of the jubilee: and he shall give thine estimation in that day, as a holy thing unto the LORD.', '2~03548~ 4~02803~ 8~04373~ 11~06187~, [12] 15~08141~ 18~03104~: 22~05414~ 24~06187~ 27~03117~, [28] 31~06944~ 34~03068~.'),
  (24545, 41, 8, 34, 'And when he had called the people unto him with his disciples also, he said unto them, Whosoever will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and follow me.', '0~2532~ 4~4341~ 6~3793~ [7 8] 9~4862~ 10~846~ 11~3101~ 14~2036~ 16~846~, 17~3748~ 18~2309~ 19~2064~ 20~3694~ 21~3450~, 24~533~ 25~1438~, 26~2532~ 28~142~ 29~846~ 30~4716~, 31~2532~ 32~190~ 33~3427~.'),
  (20828, 26, 16, 57, 'Before thy wickedness was discovered, as at the time of thy reproach of the daughters of Syria, and all that are round about her, the daughters of the Philistines, which despise thee round about.', '2~07451~ 4~01540~, 8~06256~ [10] 11~02781~ 14~01323~ 16~0758~, [19 20] 22~05439~ 25~01323~ 28~06430~, 30~07590~ 33~05439~.'),
  (23036, 38, 10, 11, 'And he shall pass through the sea with affliction, and shall smite the waves in the sea, and all the deeps of the river shall dry up: and the pride of Assyria shall be brought down, and the sceptre of Egypt shall depart away.', '4~05674~ 6~03220~ 8~06869~, 11~05221~ 13~01530~ 16~03220~, 20~04688~ 23~02975~ 26~03001~: 29~01347~ 31~0804~ 35~03381~, 38~07626~ 40~04714~ 43~05493~.'),
  (20277, 24, 51, 56, 'Because the spoiler is come upon her, even upon Babylon, and her mighty men are taken, every one of their bows is broken: for the LORD God of recompenses shall surely requite.', '2~07703~ 4~0935~ [7] 9~0894~, 13~01368~ 15~03920~, 20~07198~ 22~02865~: 25~03068~ 26~0410~ 28~01578~ 30~07999~ 31~07999~.'),
  (13180, 18, 13, 18, 'Behold now, I have ordered my cause; I know that I shall be justified.', '4~06186~ [5] 6~04941~; 8~03045~ 13~06663~.'),
  (1848, 2, 12, 27, 'That ye shall say, It is the sacrifice of the LORD''S passover, who passed over the houses of the children of Israel in Egypt, when he smote the Egyptians, and delivered our houses. And the people bowed the head and worshipped.', '3~0559~, [5] 7~02077~ 10~03068~ 11~06453~, 13~06452~ 16~01004~ 19~01121~ 21~03478~ 23~04714~, 26~05062~ 28~04714~, 30~05337~ 32~01004~. 35~05971~ 38~06915~ 40~07812~.'),
