VALUES
  (11722, 14, 25, 9, 'And Amaziah said to the man of God, But what shall we do for the hundred talents which I have given to the army of Israel? And the man of God answered, The LORD is able to give thee much more than this.', '1~0558~ 2~0559~ 5~0376~ 7~0430~, 12~06213~ 15~03967~ 16~03603~ 20~05414~ 23~01416~ 25~03478~? 28~0376~ 30~0430~ 31~0559~, 33~03068~ 34~03426~ 37~05414~ 40~07235~'),
  (4431, 4, 23, 10, 'Who can count the dust of Jacob, and the number of the fourth part of Israel? Let me die the death of the righteous, and let my last end be like his!', '2~04487~ 4~06083~ 6~03290~, 9~04557~ 12~07255~ [13] 15~03478~? 18~04191~ 19~05315~* 21~04194~ 24~03477~, 28~0319~'),
  (8099, 10, 3, 11, 'And he could not answer Abner a word again, because he feared him.', '2~03201~ 4~07725~ 5~074~ 7~01697~ 11~03372~'),
  (27026, 44, 3, 14, 'But ye denied the Holy One and the Just, and desired a murderer to be granted unto you;', '0~1161~ 1~5210~ 2~720~ 5~40~ 6~2532~ 8~1342~, 9~2532~ 10~154~ 12~435~ 13~5406~ 15~5483~ 17~5213~;'),
  (18273, 23, 32, 5, 'The vile person shall be no more called liberal, nor the churl said to be bountiful.', '2~05036~ 7~07121~ 8~05081~, 11~03596~ 12~0559~ [13 14] 15~07771~.'),
  (2888, 3, 7, 4, 'And the two kidneys, and the fat that is on them, which is by the flanks, and the caul that is above the liver, with the kidneys, it shall he take away:', '2~08147~ 3~03629~, 6~02459~ [8] [12] 15~03689~, 18~03508~ [19 20] 23~03516~, 26~03629~, 31~05493~:'),
  (24472, 41, 6, 55, 'And ran through that whole region round about, and began to carry about in beds those that were sick, where they heard he was.', '2~4063~ 3~1565~ 4~3650~ 7~4066~, 9~756~ 12~4064~ 13~1909~ 14~2895~ 17~2192~ 18~2560~, 19~3699~ 21~191~ 23~2076~ 24~3754~* 25~1563~.*'),
  (14884, 19, 66, 2, 'Sing forth the honour of his name: make his praise glorious.', '1~02167~ 3~03519~ 6~08034~: 7~07760~ 9~08416~ 10~03519~.'),
  (30826, 66, 6, 17, 'For the great day of his wrath is come; and who shall be able to stand?', '0~3754~ 2~3173~ 3~2250~ 5~846~ 6~3709~ 8~2064~; 9~2532~ 10~5101~ 13~1410~ 15~2476~?'),
  (19252, 24, 11, 17, 'For the LORD of hosts, that planted thee, hath pronounced evil against thee, for the evil of the house of Israel and of the house of Judah, which they have done against themselves to provoke me to anger in offering incense unto Baal.', '2~03068~ 4~06635~, 6~05193~ 9~01696~ 10~07451~ 13~01558~ 15~07451~ 18~01004~ 20~03478~ 24~01004~ 26~03063~, 30~06213~ 37~03707~ 40~06999~ 42~01168~.'),
  (25665, 42, 16, 31, 'And he said unto him, If they hear not Moses and the prophets, neither will they be persuaded, though one rose from the dead.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~1487~ 7~191~ 8~3756~ 9~3475~ 10~2532~ 12~4396~, 13~3761~ 17~3982~, 18~1437~ 19~5100~ 20~450~ 21~1537~ 23~3498~.'),
  (19969, 24, 41, 3, 'Ishmael also slew all the Jews that were with him, even with Gedaliah, at Mizpah, and the Chaldeans that were found there, and the men of war.', '0~03458~ 2~05221~ 5~03064~ [10] 12~01436~, 14~04709~, 17~03778~ 20~04672~ [22] 24~0582~ 26~04421~.'),
  (15753, 19, 108, 2, 'Awake, psaltery and harp: I myself will awake early.', '0~05782~, 1~05035~ 3~03658~: [5] 7~05782~ 8~07837~.'),
  (25864, 42, 21, 24, 'And they shall fall by the edge of the sword, and shall be led away captive into all nations: and Jerusalem shall be trodden down of the Gentiles, until the times of the Gentiles be fulfilled.', '0~2532~ 3~4098~ 6~4750~ 9~3162~, 10~2532~ 15~163~ 16~1519~ 17~3956~ 18~1484~: 19~2532~ 20~2419~ 22~2071~ 24~3961~ 25~5259~ 27~1484~, 28~891~ 30~2540~ 33~1484~ 35~4137~.'),
  (10460, 13, 5, 24, 'And these were the heads of the house of their fathers, even Epher, and Ishi, and Eliel, and Azriel, and Jeremiah, and Hodaviah, and Jahdiel, mighty men of valour, famous men, and heads of the house of their fathers.', '[2] 4~07218~ 7~01004~ 10~01~, 12~06081~, 14~03469~, 16~0447~, 18~05837~, 20~03414~, 22~01938~, 24~03164~, 25~01368~ 26~0582~ 28~02428~, 29~08034~ 30~0582~, [31] 32~07218~ 35~01004~ 38~01~.'),
  (15081, 19, 75, 1, 'To the chief Musician, Altaschith, A Psalm or Song of Asaph. Unto thee, O God, do we give thanks, unto thee do we give thanks: for that thy name is near thy wondrous works declare.', '&para; [0 3~05329~, 4~0516~, 6~04210~ [7] 8~07892~ 10] 10~0623~ 14~0430~, 18~03034~, [19 20] 24~03034~: [26] 28~08034~ 30~07138~ 33~06381~ 34~05608~.'),
  (19707, 24, 31, 7, 'For thus saith the LORD; Sing with gladness for Jacob, and shout among the chief of the nations: publish ye, praise ye, and say, O LORD, save thy people, the remnant of Israel.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~; 5~07442~ 7~08057~ 9~03290~, 11~06670~ 14~07218~ 17~01471~: 18~08085~ 20~01984~ 23~0559~, 25~03068~, 26~03467~ 28~05971~, 30~07611~ 32~03478~.'),
  (29430, 50, 2, 23, 'Him therefore I hope to send presently, so soon as I shall see how it will go with me.', '0~5126~ 1~3303~* 2~3767~ 4~1679~ 6~3992~ 7~1824~, 10~5613~ 11~302~ 13~542~ 14~4012~ 19~1691~.'),
  (7191, 8, 3, 12, 'And now it is true that I am thy near kinsman: howbeit there is a kinsman nearer than I.', '4~0551~ [7 8] 10~01350~: 13~03426~ 15~01350~ 16~07138~'),
  (21469, 26, 39, 12, 'And seven months shall the house of Israel be burying of them, that they may cleanse the land.', '1~07651~ 2~02320~ 5~01004~ 7~03478~ 9~06912~ 15~02891~ 17~0776~.'),
  (17599, 22, 4, 8, 'Come with me from Lebanon, my spouse, with me from Lebanon: look from the top of Amana, from the top of Shenir and Hermon, from the lions'' dens, from the mountains of the leopards.', '&para; 0~0935~ 4~03844~, [5] 6~03618~, 10~03844~: 11~07789~ 14~07218~ 16~0549~, 19~07218~ 21~08149~ 23~02768~, 26~0738~ 27~04585~, 30~02042~ 33~05246~.'),
  (10949, 13, 21, 7, 'And God was displeased with this thing; therefore he smote Israel.', '&para; 1~0430~ 3~03415~ 4~05869~* 7~01697~; 10~05221~ 11~03478~.'),
  (24874, 41, 15, 37, 'And Jesus cried with a loud voice, and gave up the ghost.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~863~ 5~3173~ 6~5456~, 11~1606~.'),
  (4626, 4, 29, 12, 'And on the fifteenth day of the seventh month ye shall have an holy convocation; ye shall do no servile work, and ye shall keep a feast unto the LORD seven days:', '&para; 3~06240~ 4~02568~* 5~03117~ 8~07637~ 9~02320~ 14~06944~ 15~04744~; 18~06213~ 20~05656~ 21~04399~, 25~02287~ 27~02282~ 30~03068~ 31~07651~ 32~03117~:'),
  (11616, 14, 20, 20, 'And they rose early in the morning, and went forth into the wilderness of Tekoa: and as they went forth, Jehoshaphat stood and said, Hear me, O Judah, and ye inhabitants of Jerusalem; Believe in the LORD your God, so shall ye be established; believe his prophets, so shall ye prosper.', '&para; 3~07925~ 6~01242~, 9~03318~ 12~04057~ 14~08620~: 19~03318~, 20~03092~ 21~05975~ 23~0559~, 24~08085~ 27~03063~, 30~03427~ 32~03389~; 33~0539~ 36~03068~ 38~0430~, 43~0539~; 44~0539~ 46~05030~, 50~06743~.'),
  (19411, 24, 18, 18, 'Then said they, Come, and let us devise devices against Jeremiah; for the law shall not perish from the priest, nor counsel from the wise, nor the word from the prophet. Come, and let us smite him with the tongue, and let us not give heed to any of his words.', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03212~, 7~02803~ 8~04284~ 10~03414~; 13~08451~ 16~06~ 19~03548~, 21~06098~ 24~02450~, 27~01697~ 30~05030~. 31~03212~, 35~05221~ 39~03956~, 45~07181~ 50~01697~.'),
  (25587, 42, 14, 21, 'So that servant came, and shewed his lord these things. Then the master of the house being angry said to his servant, Go out quickly into the streets and lanes of the city, and bring in hither the poor, and the maimed, and the halt, and the blind.', '0~2532~ 1~1565~ 2~1401~ 3~3854~, 5~518~ 6~846~ 7~2962~ 9~5023~. 10~5119~ 15~3617~ 17~3710~ 18~2036~ 20~846~ 21~1401~, 23~1831~ 24~5030~ 25~1519~ 27~4113~ 28~2532~ 29~4505~ 32~4172~, 33~2532~ 35~1521~ 36~5602~ 38~4434~, 39~2532~ 41~376~, 42~2532~ 44~5560~, 45~2532~ 47~5185~.'),
  (24849, 41, 15, 12, 'And Pilate answered and said again unto them, What will ye then that I shall do unto him whom ye call the King of the Jews?', '0~1161~ 1~4091~ 2~611~ 4~2036~ 5~3825~ 7~846~, 8~5101~ 10~2309~ 11~3767~ 15~4160~ [16 17] 18~3739~ 20~3004~ 22~935~ 25~2453~?'),
  (13936, 18, 42, 5, 'I have heard of thee by the hearing of the ear: but now mine eye seeth thee.', '2~08085~ 7~08088~ 10~0241~: 14~05869~ 15~07200~'),
  (21396, 26, 36, 28, 'And ye shall dwell in the land that I gave to your fathers; and ye shall be my people, and I will be your God.', '3~03427~ 6~0776~ 9~05414~ 12~01~; 18~05971~, 24~0430~.'),
  (10264, 13, 1, 4, 'Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth.', '0~05146~, 1~08035~, 2~02526~, 4~03315~.'),
  (29354, 49, 6, 1, 'Children, obey your parents in the Lord: for this is right.', '&para; 0~5043~, 1~5219~ 2~5216~ 3~1118~ 4~1722~ 6~2962~: 7~1063~ 8~5124~ 9~2076~ 10~1342~.'),
  (21967, 27, 7, 25, 'And he shall speak great words against the most High, and shall wear out the saints of the most High, and think to change times and laws: and they shall be given into his hand until a time and times and the dividing of time.', '3~04449~ [4] 5~04406~ 6~06655~ 9~05943~, 13~01080~ 15~06922~ 19~05946~, 21~05452~ 23~08133~ 24~02166~ 26~01882~: 31~03052~ 34~03028~ 35~05705~ 37~05732~ 39~05732~ 42~06387~ 44~05732~.'),
  (13702, 18, 34, 10, 'Therefore hearken unto me, ye men of understanding: far be it from God, that he should do wickedness; and from the Almighty, that he should commit iniquity.', '&para; 1~08085~ 5~0582~ 7~03824~: 10~02486~ 12~0410~, [13 16] 17~07562~; [19] 21~07706~, [22 25] 26~05766~.'),
  (5980, 6, 6, 25, 'And Joshua saved Rahab the harlot alive, and her father''s household, and all that she had; and she dwelleth in Israel even unto this day; because she hid the messengers, which Joshua sent to spy out Jericho.', '1~03091~ 2~02421~ 3~07343~ 5~02181~ 6~02421~, 9~01~ 10~01004~, 18~03427~ 19~07130~ 20~03478~ [21] 24~03117~; 27~02244~ 29~04397~, 31~03091~ 32~07971~ 35~07270~ 36~03405~.'),
  (1944, 2, 15, 19, 'For the horse of Pharaoh went in with his chariots and with his horsemen into the sea, and the LORD brought again the waters of the sea upon them; but the children of Israel went on dry land in the midst of the sea.', '2~05483~ 4~06547~ 6~0935~ 9~07393~ 13~06571~ 16~03220~, 19~03068~ 21~07725~ 23~04325~ 26~03220~ 31~01121~ 33~03478~ 34~01980~ 36~03004~ [37] 40~08432~ 43~03220~.'),
  (8689, 10, 23, 28, 'Zalmon the Ahohite, Maharai the Netophathite,', '0~06756~ 2~0266~, 3~04121~ 5~05200~,'),
  (3707, 4, 3, 10, 'And thou shalt appoint Aaron and his sons, and they shall wait on their priest''s office: and the stranger that cometh nigh shall be put to death.', '3~06485~ 4~0175~ 7~01121~, 12~08104~ 15~03550~: 18~02114~ 21~07131~ 26~04191~.'),
  (17521, 21, 10, 19, 'A feast is made for laughter, and wine maketh merry: but money answereth all things.', '1~03899~ 3~06213~ 5~07814~, 7~03196~ 9~08055~ 10~02416~:* 12~03701~ 13~06030~ [15]'),
  (15176, 19, 78, 54, 'And he brought them to the border of his sanctuary, even to this mountain, which his right hand had purchased.', '2~0935~ 6~01366~ 9~06944~, [10 11] 13~02022~, [14] 17~03225~ 19~07069~.'),
  (24630, 41, 10, 31, 'But many that are first shall be last; and the last first.', '0~1161~ 1~4183~ [2 3] 4~4413~ 6~2071~ 7~2078~; 8~2532~ 10~2078~ 11~4413~.'),
  (49, 1, 2, 18, 'And the LORD God said, It is not good that the man should be alone; I will make him an help meet for him.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0430~ 4~0559~, [5 6] 8~02896~ 11~0120~ 13~01961~ 17~06213~ 21~05828~'),
  (24176, 40, 27, 37, 'And set up over his head his accusation written, THIS IS JESUS THE KING OF THE JEWS.', '0~2532~ 2~2007~ 3~1883~ 4~846~ 5~2776~ 6~846~ 7~156~ 8~1125~, 9~3778~ 10~2076~ 11~2424~ 13~935~ 16~2453~.'),
  (6434, 6, 22, 1, 'Then Joshua called the Reubenites, and the Gadites, and the half tribe of Manasseh,', '&para; 1~03091~ 2~07121~ 4~07206~, 7~01425~, 10~02677~ 11~04294~ 13~04519~,'),
  (25686, 42, 17, 21, 'Neither shall they say, Lo here! or, lo there! for, behold, the kingdom of God is within you.', '0~3761~ 3~2046~, 4~2400~ 5~5602~! 6~2228~, 7~2400~ 8~1563~! 9~1063~, 10~2400~, 12~932~ 14~2316~ 15~2076~ 16~1787~ 17~5216~.'),
  (25912, 42, 22, 34, 'And he said, I tell thee, Peter, the cock shall not crow this day, before that thou shalt thrice deny that thou knowest me.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~, 4~3004~ 5~4671~, 6~4074~, 8~220~ 9~5455~ 10~3364~ 11~5455~ 13~4594~, 15~4250~ 17~2228~ 18~5151~ 19~533~ 21~3361~ 22~1492~ 23~3165~.'),
  (20338, 25, 1, 19, 'I called for my lovers, but they deceived me: my priests and mine elders gave up the ghost in the city, while they sought their meat to relieve their souls.', '1~07121~ 4~0157~, [5] 7~07411~ 10~03548~ 13~02205~ 17~01478~ 20~05892~, 23~01245~ 25~0400~ 27~07725~ 29~05315~.'),
  (13095, 18, 9, 35, 'Then would I speak, and not fear him; but it is not so with me.', '[0] 3~01696~, 6~03372~ [9 10]'),
  (27051, 44, 4, 13, 'Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and perceived that they were unlearned and ignorant men, they marvelled; and they took knowledge of them, that they had been with Jesus.', '0~1161~ 3~2334~ 5~3954~ 7~4074~ 8~2532~ 9~2491~, 10~2532~ 11~2638~ 12~3754~ 14~1526~ 15~62~ 16~2532~ 17~2399~ 18~444~, 20~2296~; 21~5037~ 24~1921~ 26~846~, 27~3754~ 30~2258~ 31~4862~ 32~2424~.'),
  (23156, 40, 1, 2, 'Abraham begat Isaac; and Isaac begat Jacob; and Jacob begat Judas and his brethren;', '0~11~ 1~1080~ 2~2464~; 3~1161~ 4~2464~ 5~1080~ 6~2384~; 7~1161~ 8~2384~ 9~1080~ 10~2455~ 11~2532~ 12~846~ 13~80~;'),
  (11140, 13, 27, 23, 'But David took not the number of them from twenty years old and under: because the LORD had said he would increase Israel like to the stars of the heavens.', '1~01732~ 2~05375~ 5~04557~ 9~06242~ 10~08141~ 11~01121~ 13~04295~: 16~03068~ 18~0559~ 21~07235~ 22~03478~ 26~03556~ 29~08064~.'),
  (25601, 42, 14, 35, 'It is neither fit for the land, nor yet for the dunghill; but men cast it out. He that hath ears to hear, let him hear.', '1~2076~ 2~3777~ 3~2111~ 4~1519~ 6~1093~, 8~3777~ 9~1519~ 11~2874~; [12] 14~906~ 15~846~ 16~1854~. 19~2192~ 20~3775~ 22~191~, 25~191~.'),
  (17201, 20, 27, 23, 'Be thou diligent to know the state of thy flocks, and look well to thy herds.', '&para; 2~03045~ 4~03045~ 6~06440~ 9~06629~, [10] 11~07896~ 12~03820~ 15~05739~.'),
  (22630, 33, 4, 1, 'But in the last days it shall come to pass, that the mountain of the house of the LORD shall be established in the top of the mountains, and it shall be exalted above the hills; and people shall flow unto it.', '&para; 3~0319~ 4~03117~ [10] 12~02022~ 15~01004~ 18~03068~ 21~03559~ 24~07218~ 27~02022~, 32~05375~ 35~01389~; 37~05971~ 39~05102~'),
  (10600, 13, 8, 17, 'And Zebadiah, and Meshullam, and Hezeki, and Heber,', '1~02069~, 3~04918~, 5~02395~, 7~02268~,'),
  (2148, 2, 22, 30, 'Likewise shalt thou do with thine oxen, and with thy sheep: seven days it shall be with his dam; on the eighth day thou shalt give it me.', '0~03651~ 3~06213~ 6~07794~, [7] 10~06629~: 11~07651~ 12~03117~ 18~0517~; 21~08066~ 22~03117~ 25~05414~'),
  (17046, 20, 22, 22, 'Rob not the poor, because he is poor: neither oppress the afflicted in the gate:', '&para; 0~01497~ 3~01800~, [6] 7~01800~: 9~01792~ 11~06041~ 14~08179~:'),
  (8431, 10, 15, 35, 'And hast thou not there with thee Zadok and Abiathar the priests? therefore it shall be, that what thing soever thou shalt hear out of the king''s house, thou shalt tell it to Zadok and Abiathar the priests.', '[1 2] 7~06659~ 9~054~ 11~03548~? [16] 18~01697~ 22~08085~ 26~04428~ 27~01004~, 30~05046~ [31] 33~06659~ 35~054~ 37~03548~.'),
  (30227, 58, 11, 39, 'And these all, having obtained a good report through faith, received not the promise:', '0~2532~ 1~3778~ 2~3956~, 7~3140~ 8~1223~ 9~4102~, 10~2865~ 11~3756~ 13~1860~:'),
  (13774, 18, 36, 29, 'Also can any understand the spreadings of the clouds, or the noise of his tabernacle?', '[2] 3~0995~ 5~04666~ 8~05645~, [9] 11~08663~ 14~05521~?'),
  (2188, 2, 24, 6, 'And Moses took half of the blood, and put it in basins; and half of the blood he sprinkled on the altar.', '1~04872~ 2~03947~ 3~02677~ 6~01818~, 8~07760~ [9] 11~0101~; 13~02677~ 16~01818~ 18~02236~ 21~04196~.'),
  (9201, 11, 13, 9, 'For so was it charged me by the word of the LORD, saying, Eat no bread, nor drink water, nor turn again by the same way that thou camest.', '4~06680~ 8~01697~ 11~03068~, 12~0559~, 13~0398~ 15~03899~, 17~08354~ 18~04325~, 21~07725~ 25~01870~ 28~01980~.'),
  (30229, 58, 12, 1, 'Wherefore seeing we also are compassed about with so great a cloud of witnesses, let us lay aside every weight, and the sin which doth so easily beset us, and let us run with patience the race that is set before us,', '&para; 0~5105~ 3~2532~ 4~2192~ 6~4029~ 7~2254~* 10~5118~ 12~3509~ 14~3144~, 15~659~ 16~2249~ 18~659~ 19~3956~ 20~3591~, 21~2532~ 23~266~ 28~2139~ [29] 33~5143~ 34~1223~ 35~5281~ 37~73~ 41~4295~ 42~2254~,'),
  (8939, 11, 6, 35, 'And he carved thereon cherubims and palm trees and open flowers: and covered them with gold fitted upon the carved work.', '2~07049~ [3] 4~03742~ 7~08561~ 9~06362~ 10~06731~: 12~06823~ [13] 15~02091~ 16~03474~ 20~02707~.'),
  (24248, 41, 1, 23, 'And there was in their synagogue a man with an unclean spirit; and he cried out,', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~2258~ 3~1722~ 4~846~ 5~4864~ 7~444~ 8~1722~ 10~169~ 11~4151~; 12~2532~ 15~349~,'),
  (2764, 3, 1, 14, 'And if the burnt sacrifice for his offering to the LORD be of fowls, then he shall bring his offering of turtledoves, or of young pigeons.', '4~05930~ 7~07133~ 10~03068~ [11] 13~05775~, 17~07126~ 19~07133~ 21~08449~, 24~01121~ 25~03123~.'),
  (12275, 15, 10, 14, 'Let now our rulers of all the congregation stand, and let all them which have taken strange wives in our cities come at appointed times, and with them the elders of every city, and the judges thereof, until the fierce wrath of our God for this matter be turned from us.', '3~08269~ 7~06951~ 8~05975~, 15~03427~ 16~05237~ 17~0802~ 20~05892~ 21~0935~ 23~02163~ 24~06256~, 29~02205~ 32~05892~, 35~08199~ 39~02740~ 40~0639~ 43~0430~ 46~01697~ 48~07725~'),
  (19621, 24, 27, 16, 'Also I spake to the priests and to all this people, saying, Thus saith the LORD; Hearken not to the words of your prophets that prophesy unto you, saying, Behold, the vessels of the LORD''S house shall now shortly be brought again from Babylon: for they prophesy a lie unto you.', '2~01696~ 5~03548~ 10~05971~, 11~0559~, 13~0559~ 15~03068~; 16~08085~ 20~01697~ 23~05030~ 25~05012~ 28~0559~, 31~03627~ 34~03068~ 35~01004~ 38~04120~ 41~07725~ 43~0894~: 46~05012~ 48~08267~'),
  (8643, 10, 22, 33, 'God is my strength and power: And he maketh my way perfect.', '0~0410~ [1] 3~04581~ [4] 5~02428~: 8~05425~ 10~01870~ 11~08549~.'),
  (3554, 3, 26, 25, 'And I will bring a sword upon you, that shall avenge the quarrel of my covenant: and when ye are gathered together within your cities, I will send the pestilence among you; and ye shall be delivered into the hand of the enemy.', '3~0935~ 5~02719~ 10~05358~ 12~05359~ [14] 15~01285~: 21~0622~ 22~0413~ 24~05892~, 27~07971~ 29~01698~ 30~08432~ 36~05414~ 39~03027~ 42~0341~.'),
  (16001, 19, 119, 94, 'I am thine, save me; for I have sought thy precepts.', '&para; [1] 3~03467~ 8~01875~ 10~06490~.'),
  (7141, 8, 1, 7, 'Wherefore she went forth out of the place where she was, and her two daughters in law with her; and they went on the way to return unto the land of Judah.', '3~03318~ 7~04725~ 13~08147~ 16~03618~ 21~03212~ 24~01870~ 26~07725~ 29~0776~ 31~03063~.'),
  (18342, 23, 36, 3, 'Then came forth unto him Eliakim, Hilkiah''s son, which was over the house, and Shebna the scribe, and Joah, Asaph''s son, the recorder.', '2~03318~ 5~0471~, 6~02518~ 7~01121~, 12~01004~, 14~07644~ 16~05608~, 18~03098~, 19~0623~ 20~01121~, 22~02142~.'),
  (12370, 16, 4, 2, 'And he spake before his brethren and the army of Samaria, and said, What do these feeble Jews? will they fortify themselves? will they sacrifice? will they make an end in a day? will they revive the stones out of the heaps of the rubbish which are burned?', '2~0559~ 3~06440~ 5~0251~ 8~02428~ 10~08111~, 12~0559~, 14~06213~ 16~0537~ 17~03064~? 20~05800~ 24~02076~? 29~03615~ 32~03117~? 35~02421~ 37~068~ 41~06194~ 44~06083~ 47~08313~?'),
  (2929, 3, 8, 7, 'And he put upon him the coat, and girded him with the girdle, and clothed him with the robe, and put the ephod upon him, and he girded him with the curious girdle of the ephod, and bound it unto him therewith.', '2~05414~ 6~03801~, 8~02296~ 12~073~, 14~03847~ 18~04598~, 20~05414~ 22~0646~ 27~02296~ 32~02805~ 35~0646~, 37~0640~ [38]'),
  (9588, 12, 3, 4, 'And Mesha king of Moab was a sheepmaster, and rendered unto the king of Israel an hundred thousand lambs, and an hundred thousand rams, with the wool.', '1~04338~ 2~04428~ 4~04124~ 7~05349~, 9~07725~ 12~04428~ 14~03478~ 16~03967~ 17~0505~ 18~03733~, 21~03967~ 22~0505~ 23~0352~, 26~06785~.'),
  (7877, 9, 25, 9, 'And when David''s young men came, they spake to Nabal according to all those words in the name of David, and ceased.', '2~01732~ 4~05288~ 5~0935~, 7~01696~ 9~05037~ 14~01697~ 17~08034~ 19~01732~, 21~05117~.'),
  (26813, 43, 18, 13, 'And led him away to Annas first; for he was father in law to Caiaphas, which was the high priest that same year.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~520~ 2~846~ 3~520~ 4~4314~ 5~452~ 6~4412~; 7~1063~ 9~2258~ 12~3995~ 14~2533~, 15~3739~ 16~2258~ 19~749~ 21~1565~ 22~1763~.'),
  (4327, 4, 20, 11, 'And Moses lifted up his hand, and with his rod he smote the rock twice: and the water came out abundantly, and the congregation drank, and their beasts also.', '1~04872~ 3~07311~ 5~03027~, 9~04294~ 11~05221~ 13~05553~ 14~06471~: 17~04325~ 19~03318~ 20~07227~, 23~05712~ 24~08354~, 27~01165~ [28]'),
  (24514, 41, 8, 3, 'And if I send them away fasting to their own houses, they will faint by the way: for divers of them came from far.', '0~2532~ 1~1437~ 3~630~ 4~846~ 5~630~ 6~3523~ 7~1519~ 9~846~ 10~3624~, 13~1590~ 14~1722~ 16~3598~: 17~1063~ 18~5100~ 20~846~ 21~2240~ 23~3113~.'),
  (14219, 19, 22, 6, 'But I am a worm, and no man; a reproach of men, and despised of the people.', '[2] 4~08438~, 7~0376~; 9~02781~ 11~0120~, 13~0959~ 16~05971~.'),
  (3258, 3, 18, 2, 'Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, I am the LORD your God.', '0~01696~ 3~01121~ 5~03478~, 7~0559~ 13~03068~ 15~0430~.'),
  (25933, 42, 22, 55, 'And when they had kindled a fire in the midst of the hall, and were set down together, Peter sat down among them.', '0~1161~ 2~846~ 4~681~ 6~4442~ 7~1722~ 9~3319~ 12~833~, 13~2532~ 17~4776~, 18~4074~ 20~2521~ 21~1722~ 22~3319~* 23~846~.'),
  (21308, 26, 33, 19, 'But if the wicked turn from his wickedness, and do that which is lawful and right, he shall live thereby.', '3~07563~ 4~07725~ 7~07564~, 9~06213~ 13~04941~ 15~06666~, 18~02421~'),
  (21010, 26, 22, 25, 'There is a conspiracy of her prophets in the midst thereof, like a roaring lion ravening the prey; they have devoured souls; they have taken the treasure and precious things; they have made her many widows in the midst thereof.', '[0 1] 3~07195~ 6~05030~ 9~08432~ 13~07580~ 14~0738~ 15~02963~ 17~02964~; 20~0398~ 21~05315~; 24~03947~ 26~02633~ 29~03366~; 34~07235~ 35~0490~ 38~08432~'),
  (17033, 20, 22, 9, 'He that hath a bountiful eye shall be blessed; for he giveth of his bread to the poor.', '&para; 4~02896~ 5~05869~ 8~01288~; 11~05414~ 14~03899~ 17~01800~.'),
  (2392, 2, 30, 5, 'And thou shalt make the staves of shittim wood, and overlay them with gold.', '3~06213~ 5~0905~ [6] 7~07848~ 8~06086~, 10~06823~ 13~02091~.'),
  (80, 1, 3, 24, 'So he drove out the man; and he placed at the east of the garden of Eden Cherubims, and a flaming sword which turned every way, to keep the way of the tree of life.', '3~01644~ 5~0120~; 8~07931~ 11~06924~ 14~01588~ 16~05731~ 17~03742~, 20~03858~ 21~02719~ 25~02015~, 27~08104~ 29~01870~ 32~06086~ 34~02416~.'),
  (5243, 5, 11, 29, 'And it shall come to pass, when the LORD thy God hath brought thee in unto the land whither thou goest to possess it, that thou shalt put the blessing upon mount Gerizim, and the curse upon mount Ebal.', '8~03068~ 10~0430~ 14~0935~ 17~0776~ 20~0935~ 22~03423~ 27~05414~ 29~01293~ 31~02022~ 32~01630~, 35~07045~ 37~02022~ 38~05858~.'),
  (28724, 46, 14, 30, 'If any thing be revealed to another that sitteth by, let the first hold his peace.', '0~1437~ [1 1~1161~ 2] 4~601~ 6~243~ 9~2521~, 10~4601~ 12~4413~ 15~4601~.'),
  (7821, 9, 23, 4, 'Then David inquired of the LORD yet again. And the LORD answered him and said, Arise, go down to Keilah: for I will deliver the Philistines into thine hand.', '1~01732~ 2~07592~ 5~03068~ 7~03254~. 10~03068~ 11~06030~ 14~0559~, 15~06965~, 17~03381~ 19~07084~; 23~05414~ 25~06430~ 28~03027~.'),
  (7587, 9, 15, 20, 'And Saul said unto Samuel, Yea, I have obeyed the voice of the LORD, and have gone the way which the LORD sent me, and have brought Agag the king of Amalek, and have utterly destroyed the Amalekites.', '1~07586~ 2~0559~ 4~08050~, 8~08085~ 10~06963~ 13~03068~, 16~03212~ 18~01870~ 21~03068~ 22~07971~ 26~0935~ 27~090~ 29~04428~ 31~06002~, 35~02763~ 37~06002~.'),
  (15771, 19, 109, 7, 'When he shall be judged, let him be condemned: and let his prayer become sin.', '4~08199~, 7~03318~ 8~07563~: 12~08605~ 14~02401~.'),
  (6688, 7, 6, 27, 'Then Gideon took ten men of his servants, and did as the LORD had said unto him: and so it was, because he feared his father''s household, and the men of the city, that he could not do it by day, that he did it by night.', '1~01439~ 2~03947~ 3~06235~ 4~0582~ 7~05650~, 9~06213~ 12~03068~ 14~01696~ [18] 23~03372~ 25~01~ 26~01004~, 29~0582~ 32~05892~, 37~06213~ [38] 40~03119~, 43~06213~ [44] 46~03915~.'),
  (21226, 26, 30, 13, 'Thus saith the Lord GOD; I will also destroy the idols, and I will cause their images to cease out of Noph; and there shall be no more a prince of the land of Egypt: and I will put a fear in the land of Egypt.', '1~0559~ 3~0136~ 4~03069~; 8~06~ 10~01544~, [15] 16~0457~ 18~07673~ 21~05297~; 29~05387~ 32~0776~ 34~04714~: 38~05414~ 40~03374~ 43~0776~ 45~04714~.'),
  (11443, 14, 11, 20, 'And after her he took Maachah the daughter of Absalom; which bare him Abijah, and Attai, and Ziza, and Shelomith.', '1~0310~ 4~03947~ 5~04601~ 7~01323~ 9~053~; 11~03205~ 13~029~, 15~06262~, 17~02124~, 19~08019~.'),
  (11571, 14, 18, 20, 'Then there came out a spirit, and stood before the LORD, and said, I will entice him. And the LORD said unto him, Wherewith?', '3~03318~ 5~07307~, 7~05975~ 8~06440~ 10~03068~, 12~0559~, 15~06601~ 19~03068~ 20~0559~'),
  (4278, 4, 18, 16, 'And those that are to be redeemed from a month old shalt thou redeem, according to thine estimation, for the money of five shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary, which is twenty gerahs.', '6~06299~ 9~02320~ 10~01121~ 13~06299~, 17~06187~, 20~03701~ 22~02568~ 23~08255~, 26~08255~ 29~06944~, [31] 32~06242~ 33~01626~.'),
  (5417, 5, 19, 5, 'As when a man goeth into the wood with his neighbour to hew wood, and his hand fetcheth a stroke with the ax to cut down the tree, and the head slippeth from the helve, and lighteth upon his neighbour, that he die; he shall flee unto one of those cities, and live:', '4~0935~ 7~03293~ 10~07453~ 12~02404~ 13~06086~, 16~03027~ 19~05080~ 22~01631~ 25~03772~ 27~06086~, 30~01270~ 31~05394~ 34~06086~, 36~04672~ 39~07453~, 42~04191~; 45~05127~ 47~0259~ 50~05892~, 52~02425~:'),
  (26880, 43, 19, 40, 'Then took they the body of Jesus, and wound it in linen clothes with the spices, as the manner of the Jews is to bury.', '0~3767~ 2~2983~ 4~4983~ 6~2424~, 7~2532~ 8~1210~ 9~846~ 12~3608~ 13~3326~ 15~759~, 16~2531~ 18~1485~ 21~2453~ 22~2076~ 24~1779~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (10627, 13, 9, 4, 'Uthai the son of Ammihud, the son of Omri, the son of Imri, the son of Bani, of the children of Pharez the son of Judah.', '0~05793~ 2~01121~ 4~05989~, 6~01121~ 8~06018~, 10~01121~ 12~0566~, 14~01121~ 16~01137~, 19~01121~ 21~06557~ 23~01121~ 25~03063~.'),
  (10966, 13, 21, 24, 'And king David said to Ornan, Nay; but I will verily buy it for the full price: for I will not take that which is thine for the LORD, nor offer burnt offerings without cost.', '1~04428~ 2~01732~ 3~0559~ 5~0771~, 10~07069~ 11~07069~ 15~04392~ 16~03701~: 21~05375~ [22] [24] 28~03068~, 30~05927~ 32~05930~ 34~02600~.'),
  (25397, 42, 10, 22, 'All things are delivered to me of my Father: and no man knoweth who the Son is, but the Father; and who the Father is, but the Son, and he to whom the Son will reveal him.', '1~3956~ 3~3860~ 5~3427~ 6~5259~ 7~3450~ 8~3962~: 9~2532~ 11~3762~ 12~1097~ 13~5101~ 15~5207~ 16~2076~, 17~1508~ 19~3962~; 20~2532~ 21~5101~ 23~3962~ 24~2076~, 25~1508~ 27~5207~, 28~2532~ [29] 31~1437~ 32~3739~ 33~5207~ 34~1014~ 35~601~ [36]'),
  (8188, 10, 7, 1, 'And it came to pass, when the king sat in his house, and the LORD had given him rest round about from all his enemies;', '&para; 7~04428~ 8~03427~ 11~01004~, 14~03068~ 18~05117~ 20~05439~ 24~0341~;'),
  (168, 1, 7, 8, 'Of clean beasts, and of beasts that are not clean, and of fowls, and of every thing that creepeth upon the earth,', '1~02889~ 2~0929~, 5~0929~ [7] 9~02889~, 12~05775~, 18~07430~ 21~0127~,'),
  (21576, 26, 42, 15, 'Now when he had made an end of measuring the inner house, he brought me forth toward the gate whose prospect is toward the east, and measured it round about.', '&para; 6~03615~ 8~04060~ 10~06442~ 11~01004~, 15~03318~ 16~01870~ 18~08179~ 20~06440~ [21] 22~01870~ 24~06921~, 26~04058~ 29~05439~.'),
  (12659, 16, 12, 26, 'These were in the days of Joiakim the son of Jeshua, the son of Jozadak, and in the days of Nehemiah the governor, and of Ezra the priest, the scribe.', '[1] 4~03117~ 6~03113~ 8~01121~ 10~03442~, 12~01121~ 14~03136~, 18~03117~ 20~05166~ 22~06346~, 25~05830~ 27~03548~, 29~05608~.'),
  (27083, 44, 5, 8, 'And Peter answered unto her, Tell me whether ye sold the land for so much? And she said, Yea, for so much.', '0~1161~ 1~4074~ 2~611~ 4~846~, 5~2036~ 6~3427~ 7~1487~ 9~591~ 11~5564~ 14~5118~? 15~1161~ 17~2036~, 18~3483~, 21~5118~.'),
  (15697, 19, 106, 37, 'Yea, they sacrificed their sons and their daughters unto devils,', '2~02076~ 4~01121~ 7~01323~ 9~07700~,'),
  (22773, 35, 2, 16, 'Thou art filled with shame for glory: drink thou also, and let thy foreskin be uncovered: the cup of the LORD''S right hand shall be turned unto thee, and shameful spewing shall be on thy glory.', '2~07646~ 4~07036~ 6~03519~: 7~08354~ 15~06188~: 17~03563~ 20~03068~ 22~03225~ 25~05437~ 30~07022~ [31 32] 35~03519~.'),
  (15889, 19, 118, 11, 'They compassed me about; yea, they compassed me about: but in the name of the LORD I will destroy them.', '3~05437~; 8~05437~: 12~08034~ 15~03068~ 18~04135~'),
  (22067, 27, 11, 22, 'And with the arms of a flood shall they be overflown from before him, and shall be broken; yea, also the prince of the covenant.', '3~02220~ 6~07858~ 10~07857~ 12~06440~ 17~07665~; 21~05057~ 24~01285~.'),
  (7805, 9, 22, 11, 'Then the king sent to call Ahimelech the priest, the son of Ahitub, and all his father''s house, the priests that were in Nob: and they came all of them to the king.', '2~04428~ 3~07971~ 5~07121~ 6~0288~ 8~03548~, 10~01121~ 12~0285~, 16~01~ 17~01004~, 19~03548~ [21] 23~05011~: 26~0935~ 32~04428~.'),
  (10196, 12, 23, 23, 'But in the eighteenth year of king Josiah, wherein this passover was holden to the LORD in Jerusalem.', '3~06240~ 4~08083~* 5~08141~ 7~04428~ 8~02977~, [9] 11~06453~ 13~06213~ 16~03068~ 18~03389~.'),
  (16132, 19, 127, 2, 'It is vain for you to rise up early, to sit up late, to eat the bread of sorrows: for so he giveth his beloved sleep.', '[0 1] 2~07723~ 7~06965~ 8~07925~, 11~03427~ 12~0309~, 14~0398~ 16~03899~ 18~06089~: [19] 22~05414~ 24~03039~ 25~08142~.'),
  (26125, 43, 2, 15, 'And when he had made a scourge of small cords, he drove them all out of the temple, and the sheep, and the oxen; and poured out the changers'' money, and overthrew the tables;', '0~2532~ 4~4160~ 6~5416~ 7~1537~ 9~4979~, 11~1544~ 13~3956~ 15~1537~ 17~2411~, 18~5037~ 20~4263~, 21~2532~ 23~1016~; 24~2532~ 26~1632~ 28~2855~ 29~2772~, 30~2532~ 31~390~ 33~5132~;'),
  (2091, 2, 21, 9, 'And if he have betrothed her unto his son, he shall deal with her after the manner of daughters.', '4~03259~ 8~01121~, 11~06213~ 16~04941~ 18~01323~.'),
  (22244, 28, 10, 10, 'It is in my desire that I should chastise them; and the people shall be gathered against them, when they shall bind themselves in their two furrows.', '[0 1] 4~0185~ 8~03256~ 12~05971~ 15~0622~ 21~0631~ 25~08147~ 26~05869~.'),
  (16680, 20, 10, 15, 'The rich man''s wealth is his strong city: the destruction of the poor is their poverty.', '&para; 2~06223~ 3~01952~ [4] 6~05797~ 7~07151~: 9~04288~ 12~01800~ [13] 15~07389~.'),
  (7836, 9, 23, 19, 'Then came up the Ziphites to Saul to Gibeah, saying, Doth not David hide himself with us in strong holds in the wood, in the hill of Hachilah, which is on the south of Jeshimon?', '&para; 2~05927~ 4~02130~ 6~07586~ 8~01390~, 9~0559~, 12~01732~ 13~05641~ 19~04679~ 22~02793~, 25~01389~ 27~02444~, [29] 32~03225~ 34~03452~?'),
  (7758, 9, 20, 21, 'And, behold, I will send a lad, saying, Go, find out the arrows. If I expressly say unto the lad, Behold, the arrows are on this side of thee, take them; then come thou: for there is peace to thee, and no hurt; as the LORD liveth.', '4~07971~ 6~05288~, [7] 8~03212~, 10~04672~ 12~02671~. 15~0559~ 16~0559~ 19~05288~, 22~02671~ [23] 29~03947~ 32~0935~ [35 36] 37~07965~ 42~01697~; [43] 45~03068~ 46~02416~.'),
  (12337, 16, 3, 1, 'Then Eliashib the high priest rose up with his brethren the priests, and they builded the sheep gate; they sanctified it, and set up the doors of it; even unto the tower of Meah they sanctified it, unto the tower of Hananeel.', '&para; 1~0475~ 3~01419~ 4~03548~ 6~06965~ 9~0251~ 11~03548~, 14~01129~ 16~06629~ 17~08179~; 19~06942~ 23~05975~ 25~01817~ 31~04026~ 33~03968~ 35~06942~ 39~04026~ 41~02606~.'),
  (19926, 24, 38, 22, 'And, behold, all the women that are left in the king of Judah''s house shall be brought forth to the king of Babylon''s princes, and those women shall say, Thy friends have set thee on, and have prevailed against thee: thy feet are sunk in the mire, and they are turned away back.', '4~0802~ 7~07604~ 10~04428~ 12~03063~ 13~01004~ [14 15] 17~03318~ 20~04428~ 22~0894~ 23~08269~, [26] 28~0559~, 30~07965~ 31~0582~ 34~05496~, 37~03201~ 41~07272~ 43~02883~ 46~01206~, [47] 51~05472~ 52~0268~.'),
  (1702, 2, 7, 12, 'For they cast down every man his rod, and they became serpents: but Aaron''s rod swallowed up their rods.', '3~07993~ 5~0376~ 7~04294~, 11~08577~: 13~0175~ 14~04294~ 16~01104~ 18~04294~.'),
  (26212, 43, 4, 41, 'And many more believed because of his own word;', '0~2532~ 1~4183~ 2~4119~ 3~4100~ 4~1223~ 7~846~ 8~3056~;'),
  (6865, 7, 11, 29, 'Then the spirit of the LORD came upon Jephthah, and he passed over Gilead, and Manasseh, and passed over Mizpeh of Gilead, and from Mizpeh of Gilead he passed over unto the children of Ammon.', '&para; 2~07307~ 5~03068~ 8~03316~, 12~05674~ 13~01568~, 15~04519~, 18~05674~ 19~04708~ 21~01568~, 24~04708~ 26~01568~ 29~05674~ [30] 32~01121~ 34~05983~.'),
  (15870, 19, 116, 13, 'I will take the cup of salvation, and call upon the name of the LORD.', '2~05375~ 4~03563~ 6~03444~, 8~07121~ 11~08034~ 14~03068~.'),
  (27596, 44, 18, 23, 'And after he had spent some time there, he departed, and went over all the country of Galatia and Phrygia in order, strengthening all the disciples.', '0~2532~ 4~4160~ 5~5100~ 6~5550~ [7] 9~1831~, 12~1330~ [13] 15~5561~ 17~1054~ 18~2532~ 19~5435~ 21~2517~, 22~1991~ 23~3956~ 25~3101~.'),
  (23145, 39, 3, 15, 'And now we call the proud happy; yea, they that work wickedness are set up; yea, they that tempt God are even delivered.', '3~0833~ 5~02086~ 6~0833~; 10~06213~ 11~07564~ 14~01129~; [16 17] 18~0974~ 19~0430~ 22~04422~.'),
  (10380, 13, 3, 11, 'Joram his son, Ahaziah his son, Joash his son,', '0~03141~ 2~01121~, 3~0274~ 5~01121~, 6~03101~ 8~01121~,'),
  (17575, 22, 2, 12, 'The flowers appear on the earth; the time of the singing of birds is come, and the voice of the turtle is heard in our land;', '1~05339~ 2~07200~ 5~0776~; 7~06256~ 10~02158~ [11 12] 14~05060~, 17~06963~ 20~08449~ 22~08085~ 25~0776~;'),
  (7224, 9, 1, 5, 'But unto Hannah he gave a worthy portion; for he loved Hannah: but the LORD had shut up her womb.', '2~02584~ 4~05414~ 5~0259~ 6~0639~ 7~04490~; 10~0157~ 11~02584~: 14~03068~ 17~05462~ 19~07358~.'),
  (23594, 40, 13, 45, 'Again, the kingdom of heaven is like unto a merchant man, seeking goodly pearls:', '0~3825~, 2~932~ 4~3772~ 5~2076~ 6~3664~ 9~1713~ 10~444~, 11~2212~ 12~2570~ 13~3135~:'),
  (27516, 44, 16, 17, 'The same followed Paul and us, and cried, saying, These men are the servants of the most high God, which shew unto us the way of salvation.', '1~3778~ 2~2628~ 3~3972~ 4~2532~ 5~2254~, 7~2896~, 8~3004~, 9~3778~ 10~444~ 11~1526~ 13~1401~ 17~5310~ 18~2316~, 19~3748~ 20~2605~ 22~2254~ 24~3598~ 26~4991~.'),
  (16417, 20, 1, 8, 'My son, hear the instruction of thy father, and forsake not the law of thy mother:', '1~01121~, 2~08085~ 4~04148~ 7~01~, 9~05203~ 12~08451~ 15~0517~:'),
  (3426, 3, 23, 19, 'Then ye shall sacrifice one kid of the goats for a sin offering, and two lambs of the first year for a sacrifice of peace offerings.', '3~06213~ 4~0259~ 5~08163~ 8~05795~ 12~02403~, 14~08147~ 15~03532~ 18~01121~ 19~08141~ 22~02077~ 25~08002~.'),
  (27573, 44, 17, 34, 'Howbeit certain men clave unto him, and believed: among the which was Dionysius the Areopagite, and a woman named Damaris, and others with them.', '0~1161~ 1~5100~ 2~435~ 3~2853~ 5~846~, 7~4100~: 8~1722~ 10~2532~ [11] 11~3739~ 12~1354~ 14~698~, 15~2532~ 17~1135~ 18~3686~ 19~1152~, 20~2532~ 21~2087~ 22~4862~ 23~846~.'),
  (5631, 5, 28, 14, 'And thou shalt not go aside from any of the words which I command thee this day, to the right hand, or to the left, to go after other gods to serve them.', '5~05493~ 10~01697~ 13~06680~ 16~03117~, [17] 20~03225~, [22] 24~08040~, 26~03212~ 27~0310~ 28~0312~ 29~0430~ 31~05647~'),
  (12585, 16, 10, 27, 'Malluch, Harim, Baanah.', '0~04409~, 1~02766~, 2~01196~.'),
  (15521, 19, 100, 4, 'Enter into his gates with thanksgiving, and into his courts with praise: be thankful unto him, and bless his name.', '0~0935~ 3~08179~ 5~08426~, [6] 9~02691~ 11~08416~: 13~03034~ [16] 17~01288~ 19~08034~.'),
  (28273, 45, 12, 12, 'Rejoicing in hope; patient in tribulation; continuing instant in prayer;', '0~5463~ 2~1680~; 3~5278~ 5~2347~; 7~4342~ 9~4335~;'),
  (2942, 3, 8, 20, 'And he cut the ram into pieces; and Moses burnt the head, and the pieces, and the fat.', '2~05408~ 4~0352~ 6~05409~; 8~04872~ 9~06999~ 11~07218~, 14~05409~, 17~06309~.'),
  (22762, 35, 2, 5, 'Yea also, because he transgresseth by wine, he is a proud man, neither keepeth at home, who enlargeth his desire as hell, and is as death, and cannot be satisfied, but gathereth unto him all nations, and heapeth unto him all people:', '&para; 4~0898~ 6~03196~, [7 8] 10~03093~ 11~01397~, 15~05115~, 17~07337~ 19~05315~ 21~07585~, [23] 25~04194~, 29~07646~, 31~0622~ 35~01471~, 37~06908~ 41~05971~:'),
  (13443, 18, 23, 15, 'Therefore am I troubled at his presence: when I consider, I am afraid of him.', '3~0926~ 6~06440~: 9~0995~, 12~06342~'),
  (24295, 41, 2, 25, 'And he said unto them, Have ye never read what David did, when he had need, and was an hungred, he, and they that were with him?', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 7~3763~ 8~314~ 9~5101~ 10~1138~ 11~4160~, 12~3753~ 14~2192~ 15~5532~, 16~2532~ 19~3983~, 20~846~, 21~2532~ 25~3326~ 26~846~?'),
  (20364, 25, 3, 1, 'I am the man that hath seen affliction by the rod of his wrath.', '&para; [1] 3~01397~ [4] 6~07200~ 7~06040~ 10~07626~ 13~05678~.'),
  (1785, 2, 10, 3, 'And Moses and Aaron came in unto Pharaoh, and said unto him, Thus saith the LORD God of the Hebrews, How long wilt thou refuse to humble thyself before me? let my people go, that they may serve me.', '1~04872~ 3~0175~ 5~0935~ 7~06547~, 9~0559~ 13~0559~ 15~03068~ 16~0430~ 19~05680~, 21~04970~ 24~03985~ 26~06031~ 28~06440~ 32~05971~ 33~07971~, 37~05647~'),
  (20567, 26, 5, 12, 'A third part of thee shall die with the pestilence, and with famine shall they be consumed in the midst of thee: and a third part shall fall by the sword round about thee; and I will scatter a third part into all the winds, and I will draw out a sword after them.', '2~07992~ 6~04191~ 9~01698~, 12~07458~ 16~03615~ 19~08432~ 25~07992~ 27~05307~ 30~02719~ 32~05439~ 37~02219~ 40~07992~ 44~07307~, 49~07324~ 51~02719~ 52~0310~'),
  (6463, 6, 22, 30, 'And when Phinehas the priest, and the princes of the congregation and heads of the thousands of Israel which were with him, heard the words that the children of Reuben and the children of Gad and the children of Manasseh spake, it pleased them.', '&para; 2~06372~ 4~03548~, 7~05387~ 10~05712~ 12~07218~ 15~0505~ 17~03478~ [19] 22~08085~ 24~01697~ 27~01121~ 29~07205~ 32~01121~ 34~01410~ 37~01121~ 39~04519~ 40~01696~, 42~03190~ 43~05869~*'),
  (24121, 40, 26, 57, 'And they that had laid hold on Jesus led him away to Caiaphas the high priest, where the scribes and the elders were assembled.', '&para; 0~1161~ 5~2902~ 7~2424~ [9] 10~520~ 11~4314~ 12~2533~ 15~749~, 16~3699~ 18~1122~ 19~2532~ 21~4245~ 23~4863~.'),
  (18004, 23, 17, 12, 'Woe to the multitude of many people, which make a noise like the noise of the seas; and to the rushing of nations, that make a rushing like the rushing of mighty waters!', '&para; 0~01945~ 3~01995~ 5~07227~ 6~05971~, [7] 10~01993~ 13~01993~ 16~03220~; 20~07588~ 22~03816~, [23] 29~07582~ 31~03524~ 32~04325~!'),
  (19962, 24, 40, 12, 'Even all the Jews returned out of all places whither they were driven, and came to the land of Judah, to Gedaliah, unto Mizpah, and gathered wine and summer fruits very much.', '3~03064~ 5~07725~ 8~04725~ 12~05080~, 14~0935~ 17~0776~ 19~03063~, 21~01436~, 23~04708~, 25~0622~ 26~03196~ 29~07019~ 30~03966~ 31~07235~.'),
  (10907, 13, 18, 9, 'Now when Tou king of Hamath heard how David had smitten all the host of Hadarezer king of Zobah;', '&para; 2~08583~ 3~04428~ 5~02574~ 6~08085~ 8~01732~ 10~05221~ 13~02428~ 15~01928~ 16~04428~ 18~06678~;'),
  (24412, 41, 5, 38, 'And he cometh to the house of the ruler of the synagogue, and seeth the tumult, and them that wept and wailed greatly.', '0~2532~ 2~2064~ 3~1519~ 5~3624~ 11~752~, 12~2532~ 13~2334~ 15~2351~, 19~2799~ 20~2532~ 21~214~ 22~4183~.'),
  (28337, 45, 15, 18, 'For I will not dare to speak of any of those things which Christ hath not wrought by me, to make the Gentiles obedient, by word and deed,', '0~1063~ 2~5111~ 3~3756~ 4~5111~ 6~2980~ 8~5100~ 12~3739~ 13~5547~ 14~2716~ 15~3756~ 16~2716~ 17~1223~ 18~1700~, 20~1519~ 22~1484~ 23~5218~, 25~3056~ 26~2532~ 27~2041~,'),
  (8933, 11, 6, 29, 'And he carved all the walls of the house round about with carved figures of cherubims and palm trees and open flowers, within and without.', '2~07049~ 5~07023~ 8~01004~ 10~04524~ 12~06603~ 13~04734~ 15~03742~ 18~08561~ 20~06362~ 21~06731~, 22~06441~ 24~02435~.'),
  (22267, 28, 12, 6, 'Therefore turn thou to thy God: keep mercy and judgment, and wait on thy God continually.', '1~07725~ 5~0430~: 6~08104~ 7~02617~ 9~04941~, 11~06960~ 14~0430~ 15~08548~.'),
  (10219, 12, 24, 9, 'And he did that which was evil in the sight of the LORD, according to all that his father had done.', '2~06213~ [3 5] 6~07451~ 9~05869~ 12~03068~, 18~01~ 20~06213~.'),
  (18880, 23, 63, 5, 'And I looked, and there was none to help; and I wondered that there was none to uphold: therefore mine own arm brought salvation unto me; and my fury, it upheld me.', '2~05027~, [4 5] 8~05826~; 11~08074~ [13 14] 17~05564~: 21~02220~ 23~03467~ 28~02534~, 30~05564~'),
  (14997, 19, 71, 12, 'O God, be not far from me: O my God, make haste for my help.', '1~0430~, 4~07368~ 9~0430~, 11~02363~ 14~05833~.'),
  (5449, 5, 20, 16, 'But of the cities of these people, which the LORD thy God doth give thee for an inheritance, thou shalt save alive nothing that breatheth:', '3~05892~ 6~05971~, 9~03068~ 11~0430~ 13~05414~ [15] 17~05159~, 21~02421~ 24~05397~:'),
  (26913, 43, 20, 30, 'And many other signs truly did Jesus in the presence of his disciples, which are not written in this book:', '0~2532~ 1~4183~ 2~243~ 3~4592~ 4~3767~ 5~3303~* 6~4160~ 7~2424~ 10~1799~ 12~846~ 13~3101~, 14~3739~ 15~2076~ 16~3756~ 17~1125~ 18~1722~ 19~5129~ 20~975~:'),
  (11, 1, 1, 11, 'And God said, Let the earth bring forth grass, the herb yielding seed, and the fruit tree yielding fruit after his kind, whose seed is in itself, upon the earth: and it was so.', '1~0430~ 2~0559~, 5~0776~ 7~01876~ 8~01877~, 10~06212~ 11~02232~ 12~02233~, [13] 15~06529~ 16~06086~ 17~06213~ 18~06529~ 21~04327~, 22~0834~ 23~02233~ [24] 29~0776~:'),
  (7051, 7, 19, 20, 'And the old man said, Peace be with thee; howsoever let all thy wants lie upon me; only lodge not in the street.', '2~02205~ 3~0376~ 4~0559~, 5~07965~ [6] 9~07535~ [10] 13~04270~ [14] 18~03885~ 22~07339~.'),
  (22066, 27, 11, 21, 'And in his estate shall stand up a vile person, to whom they shall not give the honour of the kingdom: but he shall come in peaceably, and obtain the kingdom by flatteries.', '&para; 3~03653~ 6~05975~ 9~0959~, 15~05414~ 17~01935~ 20~04438~: 24~0935~ 26~07962~, 28~02388~ 30~04438~ 32~02519~.'),
  (6388, 6, 20, 9, 'These were the cities appointed for all the children of Israel, and for the stranger that sojourneth among them, that whosoever killeth any person at unawares might flee thither, and not die by the hand of the avenger of blood, until he stood before the congregation.', '3~05892~ 4~04152~ 8~01121~ 10~03478~, 14~01616~ 16~01481~ 17~08432~ 21~05221~ [22] 23~05315~ 25~07684~ 27~05127~ 31~04191~ 34~03027~ 37~01350~ 39~01818~, 42~05975~ 43~06440~ 45~05712~.'),
  (21810, 27, 2, 43, 'And whereas thou sawest iron mixed with miry clay, they shall mingle themselves with the seed of men: but they shall not cleave one to another, even as iron is not mixed with clay.', '1~01768~ 3~02370~ 4~06523~ 5~06151~ 7~02917~ 8~02635~, 12~01934~ 13~06151~* 16~02234~ 18~0606~: 21~01934~ 22~03809~ 23~01693~ 24~01836~ 25~05974~ 26~01836~, 27~01888~ 29~06523~ 31~03809~ 32~06151~ 34~02635~.'),
  (22885, 37, 2, 21, 'Speak to Zerubbabel, governor of Judah, saying, I will shake the heavens and the earth;', '0~0559~ 2~02216~, 3~06346~ 5~03063~, 6~0559~, 9~07493~ 11~08064~ 14~0776~;'),
  (14, 1, 1, 14, 'And God said, Let there be lights in the firmament of the heaven to divide the day from the night; and let them be for signs, and for seasons, and for days, and years:', '&para; 1~0430~ 2~0559~, 6~03974~ 9~07549~ 12~08064~ 14~0914~ 16~03117~ 19~03915~; 25~0226~, 28~04150~, 31~03117~, 33~08141~:'),
  (16053, 19, 119, 146, 'I cried unto thee; save me, and I shall keep thy testimonies.', '1~07121~ 4~03467~ 9~08104~ 11~05713~.'),
  (21243, 26, 31, 4, 'The waters made him great, the deep set him up on high with her rivers running round about his plants, and sent out her little rivers unto all the trees of the field.', '1~04325~ 4~01431~, 6~08415~ 11~07311~ 14~05104~ 15~01980~ 17~05439~ 19~04302~, 22~07971~ 25~08585~ 29~06086~ 32~07704~.'),
  (29007, 47, 11, 2, 'For I am jealous over you with godly jealousy: for I have espoused you to one husband, that I may present you as a chaste virgin to Christ.', '0~1063~ 3~2206~ 5~5209~ 7~2316~ 8~2205~: 9~1063~ 12~718~ 13~5209~ 15~1520~ 16~435~, 20~3936~ [21 22] 24~53~ 25~3933~ 27~5547~.'),
  (6121, 6, 11, 8, 'And the LORD delivered them into the hand of Israel, who smote them, and chased them unto great Zidon, and unto Misrephothmaim, and unto the valley of Mizpeh eastward; and they smote them, until they left them none remaining.', '2~03068~ 3~05414~ 7~03027~ 9~03478~, 11~05221~ 14~07291~ 17~07227~ 18~06721~, 21~04956~, 25~01237~ 27~04708~ 28~04217~; 31~05221~ 35~07604~ 38~08300~.'),
  (24623, 41, 10, 24, 'And the disciples were astonished at his words. But Jesus answereth again, and saith unto them, Children, how hard is it for them that trust in riches to enter into the kingdom of God!', '0~1161~ 2~3101~ 4~2284~ 5~1909~ 6~846~ 7~3056~. 8~1161~ 9~2424~ 10~611~ 11~3825~, 13~3004~ 15~846~, 16~5043~, 17~4459~ 18~1422~ 20~2076~ 24~3982~ 25~1909~ 26~5536~ 28~1525~ 29~1519~ 31~932~ 33~2316~!'),
  (6123, 6, 11, 10, 'And Joshua at that time turned back, and took Hazor, and smote the king thereof with the sword: for Hazor beforetime was the head of all those kingdoms.', '&para; 1~03091~ 4~06256~ 6~07725~, 8~03920~ 9~02674~, 11~05221~ 13~04428~ 17~02719~: 19~02674~ 20~06440~ 23~07218~ 27~04467~.'),
  (9331, 11, 17, 6, 'And the ravens brought him bread and flesh in the morning, and bread and flesh in the evening; and he drank of the brook.', '2~06158~ 3~0935~ 5~03899~ 7~01320~ 10~01242~, 12~03899~ 14~01320~ 17~06153~; 20~08354~ 23~05158~.'),
  (2649, 2, 38, 11, 'And for the north side the hangings were an hundred cubits, their pillars were twenty, and their sockets of brass twenty; the hooks of the pillars and their fillets of silver.', '3~06828~ 4~06285~ [5 7] 9~03967~ 10~0520~, 12~05982~ [13] 14~06242~, 17~0134~ 19~05178~ 20~06242~; 22~02053~ 25~05982~ 28~02838~ [29] 30~03701~.'),
  (8748, 11, 1, 23, 'And they told the king, saying, Behold Nathan the prophet. And when he was come in before the king, he bowed himself before the king with his face to the ground.', '2~05046~ 4~04428~, 5~0559~, 7~05416~ 9~05030~. 15~0935~ 16~06440~ 18~04428~, 20~07812~ 24~04428~ 27~0639~ 30~0776~.'),
  (29223, 49, 1, 1, 'Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, to the saints which are at Ephesus, and to the faithful in Christ Jesus:', '&para; 0~3972~, 2~652~ 4~2424~ 5~5547~ 6~1223~ 8~2307~ 10~2316~, 13~40~ 15~5607~ 16~1722~ 17~2181~, 18~2532~ 21~4103~ 22~1722~ 23~5547~ 24~2424~:'),
  (9191, 11, 12, 32, 'And Jeroboam ordained a feast in the eighth month, on the fifteenth day of the month, like unto the feast that is in Judah, and he offered upon the altar. So did he in Bethel, sacrificing unto the calves that he had made: and he placed in Bethel the priests of the high places which he had made.', '1~03379~ 2~06213~ 4~02282~ 7~08066~ 8~02320~, 11~06240~ 12~02568~* 13~03117~ 16~02320~, 20~02282~ [22] 24~03063~, 27~05927~ 30~04196~. 32~06213~ 35~01008~, 36~02076~ 39~05695~ 43~06213~: 46~05975~ 48~01008~ 50~03548~ 54~01116~ 58~06213~.'),
  (2651, 2, 38, 13, 'And for the east side eastward fifty cubits.', '3~06924~ 4~06285~ 5~04217~ 6~02572~ 7~0520~.'),
  (16515, 20, 4, 16, 'For they sleep not, except they have done mischief; and their sleep is taken away, unless they cause some to fall.', '2~03462~ 8~07489~; 11~08142~ 14~01497~, [18] 20~03782~'),
  (20775, 26, 16, 4, 'And as for thy nativity, in the day thou wast born thy navel was not cut, neither wast thou washed in water to supple thee; thou wast not salted at all, nor swaddled at all.', '[1 2] 4~04138~, 7~03117~ 10~03205~ 12~08270~ 15~03772~, 19~07364~ 21~04325~ 23~04935~ [24] 28~04414~ 30~04414~, 32~02853~ 34~02853~.'),
  (6634, 7, 5, 4, 'LORD, when thou wentest out of Seir, when thou marchedst out of the field of Edom, the earth trembled, and the heavens dropped, the clouds also dropped water.', '0~03068~, 4~03318~ 6~08165~, 10~06805~ 13~07704~ 15~0123~, 17~0776~ 18~07493~, 21~08064~ 22~05197~, 24~05645~ 26~05197~ 27~04325~.'),
  (9911, 12, 14, 7, 'He slew of Edom in the valley of salt ten thousand, and took Selah by war, and called the name of it Joktheel unto this day.', '1~05221~ 3~0123~ 6~01516~ 8~04417~ 9~06235~ 10~0505~, 12~08610~ 13~05554~ 15~04421~, 17~07121~ 19~08034~ 22~03371~ 25~03117~.'),
  (163, 1, 7, 3, 'Of fowls also of the air by sevens, the male and the female; to keep seed alive upon the face of all the earth.', '1~05775~ 5~08064~ 7~07651~ 8~07651~,* 10~02145~ 13~05347~; 15~02421~ 16~02233~ 17~02421~ 20~06440~ 24~0776~.'),
  (3679, 4, 2, 16, 'All that were numbered in the camp of Reuben were an hundred thousand and fifty and one thousand and four hundred and fifty, throughout their armies. And they shall set forth in the second rank.', '3~06485~ 6~04264~ 8~07205~ [9] 11~03967~ 12~0505~ 14~02572~ 16~0259~ 17~0505~ 19~0702~ 20~03967~ 22~02572~, 25~06635~. 30~05265~ 34~08145~.'),
  (24240, 41, 1, 15, 'And saying, The time is fulfilled, and the kingdom of God is at hand: repent ye, and believe the gospel.', '0~2532~ 1~3004~ 2~3754~,* 4~2540~ 6~4137~, 7~2532~ 9~932~ 11~2316~ 14~1448~: 16~3340~, 17~2532~ 18~4100~ 19~1722~* 21~2098~.'),
  (7535, 9, 14, 20, 'And Saul and all the people that were with him assembled themselves, and they came to the battle: and, behold, every man''s sword was against his fellow, and there was a very great discomfiture.', '1~07586~ 5~05971~ [7] 10~02199~ 14~0935~ 17~04421~: 21~0376~ 22~02719~ 26~07453~, [27 29] 31~03966~ 32~01419~ 33~04103~.'),
  (11249, 14, 3, 12, 'And one wing of the other cherub was five cubits, reaching to the wall of the house: and the other wing was five cubits also, joining to the wing of the other cherub.', '[1] 2~03671~ 5~0259~ 6~03742~ [7] 8~02568~ 9~0520~, 10~05060~ 13~07023~ 16~01004~: 19~0312~ 20~03671~ [21] 22~02568~ 23~0520~ [24] 25~01695~ 28~03671~ 31~0312~ 32~03742~.'),
  (9196, 11, 13, 4, 'And it came to pass, when king Jeroboam heard the saying of the man of God, which had cried against the altar in Bethel, that he put forth his hand from the altar, saying, Lay hold on him. And his hand, which he put forth against him, dried up, so that he could not pull it in again to him.', '6~04428~ 7~03379~ 8~08085~ 10~01697~ 13~0376~ 15~0430~, 18~07121~ 21~04196~ 23~01008~, 27~07971~ 29~03027~ 32~04196~, 33~0559~, 35~08610~ 40~03027~, 44~07971~ 48~03001~, 52~03201~ 57~07725~'),
  (23407, 40, 9, 18, 'While he spake these things unto them, behold, there came a certain ruler, and worshipped him, saying, My daughter is even now dead: but come and lay thy hand upon her, and she shall live.', '&para; 1~846~ 2~2980~ 4~5023~ 6~846~, 7~2400~, 9~2064~ 11~1520~ 12~758~, 14~4352~ 15~846~, 16~3004~ 17~3754~,* 18~3450~ 19~2364~ 22~737~ 23~5053~: 24~235~ 25~2064~ 27~2007~ 28~4675~ 29~5495~ 30~1909~ 31~846~, 32~2532~ 35~2198~.'),
  (31026, 66, 18, 17, 'For in one hour so great riches is come to nought. And every shipmaster, and all the company in ships, and sailors, and as many as trade by sea, stood afar off,', '0~3754~ 2~3391~ 3~5610~ 5~5118~ 6~4149~ 10~2049~. 11~2532~ 12~3956~ 13~2942~, 14~2532~ 15~3956~ 17~3658~ 18~1909~ 19~4143~, 20~2532~ 21~3492~, 22~2532~ 25~3745~ 26~2038~ 28~2281~, 29~2476~ 30~3113~ 31~575~,'),
  (23351, 40, 7, 25, 'And the rain descended, and the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat upon that house; and it fell not: for it was founded upon a rock.', '0~2532~ 2~1028~ 3~2597~, 4~2532~ 6~4215~ 7~2064~, 8~2532~ 10~417~ 11~4154~, 12~2532~ 14~4363~ 15~1565~ 16~3614~; 17~2532~ 19~4098~ 20~3756~: 21~1063~ 24~2311~ 25~1909~ 27~4073~.'),
  (55, 1, 2, 24, 'Therefore shall a man leave his father and his mother, and shall cleave unto his wife: and they shall be one flesh.', '0~03651~ 3~0376~ 4~05800~ 6~01~ 9~0517~, 12~01692~ 15~0802~: 20~0259~ 21~01320~.'),
  (17170, 20, 26, 20, 'Where no wood is, there the fire goeth out: so where there is no talebearer, the strife ceaseth.', '&para; 1~0657~ 2~06086~ [4] 6~0784~ 8~03518~: [11 12] 14~05372~, 16~04066~ 17~08367~.'),
  (9020, 11, 8, 27, 'But will God indeed dwell on the earth? behold, the heaven and heaven of heavens cannot contain thee; how much less this house that I have builded?', '2~0430~ 3~0552~ 4~03427~ 7~0776~? 10~08064~ 12~08064~ 14~08064~ 16~03557~ 20~0637~ 22~01004~ 26~01129~?'),
  (10485, 13, 6, 23, 'Elkanah his son, and Ebiasaph his son, and Assir his son,', '0~0511~ 2~01121~, 4~043~ 6~01121~, 8~0617~ 10~01121~,'),
  (21520, 26, 40, 34, 'And the arches thereof were toward the outward court; and palm trees were upon the posts thereof, on this side, and on that side: and the going up to it had eight steps.', '2~0361~ [4] 7~02435~ 8~02691~; 11~08561~ [12] 15~0352~ 27~04608~ [30] 31~08083~ 32~04609~.'),
  (13542, 18, 29, 1, 'Moreover Job continued his parable, and said,', '&para; 1~0347~ 2~03254~ 3~05375~* 5~04912~, 7~0559~,');
