VALUES
  (22544, 32, 1, 4, 'But the LORD sent out a great wind into the sea, and there was a mighty tempest in the sea, so that the ship was like to be broken.', '&para; 2~03068~ 4~02904~ 6~01419~ 7~07307~ 10~03220~, 15~01419~ 16~05591~ 19~03220~, 23~0591~ 25~02803~ 28~07665~.'),
  (18969, 24, 1, 14, 'Then the LORD said unto me, Out of the north an evil shall break forth upon all the inhabitants of the land.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 9~06828~ 11~07451~ 14~06605~ 18~03427~ 21~0776~.'),
  (20370, 25, 3, 7, 'He hath hedged me about, that I cannot get out: he hath made my chain heavy.', '2~01443~ 9~03318~: 14~05178~ 15~03513~.'),
  (29366, 49, 6, 13, 'Wherefore take unto you the whole armour of God, that ye may be able to withstand in the evil day, and having done all, to stand.', '0~5124~ 1~1223~ 3~353~ 6~3833~ 8~2316~, 9~2443~ 13~1410~ 15~436~ 16~1722~ 18~4190~ 19~2250~, 20~2532~ 22~2716~ 23~537~, 25~2476~.'),
  (12390, 16, 4, 22, 'Likewise at the same time said I unto the people, Let every one with his servant lodge within Jerusalem, that in the night they may be a guard to us, and labour on the day.', '4~06256~ 5~0559~ 9~05971~, 12~0376~ 15~05288~ 16~03885~ 17~08432~ 18~03389~, 22~03915~ 27~04929~ 31~04399~ 34~03117~.'),
  (6469, 6, 23, 2, 'And Joshua called for all Israel, and for their elders, and for their heads, and for their judges, and for their officers, and said unto them, I am old and stricken in age:', '1~03091~ 2~07121~ 5~03478~, [6] 9~02205~, 13~07218~, 17~08199~, 21~07860~, 23~0559~ 28~02204~ [29] 30~0935~ 32~03117~:'),
  (21895, 27, 5, 12, 'Forasmuch as an excellent spirit, and knowledge, and understanding, interpreting of dreams, and shewing of hard sentences, and dissolving of doubts, were found in the same Daniel, whom the king named Belteshazzar: now let Daniel be called, and he will shew the interpretation.', '1~03606~ 2~06903~ 3~03493~ 4~07308~, 6~04486~, 8~07924~, 9~06590~ 11~02493~, 13~0263~ 16~0280~, 18~08271~ 20~07001~, 22~07912~ 26~01841~, 29~04430~ 30~07761~ 31~08036~* 32~01096~: 33~03705~ 35~01841~ 37~07123~, 41~02324~ 43~06591~.'),
  (27194, 44, 8, 2, 'And devout men carried Stephen to his burial, and made great lamentation over him.', '0~1161~ 1~2126~ 2~435~ 3~4792~ 4~4736~ [5 7] 8~2532~ 9~4160~ 10~3173~ 11~2870~ 12~1909~ 13~846~.'),
  (17624, 22, 6, 1, 'Whither is thy beloved gone, O thou fairest among women? whither is thy beloved turned aside? that we may seek him with thee.', '&para; 3~01730~ 4~01980~, 7~03303~ 9~0802~? 13~01730~ 15~06437~? 19~01245~'),
  (1089, 1, 37, 1, 'And Jacob dwelt in the land wherein his father was a stranger, in the land of Canaan.', '&para; 1~03290~ 2~03427~ 5~0776~ 8~01~ 11~04033~, 14~0776~ 16~03667~.'),
  (4406, 4, 22, 26, 'And the angel of the LORD went further, and stood in a narrow place, where was no way to turn either to the right hand or to the left.', '2~04397~ 5~03068~ 6~05674~ 7~03254~, 9~05975~ 12~06862~ 13~04725~, [15] 17~01870~ 19~05186~ 24~03225~ 28~08040~.'),
  (13927, 18, 41, 30, 'Sharp stones are under him: he spreadeth sharp pointed things upon the mire.', '0~02303~ 1~02789~ [2] 6~07502~ 9~02742~ 12~02916~.'),
  (16552, 20, 6, 3, 'Do this now, my son, and deliver thyself, when thou art come into the hand of thy friend; go, humble thyself, and make sure thy friend.', '0~06213~ 2~0645~, 4~01121~, 6~05337~ 11~0935~ 14~03709~ 17~07453~; 18~03212~, 19~07511~ 23~07292~ 25~07453~.'),
  (10889, 13, 17, 18, 'What can David speak more to thee for the honour of thy servant? for thou knowest thy servant.', '1~03254~ 2~01732~ [3] 4~03254~ 9~03519~ 12~05650~? 15~03045~ 17~05650~.'),
  (12334, 16, 2, 18, 'Then I told them of the hand of my God which was good upon me; as also the king''s words that he had spoken unto me. And they said, Let us rise up and build. So they strengthened their hands for this good work.', '2~05046~ 6~03027~ 9~0430~ 12~02896~ 18~04428~ 19~01697~ 23~0559~ 28~0559~, 32~06965~ 34~01129~. 37~02388~ 39~03027~ [41] 42~02896~ [43]'),
  (26343, 43, 6, 71, 'He spake of Judas Iscariot the son of Simon: for he it was that should betray him, being one of the twelve.', '0~1161~ 1~3004~ 3~2455~ 4~2469~ [5 6] 8~4613~: 9~1063~ 10~3778~ 14~3195~ 15~3860~ 16~846~, 17~5607~ 18~1520~ 19~1537~ 21~1427~.'),
  (7930, 9, 26, 18, 'And he said, Wherefore doth my lord thus pursue after his servant? for what have I done? or what evil is in mine hand?', '2~0559~, 6~0113~ 8~07291~ 9~0310~ 11~05650~? 16~06213~? 19~07451~ [20] 23~03027~?'),
  (28549, 46, 8, 6, 'But to us there is but one God, the Father, of whom are all things, and we in him; and one Lord Jesus Christ, by whom are all things, and we by him.', '0~235~ 2~2254~ [3 5] 6~1520~ 7~2316~, 9~3962~, 10~1537~ 11~3739~ [12] 14~3956~, 15~2532~ 16~2249~ 17~1519~ 18~846~; 19~2532~ 20~1520~ 21~2962~ 22~2424~ 23~5547~, 24~1223~ 25~3739~ [26] 28~3956~, 29~2532~ 30~2249~ 31~1223~ 32~846~.'),
  (29819, 54, 6, 15, 'Which in his times he shall shew, who is the blessed and only Potentate, the King of kings, and Lord of lords;', '0~3739~ 2~2398~ 3~2540~ 6~1166~, [7 7~3588~ 8] 10~3107~ 11~2532~ 12~3441~ 13~1413~, 15~935~ 17~936~, 18~2532~ 19~2962~ 21~2961~;'),
  (29534, 51, 3, 1, 'If ye then be risen with Christ, seek those things which are above, where Christ sitteth on the right hand of God.', '&para; 0~1487~ 1~4891~ 2~3767~ 4~4891~ 6~5547~, 7~2212~ 12~507~, 13~3757~ 14~5547~ 15~2076~ 16~2521~* 17~1722~ 20~1188~ 22~2316~.'),
  (5881, 6, 2, 6, 'But she had brought them up to the roof of the house, and hid them with the stalks of flax, which she had laid in order upon the roof.', '5~05927~ 8~01406~ 13~02934~ 17~06086~ 19~06593~, 25~06186~ 28~01406~.'),
  (21301, 26, 33, 12, 'Therefore, thou son of man, say unto the children of thy people, The righteousness of the righteous shall not deliver him in the day of his transgression: as for the wickedness of the wicked, he shall not fall thereby in the day that he turneth from his wickedness; neither shall the righteous be able to live for his righteousness in the day that he sinneth.', '2~01121~ 4~0120~, 5~0559~ 8~01121~ 11~05971~, 13~06666~ 16~06662~ 19~05337~ 23~03117~ 26~06588~: 30~07564~ 33~07563~, 37~03782~ 41~03117~ 44~07725~ 47~07562~; 51~06662~ 53~03201~ 55~02421~ [58] 61~03117~ 64~02398~.'),
  (11131, 13, 27, 14, 'The eleventh captain for the eleventh month was Benaiah the Pirathonite, of the children of Ephraim: and in his course were twenty and four thousand.', '1~06240~ [2] 2~06249~ 5~06240~ 6~06249~* 7~02320~ [8] 9~01141~ 11~06553~, 14~01121~ 16~0669~: 20~04256~ [21] 22~06242~ 24~0702~ 25~0505~.'),
  (5152, 5, 8, 9, 'A land wherein thou shalt eat bread without scarceness, thou shalt not lack any thing in it; a land whose stones are iron, and out of whose hills thou mayest dig brass.', '1~0776~ 2~0834~ 5~0398~ 6~03899~ 7~03808~ 8~04544~, 12~02637~ [14] 18~0776~ 20~068~ [21] 22~01270~, 27~02042~ 30~02672~ 31~05178~.'),
  (8799, 11, 2, 21, 'And she said, Let Abishag the Shunammite be given to Adonijah thy brother to wife.', '2~0559~, 4~049~ 6~07767~ 8~05414~ 10~0138~ 12~0251~ 14~0802~.'),
  (27653, 44, 20, 11, 'When he therefore was come up again, and had broken bread, and eaten, and talked a long while, even till break of day, so he departed.', '0~1161~ 1~305~ 6~305~, 7~2532~ 9~2806~ 10~740~, 11~2532~ 12~1089~, 13~5037~ 14~3656~ 15~1909~* 18~2425~, 20~891~ 23~827~, 24~3779~ 26~1831~.'),
  (29854, 55, 2, 11, 'It is a faithful saying: For if we be dead with him, we shall also live with him:', '[0 1] 3~4103~ 4~3056~: 5~1063~ 6~1487~ 10~4880~ [11] 13~4800~ 14~2532~ 16~4800~ [17]'),
  (18198, 23, 28, 25, 'When he hath made plain the face thereof, doth he not cast abroad the fitches, and scatter the cummin, and cast in the principal wheat and the appointed barley and the rie in their place?', '4~07737~ 6~06440~ 12~06327~ 14~07100~, 16~02236~ 18~03646~, 20~07760~ 23~07795~ 24~02406~ 27~05567~ 28~08184~ 31~03698~ 34~01367~?'),
  (7201, 8, 4, 4, 'And I thought to advertise thee, saying, Buy it before the inhabitants, and before the elders of my people. If thou wilt redeem it, redeem it: but if thou wilt not redeem it, then tell me, that I may know: for there is none to redeem it beside thee; and I am after thee. And he said, I will redeem it.', '2~0559~ 4~01540~ 5~0241~* 7~0559~, 8~07069~ [9] 12~03427~, 16~02205~ 19~05971~. 23~01350~ [24] 25~01350~ [26] 32~01350~ [33 34] 35~05046~ 40~03045~: [42 43] 46~01350~ [47] 48~02108~ [52] 53~0310~ 57~0559~, 60~01350~ [61]'),
  (9505, 11, 22, 17, 'And he said, I saw all Israel scattered upon the hills, as sheep that have not a shepherd: and the LORD said, These have no master: let them return every man to his house in peace.', '2~0559~, 4~07200~ 6~03478~ 7~06327~ 10~02022~, 12~06629~ 17~07462~: 20~03068~ 21~0559~, 25~0113~: 28~07725~ 30~0376~ 33~01004~ 35~07965~.'),
  (28090, 45, 6, 6, 'Knowing this, that our old man is crucified with him, that the body of sin might be destroyed, that henceforth we should not serve sin.', '0~1097~ 1~5124~, 2~3754~ 3~2257~ 4~3820~ 5~444~ 8~4957~ [9] 10~2443~ 12~4983~ 14~266~ 17~2673~, 19~3371~ 20~2248~ 21~1398~ 22~3371~ 23~1398~ 24~266~.'),
  (21622, 26, 44, 14, 'But I will make them keepers of the charge of the house, for all the service thereof, and for all that shall be done therein.', '3~05414~ 5~08104~ 8~04931~ 11~01004~, 15~05656~ 23~06213~'),
  (25819, 42, 20, 26, 'And they could not take hold of his words before the people: and they marvelled at his answer, and held their peace.', '0~2532~ 2~2480~ 3~3756~ 5~1949~ 7~846~ 8~4487~ 9~1726~ 11~2992~: 12~2532~ 14~2296~ 15~1909~ 16~846~ 17~612~, 21~4601~.'),
  (10444, 13, 5, 8, 'And Bela the son of Azaz, the son of Shema, the son of Joel, who dwelt in Aroer, even unto Nebo and Baalmeon:', '1~01106~ 3~01121~ 5~05811~, 7~01121~ 9~08087~, 11~01121~ 13~03100~, 15~03427~ 17~06177~, 20~05015~ 22~01186~:'),
  (13791, 18, 37, 13, 'He causeth it to come, whether for correction, or for his land, or for mercy.', '4~04672~, 7~07626~, 11~0776~, 14~02617~.'),
  (13118, 18, 11, 1, 'Then answered Zophar the Naamathite, and said,', '&para; 1~06030~ 2~06691~ 4~05284~, 6~0559~,'),
  (6345, 6, 19, 17, 'And the fourth lot came out to Issachar, for the children of Issachar according to their families.', '&para; [0] 2~07243~ 3~01486~ 5~03318~ 7~03485~, 10~01121~ 12~03485~ 16~04940~.'),
  (21011, 26, 22, 26, 'Her priests have violated my law, and have profaned mine holy things: they have put no difference between the holy and profane, neither have they shewed difference between the unclean and the clean, and have hid their eyes from my sabbaths, and I am profaned among them.', '1~03548~ 3~02554~ 5~08451~, 8~02490~ 11~06944~: 16~0914~ 19~06944~ 21~02455~, 25~03045~ [26] 29~02931~ 32~02889~, 35~05956~ 37~05869~ 40~07676~, 44~02490~ 45~08432~'),
  (13502, 18, 27, 12, 'Behold, all ye yourselves have seen it; why then are ye thus altogether vain?', '5~02372~ [6] 12~01892~ 13~01891~?'),
  (18753, 23, 55, 4, 'Behold, I have given him for a witness to the people, a leader and commander to the people.', '3~05414~ [5] 7~05707~ 10~03816~, 12~05057~ 14~06680~ 17~03816~.'),
  (18002, 23, 17, 10, 'Because thou hast forgotten the God of thy salvation, and hast not been mindful of the rock of thy strength, therefore shalt thou plant pleasant plants, and shalt set it with strange slips:', '3~07911~ 5~0430~ 8~03468~, 13~02142~ 16~06697~ 19~04581~, 23~05193~ 24~05282~ 25~05194~, 28~02232~ 31~02114~ 32~02156~:'),
  (6074, 6, 10, 4, 'Come up unto me, and help me, that we may smite Gibeon: for it hath made peace with Joshua and with the children of Israel.', '1~05927~ 5~05826~ 10~05221~ 11~01391~: 16~07999~ 18~03091~ 22~01121~ 24~03478~.'),
  (19518, 24, 23, 25, 'I have heard what the prophets said, that prophesy lies in my name, saying, I have dreamed, I have dreamed.', '2~08085~ 5~05030~ 6~0559~, 8~05012~ 9~08267~ 12~08034~, 13~0559~, 16~02492~, 19~02492~.'),
  (27269, 44, 9, 37, 'And it came to pass in those days, that she was sick, and died: whom when they had washed, they laid her in an upper chamber.', '0~1161~ 4~1096~ 5~1722~ 6~1565~ 7~2250~, 11~770~, 13~599~: 15~1161~ 16~846~ 18~3068~ 19~846~,* 21~5087~ [22] 23~1722~ 26~5253~.'),
  (15881, 19, 118, 3, 'Let the house of Aaron now say, that his mercy endureth for ever.', '2~01004~ 4~0175~ 6~0559~, 9~02617~ [10] 12~05769~.'),
  (18269, 23, 32, 1, 'Behold, a king shall reign in righteousness, and princes shall rule in judgment.', '&para; 2~04428~ 4~04427~ 6~06664~, 8~08269~ 10~08323~ 12~04941~.'),
  (31024, 66, 18, 15, 'The merchants of these things, which were made rich by her, shall stand afar off for the fear of her torment, weeping and wailing,', '1~1713~ 4~5130~, 5~3588~ 8~4147~ 9~575~ 10~846~, 12~2476~ 13~3113~ 14~575~ 15~1223~ 17~5401~ 19~846~ 20~929~, 21~2799~ 22~2532~ 23~3996~,'),
  (23521, 40, 12, 22, 'Then was brought unto him one possessed with a devil, blind, and dumb: and he healed him, insomuch that the blind and dumb both spake and saw.', '&para; 0~5119~ 2~4374~ 4~846~ 9~1139~, 10~5185~, 11~2532~ 12~2974~: 13~2532~ 15~2323~ 16~846~, 18~5620~ 20~5185~ 21~2532~ 22~2974~ 23~2532~ 24~2980~ 25~2532~ 26~991~.'),
  (22795, 35, 3, 18, 'Yet I will rejoice in the LORD, I will joy in the God of my salvation.', '3~05937~ 6~03068~, 9~01523~ 12~0430~ 15~03468~.'),
  (6827, 7, 10, 9, 'Moreover the children of Ammon passed over Jordan to fight also against Judah, and against Benjamin, and against the house of Ephraim; so that Israel was sore distressed.', '2~01121~ 4~05983~ 6~05674~ 7~03383~ 9~03898~ 12~03063~, 15~01144~, 19~01004~ 21~0669~; 24~03478~ 26~03966~ 27~03334~.'),
  (3442, 3, 23, 35, 'On the first day shall be an holy convocation: ye shall do no servile work therein.', '2~07223~ 3~03117~ [4 5] 7~06944~ 8~04744~: 11~06213~ 13~05656~ 14~04399~ [15]'),
  (4991, 5, 3, 10, 'All the cities of the plain, and all Gilead, and all Bashan, unto Salchah and Edrei, cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan.', '2~05892~ 5~04334~, 8~01568~, 11~01316~, 13~05548~ 15~0154~, 16~05892~ 19~04467~ 21~05747~ 23~01316~.'),
  (14063, 19, 10, 13, 'Wherefore doth the wicked contemn God? he hath said in his heart, Thou wilt not require it.', '3~07563~ 4~05006~ 5~0430~? 8~0559~ 11~03820~, 15~01875~ [16]'),
  (20518, 26, 3, 7, 'But the house of Israel will not hearken unto thee; for they will not hearken unto me: for all the house of Israel are impudent and hardhearted.', '2~01004~ 4~03478~ 5~014~ 7~08085~ 12~014~ 14~08085~ 20~01004~ 22~03478~ [23] 24~04696~ 25~02389~ 26~03820~ 27~07186~.*'),
  (9431, 11, 20, 15, 'Then he numbered the young men of the princes of the provinces, and they were two hundred and thirty two: and after them he numbered all the people, even all the children of Israel, being seven thousand.', '2~06485~ 5~05288~ 8~08269~ 11~04082~, 15~08147~ 16~03967~ 18~07970~ 19~08147~: 21~0310~ 24~06485~ 27~05971~, [28] 31~01121~ 33~03478~, [34] 35~07651~ 36~0505~.'),
  (3411, 3, 23, 4, 'These are the feasts of the LORD, even holy convocations, which ye shall proclaim in their seasons.', '&para; [1] 3~04150~ 6~03068~, [7] 8~06944~ 9~04744~, 13~07121~ 16~04150~.'),
  (29583, 52, 1, 7, 'So that ye were ensamples to all that believe in Macedonia and Achaia.', '0~5620~ 2~5209~ 3~1096~ 4~5179~ 6~3956~ 8~4100~ 9~1722~ 10~3109~ 11~2532~ 12~882~.'),
  (23986, 40, 24, 19, 'And woe unto them that are with child, and to them that give suck in those days!', '0~1161~ 1~3759~ 5~2192~ 6~1722~ 7~1064~, 8~2532~ 13~2337~ 14~1722~ 15~1565~ 16~2250~!'),
  (18126, 23, 24, 22, 'And they shall be gathered together, as prisoners are gathered in the pit, and shall be shut up in the prison, and after many days shall they be visited.', '5~0622~, [6] 7~0616~ 9~0626~ 12~0953~, 17~05462~ 20~04525~, 23~07230~ 24~03117~ 28~06485~.'),
  (172, 1, 7, 12, 'And the rain was upon the earth forty days and forty nights.', '2~01653~ 6~0776~ 7~0705~ 8~03117~ 10~0705~ 11~03915~.'),
  (25118, 42, 4, 43, 'And he said unto them, I must preach the kingdom of God to other cities also: for therefore am I sent.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 3~4314~ 4~846~ 5~3754~,* 6~3165~ 7~1163~ 8~2097~ 10~932~ 12~2316~ 14~2087~ 15~4172~ 16~2532~: 17~3754~ 18~5124~ 19~1519~ 21~649~.'),
  (25748, 42, 19, 3, 'And he sought to see Jesus who he was; and could not for the press, because he was little of stature.', '0~2532~ 2~2212~ 4~1492~ 5~2424~ 6~5101~ 8~2076~; 9~2532~ 10~1410~ 11~3756~ 12~575~ 14~3793~, 15~3754~ 17~2258~ 18~3398~ 20~2244~.'),
  (9465, 11, 21, 6, 'And he said unto her, Because I spake unto Naboth the Jezreelite, and said unto him, Give me thy vineyard for money; or else, if it please thee, I will give thee another vineyard for it: and he answered, I will not give thee my vineyard.', '2~01696~ 7~01696~ 9~05022~ 11~03158~, 13~0559~ 16~05414~ 19~03754~ 21~03701~; 26~02655~ 30~05414~ [32] 33~03754~ 38~0559~, 42~05414~ 45~03754~.'),
  (12306, 16, 1, 1, 'The words of Nehemiah the son of Hachaliah. And it came to pass in the month Chisleu, in the twentieth year, as I was in Shushan the palace,', '&para; 1~01697~ 3~05166~ 5~01121~ 7~02446~. 15~02320~ 16~03691~, 19~06242~ 20~08141~, 25~07800~ 27~01002~,'),
  (25896, 42, 22, 18, 'For I say unto you, I will not drink of the fruit of the vine, until the kingdom of God shall come.', '0~1063~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~ 5~3754~,* 7~4095~ 8~3364~ 9~4095~ 10~575~ 12~1081~ 15~288~, 16~3755~ 17~2193~ 18~932~ 20~2316~ 22~2064~.'),
  (13636, 18, 31, 39, 'If I have eaten the fruits thereof without money, or have caused the owners thereof to lose their life:', '3~0398~ 5~03581~ 8~03701~, 13~01167~ 16~05301~ 18~05315~:'),
  (12399, 16, 5, 8, 'And I said unto them, We after our ability have redeemed our brethren the Jews, which were sold unto the heathen; and will ye even sell your brethren? or shall they be sold unto us? Then held they their peace, and found nothing to answer.', '2~0559~ 8~01767~ 10~07069~ 12~0251~ 14~03064~, 17~04376~ 20~01471~; 25~04376~ 27~0251~? 32~04376~ 39~02790~, 41~04672~ 42~01697~ [43 44]'),
  (22021, 27, 9, 24, 'Seventy weeks are determined upon thy people and upon thy holy city, to finish the transgression, and to make an end of sins, and to make reconciliation for iniquity, and to bring in everlasting righteousness, and to seal up the vision and prophecy, and to anoint the most Holy.', '0~07657~ 1~07620~ 3~02852~ 6~05971~ 10~06944~ 11~05892~, 13~03607~ 15~06588~, 20~08552~ 22~02403~, 26~03722~ 28~05771~, 32~0935~ 33~05769~ 34~06664~, 38~02856~ 40~02377~ 42~05030~, 45~04886~ 47~06944~ 48~06944~.'),
  (24485, 41, 7, 11, 'But ye say, If a man shall say to his father or mother, It is Corban, that is to say, a gift, by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me; he shall be free.', '0~1161~ 1~5210~ 2~3004~, 3~1437~ 5~444~ 7~2036~ 10~3962~ 11~2228~ 12~3384~, [13 14] 15~2878~, 19~3603~, 21~1435~, 22~1537~ 23~1437~ 24~3739~ 28~5623~ 29~1700~; [30 33]'),
  (18894, 23, 63, 19, 'We are thine: thou never barest rule over them; they were not called by thy name.', '[2] 4~05769~ 6~04910~ 12~07121~ 15~08034~.'),
  (22386, 30, 1, 13, 'Thus saith the LORD; For three transgressions of the children of Ammon, and for four, I will not turn away the punishment thereof; because they have ripped up the women with child of Gilead, that they might enlarge their border:', '1~0559~ 3~03068~; 5~07969~ 6~06588~ 9~01121~ 11~05983~, 14~0702~, 19~07725~ [20 21] 27~01234~ 31~02030~ 33~01568~, 37~07337~ 39~01366~:'),
  (24626, 41, 10, 27, 'And Jesus looking upon them saith, With men it is impossible, but not with God: for with God all things are possible.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 3~1689~ 4~846~ 5~3004~, 6~3844~ 7~444~ [8 9] 10~102~, 11~235~ 12~3756~ 13~3844~ 14~2316~: 15~1063~ 16~3844~ 17~2316~ 19~3956~ 20~2076~ 21~1415~.'),
  (5040, 5, 4, 30, 'When thou art in tribulation, and all these things are come upon thee, even in the latter days, if thou turn to the LORD thy God, and shalt be obedient unto his voice;', '4~06862~, 8~01697~ 10~04672~ [13] 16~0319~ 17~03117~, 20~07725~ 23~03068~ 25~0430~, 29~08085~ 32~06963~;'),
  (8061, 10, 2, 5, 'And David sent messengers unto the men of Jabeshgilead, and said unto them, Blessed be ye of the LORD, that ye have shewed this kindness unto your lord, even unto Saul, and have buried him.', '1~01732~ 2~07971~ 3~04397~ 6~0582~ 8~01568~ 9~03003~,* 11~0559~ 14~01288~ [15] 19~03068~, 23~06213~ 25~02617~ 28~0113~, [29] 31~07586~, 34~06912~'),
  (1290, 1, 42, 33, 'And the man, the lord of the country, said unto us, Hereby shall I know that ye are true men; leave one of your brethren here with me, and take food for the famine of your households, and be gone:', '2~0376~, 4~0113~ 7~0776~, 8~0559~ 14~03045~ [17] 18~03651~ [19] 20~03240~ 21~0259~ 24~0251~ [25] 29~03947~ [30 31] 33~07459~ 36~01004~, 39~03212~:'),
  (6234, 6, 15, 25, 'And Hazor, Hadattah, and Kerioth, and Hezron, which is Hazor,', '1~02674~, 2~02675~, 4~07152~, [5] 6~02696~, [8] 9~02674~,'),
  (27266, 44, 9, 34, 'And Peter said unto him, Aeneas, Jesus Christ maketh thee whole: arise, and make thy bed. And he arose immediately.', '0~2532~ 1~4074~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~132~, 6~2424~ 7~5547~ 8~2390~ 9~4571~ 10~2390~: 11~450~, 12~2532~ 13~4766~ 14~4572~ 15~4766~. 16~2532~ 18~450~ 19~2112~.'),
  (15578, 19, 103, 20, 'Bless the LORD, ye his angels, that excel in strength, that do his commandments, hearkening unto the voice of his word.', '0~01288~ 2~03068~, 5~04397~, 7~01368~ 9~03581~, 11~06213~ 13~01697~, 14~08085~ 17~06963~ 20~01697~.'),
  (21770, 27, 2, 3, 'And the king said unto them, I have dreamed a dream, and my spirit was troubled to know the dream.', '2~04428~ 3~0559~ 8~02492~ 10~02472~, 13~07307~ 15~06470~ 17~03045~ 19~02472~.'),
  (1459, 1, 48, 3, 'And Jacob said unto Joseph, God Almighty appeared unto me at Luz in the land of Canaan, and blessed me,', '1~03290~ 2~0559~ 4~03130~, 5~0410~ 6~07706~ 7~07200~ 11~03870~ 14~0776~ 16~03667~, 18~01288~'),
  (10392, 13, 3, 23, 'And the sons of Neariah; Elioenai, and Hezekiah, and Azrikam, three.', '2~01121~ 4~05294~; 5~0454~, 7~02396~, 9~05840~, 10~07969~.'),
  (28566, 46, 9, 10, 'Or saith he it altogether for our sakes? For our sakes, no doubt, this is written: that he that ploweth should plow in hope; and that he that thresheth in hope should be partaker of his hope.', '0~2228~ 2~3004~ [3] 4~3843~ 5~1223~ 6~2248~ 7~1223~? 8~1223~ 9~2248~ 10~1223~, 12~1063~, [13] 15~1125~: 16~3754~ 19~722~ 20~3784~ 21~722~ 22~1909~ 23~1680~; 24~2532~ 28~248~ 30~1680~ 33~3348~ 34~1909~ 35~846~ 36~1680~.'),
  (1623, 2, 4, 17, 'And thou shalt take this rod in thine hand, wherewith thou shalt do signs.', '3~03947~ 5~04294~ 8~03027~, 12~06213~ 13~0226~.'),
  (3958, 4, 8, 14, 'Thus shalt thou separate the Levites from among the children of Israel: and the Levites shall be mine.', '3~0914~ 5~03881~ 7~08432~ 9~01121~ 11~03478~: 14~03881~'),
  (8127, 10, 3, 39, 'And I am this day weak, though anointed king; and these men the sons of Zeruiah be too hard for me: the LORD shall reward the doer of evil according to his wickedness.', '[2] 4~03117~ 5~07390~, 7~04886~ 8~04428~; 11~0582~ 13~01121~ 15~06870~ [16] 18~07186~ 22~03068~ 24~07999~ 28~06213~ 32~07451~.'),
  (5308, 5, 14, 12, 'But these are they of which ye shall not eat: the eagle, and the ossifrage, and the osprey,', '[2 3] 9~0398~: 11~05404~, 14~06538~, 17~05822~,'),
  (19700, 24, 30, 24, 'The fierce anger of the LORD shall not return, until he have done it, and until he have performed the intents of his heart: in the latter days ye shall consider it.', '1~02740~ 2~0639~ 5~03068~ 8~07725~, 12~06213~ [13] 18~06965~ 20~04209~ 23~03820~: 26~0319~ 27~03117~ 30~0995~'),
  (17076, 20, 23, 23, 'Buy the truth, and sell it not; also wisdom, and instruction, and understanding.', '0~07069~ 2~0571~, 4~04376~ [5] [7] 8~02451~, 10~04148~, 12~0998~.'),
  (18729, 23, 53, 9, 'And he made his grave with the wicked, and with the rich in his death; because he had done no violence, neither was any deceit in his mouth.', '2~05414~ 4~06913~ 7~07563~, 11~06223~ 14~04194~; 18~06213~ 20~02555~, [22 23] 24~04820~ 27~06310~.'),
  (14966, 19, 69, 22, 'Let their table become a snare before them: and that which should have been for their welfare, let it become a trap.', '&para; 2~07979~ 5~06341~ 6~06440~ [9 13] [15] 16~07965~, [17 19] 21~04170~.'),
  (6297, 6, 17, 15, 'And Joshua answered them, If thou be a great people, then get thee up to the wood country, and cut down for thyself there in the land of the Perizzites and of the giants, if mount Ephraim be too narrow for thee.', '1~03091~ 2~0559~ [6] 8~07227~ 9~05971~, [10] 13~05927~ 16~03293~ [17] 20~01254~ 26~0776~ 29~06522~ 33~07497~, 35~02022~ 36~0669~ 39~0213~'),
  (5139, 5, 7, 22, 'And the LORD thy God will put out those nations before thee by little and little: thou mayest not consume them at once, lest the beasts of the field increase upon thee.', '2~03068~ 4~0430~ 7~05394~ 8~0411~ 9~01471~ 10~06440~ 13~04592~ 15~04592~: 17~03201~ 19~03615~ 22~04118~, 25~02416~ 28~07704~ 29~07235~'),
  (22095, 27, 12, 5, 'Then I Daniel looked, and, behold, there stood other two, the one on this side of the bank of the river, and the other on that side of the bank of the river.', '&para; 2~01840~ 3~07200~, 7~05975~ 8~0312~ 9~08147~, 11~0259~ 14~02008~ 17~08193~ 20~02975~, 23~0259~ 29~08193~ 32~02975~.'),
  (15833, 19, 114, 2, 'Judah was his sanctuary, and Israel his dominion.', '0~03063~ 3~06944~, [4] 5~03478~ 7~04475~.'),
  (13688, 18, 33, 29, 'Lo, all these things worketh God oftentimes with man,', '&para; [3] 4~06466~ 5~0410~ 6~07969~ 7~06471~ 8~01397~,'),
  (8164, 10, 5, 25, 'And David did so, as the LORD had commanded him; and smote the Philistines from Geba until thou come to Gazer.', '1~01732~ 3~06213~, 6~03068~ 8~06680~ 11~05221~ 13~06430~ 15~01387~ 18~0935~ 20~01507~.'),
  (7870, 9, 25, 2, 'And there was a man in Maon, whose possessions were in Carmel; and the man was very great, and he had three thousand sheep, and a thousand goats: and he was shearing his sheep in Carmel.', '&para; [1 2] 4~0376~ 6~04584~, 8~04639~ [9] 11~03760~; 14~0376~ [15] 16~03966~ 17~01419~, 21~07969~ 22~0505~ 23~06629~, 26~0505~ 27~05795~: 31~01494~ 33~06629~ 35~03760~.'),
  (21668, 26, 46, 4, 'And the burnt offering that the prince shall offer unto the LORD in the sabbath day shall be six lambs without blemish, and a ram without blemish.', '3~05930~ 6~05387~ 8~07126~ 11~03068~ 14~07676~ 15~03117~ [16 17] 18~08337~ 19~03532~ 21~08549~, 24~0352~ 26~08549~.'),
  (17052, 20, 22, 28, 'Remove not the ancient landmark, which thy fathers have set.', '&para; 0~05253~ 3~05769~ 4~01366~, 7~01~ 9~06213~.'),
  (3133, 3, 14, 17, 'And of the rest of the oil that is in his hand shall the priest put upon the tip of the right ear of him that is to be cleansed, and upon the thumb of his right hand, and upon the great toe of his right foot, upon the blood of the trespass offering:', '3~03499~ 6~08081~ [8] 11~03709~ 14~03548~ 15~05414~ 18~08571~ 21~03233~ 22~0241~ 29~02891~, 33~0931~ 36~03233~ 37~03027~, 42~0931~ 45~03233~ 46~07272~, 49~01818~ 53~0817~:');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (25724, 42, 18, 22, 'Now when Jesus heard these things, he said unto him, Yet lackest thou one thing: sell all that thou hast, and distribute unto the poor, and thou shalt have treasure in heaven: and come, follow me.', '0~1161~ 2~2424~ 3~191~ 5~5023~, 7~2036~ 9~846~, 10~2089~ 11~3007~ 12~4671~ 13~1520~ 15~4453~ 16~3956~ 17~3745~ 19~2192~, 20~2532~ 21~1239~ 24~4434~, 25~2532~ 28~2192~ 29~2344~ 30~1722~ 31~3772~: 32~2532~ 33~1204~, 34~190~ 35~3427~.'),
  (26072, 43, 1, 14, 'And the Word was made flesh, and dwelt among us, (and we beheld his glory, the glory as of the only begotten of the Father,) full of grace and truth.', '0~2532~ 2~3056~ 4~1096~ 5~4561~, 6~2532~ 7~4637~ 8~1722~ 9~2254~, 10~2532~* 13~2300~ 14~846~ 15~1391~, 17~1391~ 18~5613~ 22~3439~ 23~3844~ 25~3962~,) 26~4134~ 28~5485~ 29~2532~ 30~225~.'),
  (15788, 19, 109, 24, 'My knees are weak through fasting; and my flesh faileth of fatness.', '1~01290~ 3~03782~ 5~06685~; 8~01320~ 9~03584~ 11~08081~.'),
  (4973, 5, 2, 29, '(As the children of Esau which dwell in Seir, and the Moabites which dwell in Ar, did unto me;) until I shall pass over Jordan into the land which the LORD our God giveth us.', '2~01121~ 4~06215~ 6~03427~ 8~08165~, 11~04125~ 13~03427~ 15~06144~, 16~06213~ 23~05674~ 24~03383~ 27~0776~ 30~03068~ 32~0430~ 33~05414~'),
  (23117, 39, 2, 5, 'My covenant was with him of life and peace; and I gave them to him for the fear wherewith he feared me, and was afraid before my name.', '1~01285~ 6~02416~ 8~07965~; 11~05414~ [15] 17~04172~ 20~03372~ 24~02865~ 25~06440~ 27~08034~.'),
  (4886, 4, 36, 1, 'And the chief fathers of the families of the children of Gilead, the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh, of the families of the sons of Joseph, came near, and spake before Moses, and before the princes, the chief fathers of the children of Israel:', '&para; 2~07218~ 3~01~ 6~04940~ 9~01121~ 11~01568~, 13~01121~ 15~04353~, 17~01121~ 19~04519~, 22~04940~ 25~01121~ 27~03130~, 29~07126~, 31~01696~ 32~06440~ 33~04872~, 35~06440~ 37~05387~, 39~07218~ 40~01~ 43~01121~ 45~03478~:'),
  (23031, 38, 10, 6, 'And I will strengthen the house of Judah, and I will save the house of Joseph, and I will bring them again to place them; for I have mercy upon them: and they shall be as though I had not cast them off: for I am the LORD their God, and will hear them.', '3~01396~ 5~01004~ 7~03063~, 11~03467~ 13~01004~ 15~03130~, 23~03427~ 28~07355~ 36~0834~ 42~02186~: [45] 47~03068~ 49~0430~, 52~06030~'),
  (24764, 41, 13, 36, 'Lest coming suddenly he find you sleeping.', '0~3361~ 1~2064~ 2~1810~ 4~2147~ 5~5209~ 6~2518~.'),
  (14303, 19, 27, 9, 'Hide not thy face far from me; put not thy servant away in anger: thou hast been my help; leave me not, neither forsake me, O God of my salvation.', '0~05641~ 3~06440~ [4] 7~05186~ 10~05650~ 11~05186~ 13~0639~: 18~05833~; 19~05203~ 23~05800~ 26~0430~ 29~03468~.'),
  (23569, 40, 13, 20, 'But he that received the seed into stony places, the same is he that heareth the word, and anon with joy receiveth it;', '0~1161~ 5~4687~ 6~1909~ 8~4075~, 10~3778~ 11~2076~ 14~191~ 16~3056~, 17~2532~ 18~2117~ 19~3326~ 20~5479~ 21~2983~ 22~846~;'),
  (4539, 4, 26, 44, 'Of the children of Asher after their families: of Jimna, the family of the Jimnites: of Jesui, the family of the Jesuites: of Beriah, the family of the Beriites.', '[0] 2~01121~ 4~0836~ 7~04940~: 9~03232~, 11~04940~ 14~03232~: 16~03440~, 18~04940~ 21~03441~: 23~01283~, 25~04940~ 28~01284~.'),
  (7739, 9, 20, 2, 'And he said unto him, God forbid; thou shalt not die: behold, my father will do nothing either great or small, but that he will shew it me: and why should my father hide this thing from me? it is not so.', '2~0559~ 6~02486~; 10~04191~: 13~01~ 15~06213~ 16~01697~ 18~01419~ 20~06996~, 25~01540~ 26~0241~* 33~01~ 34~05641~ 36~01697~ [40] [42]'),
  (23711, 40, 17, 1, 'And after six days Jesus taketh Peter, James, and John his brother, and bringeth them up into an high mountain apart,', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~3326~ 2~1803~ 3~2250~ 4~2424~ 5~3880~ 6~2532~ 7~4074~,* 8~2385~, 9~2532~ 10~2491~ 11~846~ 12~80~, 13~2532~ 14~399~ 15~846~ 16~399~ 17~1519~ 19~5308~ 20~3735~ 21~2398~ 22~2596~,*'),
  (20023, 24, 44, 4, 'Howbeit I sent unto you all my servants the prophets, rising early and sending them, saying, Oh, do not this abominable thing that I hate.', '2~07971~ 7~05650~ 9~05030~, 11~07925~ 13~07971~ [14] 15~0559~, 17~06213~ 20~08441~ 21~01697~ 24~08130~.'),
  (23370, 40, 8, 15, 'And he touched her hand, and the fever left her: and she arose, and ministered unto them.', '0~2532~ 2~680~ 3~846~ 4~5495~, 5~2532~ 7~4446~ 8~863~ 9~846~: 10~2532~ 12~1453~, 13~2532~ 14~1247~ 16~846~.'),
  (16723, 20, 11, 26, 'He that withholdeth corn, the people shall curse him: but blessing shall be upon the head of him that selleth it.', '&para; 2~04513~ 3~01250~, 5~03816~ 7~05344~ 10~01293~ [11 12] 15~07218~ 19~07666~ [20]'),
  (18750, 23, 55, 1, 'Ho, every one that thirsteth, come ye to the waters, and he that hath no money; come ye, buy, and eat; yea, come, buy wine and milk without money and without price.', '&para; 0~01945~, 4~06771~, 5~03212~ 9~04325~, 15~03701~; 16~03212~ 18~07666~, 20~0398~; 22~03212~, 23~07666~ 24~03196~ 26~02461~ 28~03701~ 31~04242~.'),
  (962, 1, 32, 30, 'And Jacob called the name of the place Peniel: for I have seen God face to face, and my life is preserved.', '1~03290~ 2~07121~ 4~08034~ 7~04725~ 8~06439~: 12~07200~ 13~0430~ 14~06440~ 16~06440~, 19~05315~ 21~05337~.'),
  (18385, 23, 37, 24, 'By thy servants hast thou reproached the Lord, and hast said, By the multitude of my chariots am I come up to the height of the mountains, to the sides of Lebanon; and I will cut down the tall cedars thereof, and the choice fir trees thereof: and I will enter into the height of his border, and the forest of his Carmel.', '0~03027~ 2~05650~ 5~02778~ 7~0136~, 10~0559~, 13~07230~ 16~07393~ 20~05927~ 23~04791~ 26~02022~, 29~03411~ 31~03844~; 36~03772~ 38~06967~ 39~0730~ [41] 43~04005~ 45~01265~ 50~0935~ 53~04791~ 56~07093~, [57] 59~03293~ 62~03760~.'),
  (1113, 1, 37, 25, 'And they sat down to eat bread: and they lifted up their eyes and looked, and, behold, a company of Ishmeelites came from Gilead with their camels bearing spicery and balm and myrrh, going to carry it down to Egypt.', '3~03427~ 5~0398~ 6~03899~: 10~05375~ 12~05869~ 14~07200~, 18~0736~ 20~03459~ 21~0935~ 23~01568~ 26~01581~ 27~05375~ 28~05219~ 30~06875~ 32~03910~, 33~01980~ [36] 37~03381~ 39~04714~.'),
  (19880, 24, 36, 29, 'And thou shalt say to Jehoiakim king of Judah, Thus saith the LORD; Thou hast burned this roll, saying, Why hast thou written therein, saying, The king of Babylon shall certainly come and destroy this land, and shall cause to cease from thence man and beast?', '3~0559~ 5~03079~ 6~04428~ 8~03063~, 10~0559~ 12~03068~; 15~08313~ 17~04039~, 18~0559~, 22~03789~ 24~0559~, 26~04428~ 28~0894~ 30~0935~ 31~0935~ 33~07843~ 35~0776~, 40~07673~ 43~0120~ 45~0929~?'),
  (15042, 19, 73, 13, 'Verily I have cleansed my heart in vain, and washed my hands in innocency.', '3~02135~ 5~03824~ [6] 7~07385~, 9~07364~ 11~03709~ 13~05356~.'),
  (15663, 19, 106, 3, 'Blessed are they that keep judgment, and he that doeth righteousness at all times.', '0~0835~ [1] 4~08104~ 5~04941~, [6] 9~06213~ 10~06666~ 13~06256~.'),
  (16544, 20, 5, 18, 'Let thy fountain be blessed: and rejoice with the wife of thy youth.', '2~04726~ 4~01288~: 6~08055~ 9~0802~ 12~05271~.'),
  (19868, 24, 36, 17, 'And they asked Baruch, saying, Tell us now, How didst thou write all these words at his mouth?', '2~07592~ 3~01263~, 4~0559~, 5~05046~ 11~03789~ 14~01697~ 17~06310~?'),
  (4130, 4, 14, 17, 'And now, I beseech thee, let the power of my LORD be great, according as thou hast spoken, saying,', '7~03581~ 10~0136~ 12~01431~, 13~0834~ 17~01696~, 18~0559~,'),
  (29895, 55, 4, 9, 'Do thy diligence to come shortly unto me:', '&para; 2~4704~ 4~2064~ 5~5030~ 6~4314~ 7~3165~:'),
  (20342, 25, 2, 1, 'How hath the Lord covered the daughter of Zion with a cloud in his anger, and cast down from heaven unto the earth the beauty of Israel, and remembered not his footstool in the day of his anger!', '&para; 3~0136~ 4~05743~ 6~01323~ 8~06726~ 11~05743~ 14~0639~, [15] 17~07993~ 19~08064~ 22~0776~ 24~08597~ 26~03478~, 28~02142~ 31~07272~ 32~01916~ 34~03117~ 37~0639~!'),
  (25284, 42, 8, 27, 'And when he went forth to land, there met him out of the city a certain man, which had devils long time, and ware no clothes, neither abode in any house, but in the tombs.', '0~1161~ 2~846~ 4~1831~ 5~1909~ 6~1093~, 8~5221~ 9~846~ 11~1537~ 13~4172~ 15~5100~ 16~435~, 17~3739~ 18~2192~ 19~1140~ 20~2425~ 21~1537~* 22~5550~, 23~2532~ 24~1737~ 25~3756~ 26~2440~, 27~3756~ 28~2532~* 29~3306~ 30~1722~ [31] 32~3614~, 33~235~ 34~1722~ 36~3418~.'),
  (5962, 6, 6, 7, 'And he said unto the people, Pass on, and compass the city, and let him that is armed pass on before the ark of the LORD.', '2~0559~ 5~05971~, 7~05674~, 9~05437~ 11~05892~, 17~02502~ 19~05674~ 20~06440~ 22~0727~ 25~03068~.'),
  (29426, 50, 2, 19, 'But I trust in the Lord Jesus to send Timotheus shortly unto you, that I also may be of good comfort, when I know your state.', '0~1161~ 2~1679~ 3~1722~ 5~2962~ 6~2424~ 8~3992~ 9~5095~ 10~5030~ 12~5213~, 13~2443~ 15~2504~ 20~2174~, 23~1097~ 24~5216~ 25~4012~.'),
  (21954, 27, 7, 12, 'As concerning the rest of the beasts, they had their dominion taken away: yet their lives were prolonged for a season and time.', '3~07606~ 6~02423~, 10~07985~ 12~05709~: 15~02417~ 17~03052~ 18~05705~ 20~02166~ 22~05732~.'),
  (20560, 26, 5, 5, 'Thus saith the Lord GOD; This is Jerusalem: I have set it in the midst of the nations and countries that are round about her.', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~0136~ 4~03069~; [6] 7~03389~: 10~07760~ 14~08432~ 17~01471~ 19~0776~ [20 21] 23~05439~'),
  (4138, 4, 14, 25, '(Now the Amalekites and the Canaanites dwelt in the valley.) To morrow turn you, and get you into the wilderness by the way of the Red sea.', '2~06003~ 5~03669~ 6~03427~ 9~06010~) 11~04279~ 12~06437~ 15~05265~ 19~04057~ 22~01870~ 25~05488~ 26~03220~.'),
  (29875, 55, 3, 6, 'For of this sort are they which creep into houses, and lead captive silly women laden with sins, led away with divers lusts,', '0~1063~ 1~1537~ 3~5130~ 5~1526~ 7~1744~ 8~1519~ 9~3614~, 10~2532~ 12~162~ 14~1133~ 15~4987~ 17~266~, 19~71~ 21~4164~ 22~1939~,'),
  (7494, 9, 13, 2, 'Saul chose him three thousand men of Israel; whereof two thousand were with Saul in Michmash and in mount Bethel, and a thousand were with Jonathan in Gibeah of Benjamin: and the rest of the people he sent every man to his tent.', '0~07586~ 1~0977~ 3~07969~ 4~0505~ [5] 7~03478~; [8] 10~0505~ 13~07586~ 15~04363~ 18~02022~ 19~01008~, 22~0505~ 25~03129~ 27~01390~ 29~01144~: 32~03499~ 35~05971~ 37~07971~ 39~0376~ 42~0168~.'),
  (26864, 43, 19, 24, 'They said therefore among themselves, Let us not rend it, but cast lots for it, whose it shall be: that the scripture might be fulfilled, which saith, They parted my raiment among them, and for my vesture they did cast lots. These things therefore the soldiers did.', '1~2036~ 2~3767~ 3~4314~ 4~240~, 6~4977~ 7~3361~ 8~4977~ 9~846~, 10~235~ 12~2975~ 13~4012~ 14~846~, 15~5101~ 18~2071~: 19~2443~ 21~1124~ 24~4137~, 25~3588~ 26~3004~, 28~1266~ 29~3450~ 30~2440~ 32~1438~, 33~2532~ 34~1909~ 35~3450~ 36~2441~ 39~906~ 40~2819~. 42~3303~ 43~5023~* 44~3767~ 46~4757~ 47~4160~.'),
  (29377, 49, 6, 24, 'Grace be with all them that love our Lord Jesus Christ in sincerity. Amen.', '0~5485~ [1] 2~3326~ 3~3956~ 6~25~ 7~2257~ 8~2962~ 9~2424~ 10~5547~ 11~1722~ 12~861~. 13~281~ 14~4314~.* [15 [16] 17~2180~ 18~1125~ 19~575~ 20~4516~, 21~1223~ 22] 22~5190~'),
  (5625, 5, 28, 8, 'The LORD shall command the blessing upon thee in thy storehouses, and in all that thou settest thine hand unto; and he shall bless thee in the land which the LORD thy God giveth thee.', '1~03068~ 3~06680~ 5~01293~ 10~0618~, 16~04916~ 18~03027~ 23~01288~ 27~0776~ 30~03068~ 32~0430~ 33~05414~'),
  (11518, 14, 15, 19, 'And there was no more war unto the five and thirtieth year of the reign of Asa.', '[4] 5~04421~ 8~02568~ 10~07970~ 11~08141~ 14~04438~ 16~0609~.'),
  (21674, 26, 46, 10, 'And the prince in the midst of them, when they go in, shall go in; and when they go forth, shall go forth.', '2~05387~ 5~08432~ 11~0935~, 14~0935~; 19~03318~, 22~03318~.'),
  (3456, 3, 24, 5, 'And thou shalt take fine flour, and bake twelve cakes thereof: two tenth deals shall be in one cake.', '3~03947~ 5~05560~, 7~0644~ 8~06240~ 9~02471~ 11~08147~ 13~06241~ 17~0259~ 18~02471~.'),
  (9213, 11, 13, 21, 'And he cried unto the man of God that came from Judah, saying, Thus saith the LORD, Forasmuch as thou hast disobeyed the mouth of the LORD, and hast not kept the commandment which the LORD thy God commanded thee,', '2~07121~ 5~0376~ 7~0430~ 9~0935~ 11~03063~, 12~0559~, 14~0559~ 16~03068~, 18~03282~ 21~04784~ 23~06310~ 26~03068~, 30~08104~ 32~04687~ 35~03068~ 37~0430~ 38~06680~'),
  (27599, 44, 18, 26, 'And he began to speak boldly in the synagogue: whom when Aquila and Priscilla had heard, they took him unto them, and expounded unto him the way of God more perfectly.', '0~5037~ 1~3778~ 2~756~ 5~3955~ 6~1722~ 8~4864~: 9~846~ 10~1161~ 11~207~ 12~2532~ 13~4252~ 15~191~, 17~4355~ 18~846~ [20] 21~2532~ 22~1620~ 24~846~ 26~3598~ 28~2316~ 30~197~.'),
  (6952, 7, 15, 16, 'And Samson said, With the jawbone of an ass, heaps upon heaps, with the jaw of an ass have I slain a thousand men.', '1~08123~ 2~0559~, 5~03895~ 8~02543~, 9~02565~ 11~02565~, 14~03895~ 17~02543~ 20~05221~ 22~0505~ 23~0376~.'),
  (21277, 26, 32, 20, 'They shall fall in the midst of them that are slain by the sword: she is delivered to the sword: draw her and all her multitudes.', '2~05307~ 5~08432~ [7 9] 10~02491~ 13~02719~: 16~05414~ 19~02719~: 20~04900~ 25~01995~.'),
  (5327, 5, 15, 2, 'And this is the manner of the release: Every creditor that lendeth ought unto his neighbour shall release it; he shall not exact it of his neighbour, or of his brother; because it is called the LORD''S release.', '[2] 4~01697~ 7~08059~: 9~03027~ 10~01167~* 11~04874~ 12~05383~ [13] 16~07453~ 18~08058~ [19] 23~05065~ [24] 27~07453~, 31~0251~; 35~07121~ 37~03068~ 38~08059~.'),
  (10329, 13, 2, 15, 'Ozem the sixth, David the seventh:', '0~0684~ 2~08345~, 3~01732~ 5~07637~:'),
  (3671, 4, 2, 8, 'And his host, and those that were numbered thereof, were fifty and seven thousand and four hundred.', '2~06635~, 7~06485~ [9] 10~02572~ 12~07651~ 13~0505~ 15~0702~ 16~03967~.'),
  (715, 1, 26, 19, 'And Isaac''s servants digged in the valley, and found there a well of springing water.', '1~03327~ 2~05650~ 3~02658~ 6~05158~, 8~04672~ 11~0875~ 13~02416~ 14~04325~.'),
  (453, 1, 18, 25, 'That be far from thee to do after this manner, to slay the righteous with the wicked: and that the righteous should be as the wicked, that be far from thee: Shall not the Judge of all the earth do right?', '2~02486~ 6~06213~ 9~01697~, 11~04191~ 13~06662~ 16~07563~: 20~06662~ 25~07563~, 28~02486~ 34~08199~ 38~0776~ 39~06213~ 40~04941~?'),
  (4424, 4, 23, 3, 'And Balaam said unto Balak, Stand by thy burnt offering, and I will go: peradventure the LORD will come to meet me: and whatsoever he sheweth me I will tell thee. And he went to an high place.', '1~01109~ 2~0559~ 4~01111~, 5~03320~ 9~05930~, 13~03212~: 16~03068~ 18~07136~ 20~07125~ 23~01697~ 25~07200~ 29~05046~ 33~03212~ 37~08205~.'),
  (23516, 40, 12, 17, 'That it might be fulfilled which was spoken by Esaias the prophet, saying,', '0~3704~ 4~4137~ 5~3588~ 7~4483~ 8~1223~ 9~2268~ 11~4396~, 12~3004~,'),
  (23893, 40, 22, 11, 'And when the king came in to see the guests, he saw there a man which had not on a wedding garment:', '0~1161~ 1~1525~ 3~935~ 5~1525~ 7~2300~ 9~345~, 11~1492~ 12~1563~ 14~444~ 16~1746~ 17~3756~ 18~1746~ 20~1062~ 21~1742~:'),
  (26660, 43, 13, 15, 'For I have given you an example, that ye should do as I have done to you.', '0~1063~ 3~1325~ 4~5213~ 6~5262~, 7~2443~ 8~5210~ 10~4160~ 11~2532~ 12~2531~* 13~1473~ 15~4160~ 17~5213~.'),
  (22821, 36, 2, 7, 'And the coast shall be for the remnant of the house of Judah; they shall feed thereupon: in the houses of Ashkelon shall they lie down in the evening: for the LORD their God shall visit them, and turn away their captivity.', '2~02256~ 7~07611~ 10~01004~ 12~03063~; 15~07462~ 19~01004~ 21~0831~ 25~07257~ 28~06153~: 31~03068~ 33~0430~ 35~06485~ 39~07725~ 41~07622~ 42~07622~.*'),
  (30585, 62, 2, 19, 'They went out from us, but they were not of us; for if they had been of us, they would no doubt have continued with us: but they went out, that they might be made manifest that they were not all of us.', '2~1831~ 3~1537~ 4~2257~, 5~235~ 7~2258~ 8~3756~ 9~1537~ 10~2257~; 11~1063~ 12~1487~ 15~2258~ 16~1537~ 17~2257~, 19~302~ [20 21] 23~3306~ 24~3326~ 25~2257~: 26~235~ [27 29] 30~2443~ 35~5319~ 36~3754~ 38~1526~ 39~3756~ 40~3956~ 41~1537~ 42~2257~.'),
  (30307, 59, 1, 25, 'But whoso looketh into the perfect law of liberty, and continueth therein, he being not a forgetful hearer, but a doer of the work, this man shall be blessed in his deed.', '0~1161~ 2~3879~ 3~1519~ 5~5046~ 6~3551~ 8~1657~, 9~2532~ 10~3887~ [11] 12~3778~ 13~1096~ 14~3756~ 16~1953~ 17~202~, 18~235~ 20~4163~ 23~2041~, 25~3778~ 27~2071~ 28~3107~ 29~1722~ 30~846~ 31~4162~.'),
  (20628, 26, 8, 15, 'Then said he unto me, Hast thou seen this, O son of man? turn thee yet again, and thou shalt see greater abominations than these.', '1~0559~ 7~07200~ [8] 10~01121~ 12~0120~? 13~07725~ [17] 20~07200~ 21~01419~ 22~08441~'),
  (1227, 1, 41, 27, 'And the seven thin and ill favoured kine that came up after them are seven years; and the seven empty ears blasted with the east wind shall be seven years of famine.', '2~07651~ 3~07534~ 6~07451~ 7~06510~ 10~05927~ 12~0310~ [13] 14~07651~ 15~08141~; 18~07651~ 19~07386~ 20~07641~ 21~07710~ 25~06921~ 28~07651~ 29~08141~ 31~07458~.'),
  (4870, 4, 35, 19, 'The revenger of blood himself shall slay the murderer: when he meeteth him, he shall slay him.', '1~01350~ 3~01818~ 6~04191~ 8~07523~: 11~06293~ 13~01931~ 15~04191~'),
  (17864, 23, 10, 5, 'O Assyrian, the rod of mine anger, and the staff in their hand is mine indignation.', '&para; 0~01945~ 1~0804~, 3~07626~ 6~0639~, 9~04294~ 12~03027~ 15~02195~.'),
  (13246, 18, 15, 34, 'For the congregation of hypocrites shall be desolate, and fire shall consume the tabernacles of bribery.', '2~05712~ 4~02611~ [5 6] 7~01565~, 9~0784~ 11~0398~ 13~0168~ 15~07810~.'),
  (16072, 19, 119, 165, 'Great peace have they which love thy law: and nothing shall offend them.', '&para; 0~07227~ 1~07965~ 5~0157~ 7~08451~: 11~04383~'),
  (6555, 7, 2, 3, 'Wherefore I also said, I will not drive them out from before you; but they shall be as thorns in your sides, and their gods shall be a snare unto you.', '3~0559~, 9~01644~ 11~06440~ [17 18] 21~06654~, 24~0430~ 28~04170~'),
  (29340, 49, 5, 20, 'Giving thanks always for all things unto God and the Father in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ;', '1~2168~ 2~3842~ 3~5228~ 5~3956~ 7~2316~ 8~2532~ 10~3962~ 11~1722~ 13~3686~ 15~2257~ 16~2962~ 17~2424~ 18~5547~;'),
  (8341, 10, 13, 17, 'Then he called his servant that ministered unto him, and said, Put now this woman out from me, and bolt the door after her.', '2~07121~ 4~05288~ 6~08334~ 10~0559~, 11~07971~ [14] 15~02351~ 19~05274~ 21~01817~ 22~0310~'),
  (20033, 24, 44, 14, 'So that none of the remnant of Judah, which are gone into the land of Egypt to sojourn there, shall escape or remain, that they should return into the land of Judah, to the which they have a desire to return to dwell there: for none shall return but such as shall escape.', '5~07611~ 7~03063~, 10~0935~ 13~0776~ 15~04714~ 17~01481~ 20~06412~ 22~08300~, 26~07725~ 29~0776~ 31~03063~, 36~05375~ 38~05315~ 40~07725~ 42~03427~ 47~07725~ 52~06405~.'),
  (13221, 18, 15, 9, 'What knowest thou, that we know not? what understandest thou, which is not in us?', '1~03045~ 5~03045~ [7] 8~0995~ [11]'),
  (6777, 7, 9, 16, 'Now therefore, if ye have done truly and sincerely, in that ye have made Abimelech king, and if ye have dealt well with Jerubbaal and his house, and have done unto him according to the deserving of his hands;', '5~06213~ 6~0571~ 8~08549~, 14~040~ 15~04427~, 20~06213~ 21~02896~ 23~03378~ 26~01004~, 29~06213~ 35~01576~ 38~03027~;'),
  (4906, 5, 1, 8, 'Behold, I have set the land before you: go in and possess the land which the LORD sware unto your fathers, Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, to give unto them and to their seed after them.', '0~07200~, 3~05414~ 5~0776~ 6~06440~ 8~0935~ 11~03423~ 13~0776~ 16~03068~ 17~07650~ 20~01~, 21~085~, 22~03327~, 24~03290~, 26~05414~ 32~02233~ 33~0310~'),
  (2856, 3, 6, 2, 'If a soul sin, and commit a trespass against the LORD, and lie unto his neighbour in that which was delivered him to keep, or in fellowship, or in a thing taken away by violence, or hath deceived his neighbour;', '2~05315~ 3~02398~, 5~04603~ 7~04604~ 10~03068~, 12~03584~ 15~05997~ 20~06487~ 26~03027~ 27~08667~,* 35~01498~, 38~06231~ 40~05997~;'),
  (3588, 3, 27, 13, 'But if he will at all redeem it, then he shall add a fifth part thereof unto thy estimation.', '5~01350~ 6~01350~ 11~03254~ 13~02549~ [14] 18~06187~.'),
  (18827, 23, 59, 18, 'According to their deeds, accordingly he will repay, fury to his adversaries, recompense to his enemies; to the islands he will repay recompense.', '1~05921~ [2] 3~01578~, 7~07999~, 8~02534~ 11~06862~, 12~01576~ 15~0341~; 18~0339~ 21~07999~ 22~01576~.'),
  (12755, 17, 2, 22, 'And the thing was known to Mordecai, who told it unto Esther the queen; and Esther certified the king thereof in Mordecai''s name.', '2~01697~ 4~03045~ 6~04782~, 8~05046~ [9] 11~0635~ 13~04436~; 15~0635~ 16~0559~ 18~04428~ [19] 21~04782~ 22~08034~.'),
  (21470, 26, 39, 13, 'Yea, all the people of the land shall bury them; and it shall be to them a renown the day that I shall be glorified, saith the Lord GOD.', '3~05971~ 6~0776~ 8~06912~ [9] 17~08034~ 19~03117~ 24~03513~, 25~05002~ 27~0136~ 28~03069~.'),
  (16002, 19, 119, 95, 'The wicked have waited for me to destroy me: but I will consider thy testimonies.', '&para; 1~07563~ 3~06960~ 7~06~ [9] 12~0995~ 14~05713~.'),
  (30068, 58, 6, 8, 'But that which beareth thorns and briers is rejected, and is nigh unto cursing; whose end is to be burned.', '0~1161~ 3~1627~ 4~173~ 5~2532~ 6~5146~ [7] 8~96~, 9~2532~ [10] 11~1451~ 13~2671~; 14~3739~ 15~5056~ [16] 17~1519~ 19~2740~.'),
  (19350, 24, 16, 5, 'For thus saith the LORD, Enter not into the house of mourning, neither go to lament nor bemoan them: for I have taken away my peace from this people, saith the LORD, even lovingkindness and mercies.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~, 5~0935~ 9~01004~ 11~04798~, 13~03212~ 15~05594~ 17~05110~ 23~0622~ 25~07965~ 28~05971~, 29~05002~ 31~03068~, [32] 33~02617~ 35~07356~.'),
  (24427, 41, 6, 10, 'And he said unto them, In what place soever ye enter into an house, there abide till ye depart from that place.', '0~2532~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 8~1437~ 9~3699~ 10~1525~ 11~1519~ 13~3614~, 14~1563~ 15~3306~ 16~302~ 17~2193~ 18~1831~ 21~1564~.'),
  (21422, 26, 37, 16, 'Moreover, thou son of man, take thee one stick, and write upon it, For Judah, and for the children of Israel his companions: then take another stick, and write upon it, For Joseph, the stick of Ephraim, and for all the house of Israel his companions:', '2~01121~ 4~0120~, 5~03947~ 7~0259~ 8~06086~, 10~03789~ 14~03063~, 18~01121~ 20~03478~ 22~02270~: 24~03947~ 25~0259~ 26~06086~, 28~03789~ 32~03130~, 34~06086~ 36~0669~, [38] 41~01004~ 43~03478~ 45~02270~:'),
  (10295, 13, 1, 35, 'The sons of Esau; Eliphaz, Reuel, and Jeush, and Jaalam, and Korah.', '1~01121~ 3~06215~; 4~0464~, 5~07467~, 7~03266~, 9~03281~, 11~07141~.'),
  (19783, 24, 32, 43, 'And fields shall be bought in this land, whereof ye say, It is desolate without man or beast; it is given into the hand of the Chaldeans.', '1~07704~ 4~07069~ 7~0776~, 10~0559~, [11 12] 13~08077~ 15~0120~ 17~0929~; 20~05414~ 23~03027~ 26~03778~.'),
  (24142, 40, 27, 3, 'Then Judas, which had betrayed him, when he saw that he was condemned, repented himself, and brought again the thirty pieces of silver to the chief priests and elders,', '0~5119~ 1~2455~, 2~3588~ 4~3860~ 5~846~, 8~1492~ 9~3754~ 12~2632~, 14~3338~, 17~654~ 19~5144~ 22~694~ 26~749~ 27~2532~ 28~4245~,'),
  (5155, 5, 8, 12, 'Lest when thou hast eaten and art full, and hast built goodly houses, and dwelt therein;', '[1] 4~0398~ 7~07646~, 10~01129~ 11~02896~ 12~01004~, 14~03427~ [15]'),
  (18595, 23, 45, 25, 'In the LORD shall all the seed of Israel be justified, and shall glory.', '2~03068~ 6~02233~ 8~03478~ 10~06663~, 13~01984~.'),
  (15684, 19, 106, 24, 'Yea, they despised the pleasant land, they believed not his word:', '2~03988~ 4~02532~ 5~0776~, 7~0539~ 10~01697~:'),
  (23398, 40, 9, 9, 'And as Jesus passed forth from thence, he saw a man, named Matthew, sitting at the receipt of custom: and he saith unto him, Follow me. And he arose, and followed him.', '&para; 1~2532~ 2~2424~ 4~3855~ 6~1564~, 8~1492~ 10~444~, 11~3004~ 12~3156~, 13~2521~ 14~1909~ 18~5058~: 19~2532~ 21~3004~ 23~846~, 24~190~ 25~3427~. 26~2532~ 28~450~, 30~190~ 31~846~.'),
  (21564, 26, 42, 3, 'Over against the twenty cubits which were for the inner court, and over against the pavement which was for the utter court, was gallery against gallery in three stories.', '3~06242~ [4] [6] 9~06442~ 10~02691~, 15~07531~ [17] 20~02435~ 21~02691~, [22] 23~0862~ 24~06440~ 25~0862~ 27~07992~ [28]'),
  (8541, 10, 19, 22, 'And David said, What have I to do with you, ye sons of Zeruiah, that ye should this day be adversaries unto me? shall there any man be put to death this day in Israel? for do not I know that I am this day king over Israel?', '1~01732~ 2~0559~, 11~01121~ 13~06870~, 18~03117~ 20~07854~ 26~0376~ 30~04191~ 32~03117~ 34~03478~? 39~03045~ [42] 44~03117~ 45~04428~ 47~03478~?'),
  (18630, 23, 48, 7, 'They are created now, and not from the beginning; even before the day when thou heardest them not; lest thou shouldest say, Behold, I knew them.', '2~01254~ 10~06440~ 12~03117~ 15~08085~ 21~0559~, 24~03045~'),
  (9538, 11, 22, 50, 'And Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in the city of David his father: and Jehoram his son reigned in his stead.', '1~03092~ 2~07901~ 5~01~, 8~06912~ 11~01~ 14~05892~ 16~01732~ 18~01~: 20~03088~ 22~01121~ 23~04427~'),
  (7504, 9, 13, 12, 'Therefore said I, The Philistines will come down now upon me to Gilgal, and I have not made supplication unto the LORD: I forced myself therefore, and offered a burnt offering.', '1~0559~ 4~06430~ 7~03381~ 12~01537~, 18~02470~ 19~06440~ 21~03068~: 23~0662~ 27~05927~ 30~05930~.'),
  (6433, 6, 21, 45, 'There failed not ought of any good thing which the LORD had spoken unto the house of Israel; all came to pass.', '1~05307~ 3~01697~ 6~02896~ 7~01697~ 10~03068~ 12~01696~ 15~01004~ 17~03478~; 21~0935~.'),
  (19977, 24, 41, 11, 'But when Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the captains of the forces that were with him, heard of all the evil that Ishmael the son of Nethaniah had done,', '&para; 2~03110~ 4~01121~ 6~07143~, 10~08269~ 13~02428~ [15] 18~08085~ 22~07451~ 24~03458~ 26~01121~ 28~05418~ 30~06213~,'),
  (4868, 4, 35, 17, 'And if he smite him with throwing a stone, wherewith he may die, and he die, he is a murderer: the murderer shall surely be put to death.', '3~05221~ 6~03027~ 8~068~, 12~04191~, 15~04191~, [17] 19~07523~: 21~07523~ 23~04191~ 27~04191~.'),
  (13216, 18, 15, 4, 'Yea, thou castest off fear, and restrainest prayer before God.', '3~06565~ 4~03374~, 6~01639~ 7~07881~ 8~06440~ 9~0410~.'),
  (2655, 2, 38, 17, 'And the sockets for the pillars were of brass; the hooks of the pillars and their fillets of silver; and the overlaying of their chapiters of silver; and all the pillars of the court were filleted with silver.', '2~0134~ 5~05982~ [6 7] 8~05178~; 10~02053~ 13~05982~ 16~02838~ [17] 18~03701~; 21~06826~ 24~07218~ [25] 26~03701~; 30~05982~ 33~02691~ [34] 35~02836~ 37~03701~.'),
  (19521, 24, 23, 28, 'The prophet that hath a dream, let him tell a dream; and he that hath my word, let him speak my word faithfully. What is the chaff to the wheat? saith the LORD.', '1~05030~ 5~02472~, 8~05608~ 10~02472~; 16~01697~, 19~01696~ 21~01697~ 22~0571~. [24] 26~08401~ 29~01250~? 30~05002~ 32~03068~.'),
  (7, 1, 1, 7, 'And God made the firmament, and divided the waters which were under the firmament from the waters which were above the firmament: and it was so.', '1~0430~ 2~06213~ 4~07549~, 6~0914~ 8~04325~ 9~0834~ [10] 11~08478~ 13~07549~ 16~04325~ 17~0834~ [18] 19~05921~ 21~07549~: 25~03651~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (26145, 43, 3, 10, 'Jesus answered and said unto him, Art thou a master of Israel, and knowest not these things?', '0~2424~ 1~611~ 2~2532~ 3~2036~ 5~846~, 6~1488~ 7~4771~ 9~1320~ 11~2474~, 12~2532~ 13~1097~ 14~3756~ 16~5023~?'),
  (19399, 24, 18, 6, 'O house of Israel, cannot I do with you as this potter? saith the LORD. Behold, as the clay is in the potter''s hand, so are ye in mine hand, O house of Israel.', '1~01004~ 3~03478~, 4~03201~ 6~06213~ 11~03335~? 12~05002~ 14~03068~. 18~02563~ [19] 22~03335~ 23~03027~, [25] 29~03027~, 31~01004~ 33~03478~.'),
  (16455, 20, 2, 13, 'Who leave the paths of uprightness, to walk in the ways of darkness;', '1~05800~ 3~0734~ 5~03476~, 7~03212~ 10~01870~ 12~02822~;'),
  (10456, 13, 5, 20, 'And they were helped against them, and the Hagarites were delivered into their hand, and all that were with them: for they cried to God in the battle, and he was entreated of them; because they put their trust in him.', '3~05826~ 8~01905~ 10~05414~ 13~03027~, [17] 22~02199~ 24~0430~ 27~04421~, 31~06279~ 38~0982~'),
  (3244, 3, 17, 4, 'And bringeth it not unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, to offer an offering unto the LORD before the tabernacle of the LORD; blood shall be imputed unto that man; he hath shed blood; and that man shall be cut off from among his people:', '1~0935~ 6~06607~ 9~0168~ 12~04150~, 14~07126~ 16~07133~ 19~03068~ 20~06440~ 22~04908~ 25~03068~; 26~01818~ 29~02803~ 32~0376~; 35~08210~ 36~01818~; 39~0376~ 43~03772~ 45~07130~ 47~05971~:'),
  (26556, 43, 11, 18, 'Now Bethany was nigh unto Jerusalem, about fifteen furlongs off:', '0~1161~ 1~963~ 2~2258~ 3~1451~ 5~2414~, 6~5613~ 7~1178~ 8~4712~ 9~575~:'),
  (12216, 15, 8, 6, 'Of the sons also of Adin; Ebed the son of Jonathan, and with him fifty males.', '2~01121~ 5~05720~; 6~05651~ 8~01121~ 10~03129~, 14~02572~ 15~02145~.'),
  (16707, 20, 11, 10, 'When it goeth well with the righteous, the city rejoiceth: and when the wicked perish, there is shouting.', '&para; 3~02898~ 6~06662~, 8~07151~ 9~05970~: 13~07563~ 14~06~, [15 16] 17~07440~.'),
  (15973, 19, 119, 66, 'Teach me good judgment and knowledge: for I have believed thy commandments.', '0~03925~ 2~02898~ 3~02940~ 5~01847~: 9~0539~ 11~04687~.'),
  (25233, 42, 7, 26, 'But what went ye out for to see? A prophet? Yea, I say unto you, and much more than a prophet.', '0~235~ 1~5101~ 4~1831~ 7~1492~? 9~4396~? 10~3483~, 12~3004~ 14~5213~, 15~2532~ 17~4055~ 20~4396~.'),
  (3030, 3, 11, 28, 'And he that beareth the carcase of them shall wash his clothes, and be unclean until the even: they are unclean unto you.', '3~05375~ 5~05038~ 9~03526~ 11~0899~, 14~02930~ 17~06153~: [19] 20~02931~'),
  (7333, 9, 5, 7, 'And when the men of Ashdod saw that it was so, they said, The ark of the God of Israel shall not abide with us: for his hand is sore upon us, and upon Dagon our god.', '3~0582~ 5~0795~ 6~07200~ [8 9] 12~0559~, 14~0727~ 17~0430~ 19~03478~ 22~03427~ 27~03027~ 29~07185~ 34~01712~ 36~0430~.'),
  (10757, 13, 12, 29, 'And of the children of Benjamin, the kindred of Saul, three thousand: for hitherto the greatest part of them had kept the ward of the house of Saul.', '3~01121~ 5~01144~, 7~0251~ 9~07586~, 10~07969~ 11~0505~: 15~04768~ 20~08104~ 22~04931~ 25~01004~ 27~07586~.'),
  (20827, 26, 16, 56, 'For thy sister Sodom was not mentioned by thy mouth in the day of thy pride,', '2~0269~ 3~05467~ 6~08052~ 9~06310~ 12~03117~ 15~01347~,'),
  (29716, 54, 1, 4, 'Neither give heed to fables and endless genealogies, which minister questions, rather than godly edifying which is in faith: so do.', '0~3366~ 2~4337~ 4~3454~ 5~2532~ 6~562~ 7~1076~, 8~3748~ 9~3930~ 10~2214~, 11~3123~ 12~2228~ 13~2316~ 14~3620~ 15~3588~ 17~1722~ 18~4102~: [19 20]'),
  (894, 1, 31, 17, 'Then Jacob rose up, and set his sons and his wives upon camels;', '&para; 1~03290~ 3~06965~, 5~05375~ 7~01121~ 10~0802~ 12~01581~;'),
  (30441, 60, 3, 1, 'Likewise, ye wives, be in subjection to your own husbands; that, if any obey not the word, they also may without the word be won by the conversation of the wives;', '&para; 0~3668~, 2~1135~, [3] 5~5293~ 8~2398~ 9~435~; 10~2443~, 12~1536~ 14~544~ 16~3056~, 17~2770~ 18~2532~ 19~2770~ 20~427~ 22~3056~ 24~2770~ 25~1223~ 27~391~ 30~1135~;'),
  (25567, 42, 14, 1, 'And it came to pass, as he went into the house of one of the chief Pharisees to eat bread on the sabbath day, that they watched him.', '&para; 0~2532~ 4~1096~, 5~1722~ 6~846~ 7~2064~ 8~1519~ 10~3624~ 12~5100~ 15~758~ 16~5330~ 18~5315~ 19~740~ 22~4521~ 24~2532~ 25~846~ 26~2258~ 27~3906~* 28~846~.'),
  (16602, 20, 7, 18, 'Come, let us take our fill of love until the morning: let us solace ourselves with loves.', '0~03212~, 5~07301~ 7~01730~ 10~01242~: 13~05965~ 16~0159~.'),
  (1588, 2, 3, 4, 'And when the LORD saw that he turned aside to see, God called unto him out of the midst of the bush, and said, Moses, Moses. And he said, Here am I.', '3~03068~ 4~07200~ 8~05493~ 10~07200~, 11~0430~ 12~07121~ 18~08432~ 21~05572~, 23~0559~, 24~04872~, 25~04872~. 28~0559~, [30]'),
  (4487, 4, 25, 11, 'Phinehas, the son of Eleazar, the son of Aaron the priest, hath turned my wrath away from the children of Israel, while he was zealous for my sake among them, that I consumed not the children of Israel in my jealousy.', '0~06372~, 2~01121~ 4~0499~, 6~01121~ 8~0175~ 10~03548~, 12~07725~ 14~02534~ 15~07725~ 18~01121~ 20~03478~, 24~07065~ 27~07068~ 28~08432~ 32~03615~ 35~01121~ 37~03478~ 40~07068~.'),
  (20337, 25, 1, 18, 'The LORD is righteous; for I have rebelled against his commandment: hear, I pray you, all people, and behold my sorrow: my virgins and my young men are gone into captivity.', '1~03068~ 3~06662~; 7~04784~ 10~06310~: 11~08085~, 16~05971~, 18~07200~ 20~04341~: 22~01330~ 26~0970~ 28~01980~ 30~07628~.'),
  (29335, 49, 5, 15, 'See then that ye walk circumspectly, not as fools, but as wise,', '0~991~ 1~3767~ 2~4459~ 4~4043~ 5~199~, 6~3361~ 7~5613~ 8~781~, 9~235~ 10~5613~ 11~4680~,'),
  (27356, 44, 12, 3, 'And because he saw it pleased the Jews, he proceeded further to take Peter also. (Then were the days of unleavened bread.)', '0~2532~ 3~1492~ 4~3754~ 5~2076~ 6~701~* 8~2453~, 11~4369~ 13~4815~ 14~4074~ 15~2532~. 16~1161~* 18~2258~ 20~2250~ 23~106~)'),
  (2549, 2, 35, 13, 'The table, and his staves, and all his vessels, and the shewbread,', '1~07979~, 4~0905~, 8~03627~, 11~03899~ 12~06440~,*'),
  (13976, 19, 4, 2, 'O ye sons of men, how long will ye turn my glory into shame? how long will ye love vanity, and seek after leasing? Selah.', '2~01121~ 4~0376~, 6~05704~ [7 9] 11~03519~ 13~03639~? [14 15] 18~0157~ 19~07385~, [20] 21~01245~ 23~03577~? 24~05542~.'),
  (9255, 11, 14, 29, 'Now the rest of the acts of Rehoboam, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah?', '2~03499~ 5~01697~ 7~07346~, 12~06213~, [13] 16~03789~ 19~05612~ 22~03117~ 23~01697~ 25~04428~ 27~03063~?'),
  (10337, 13, 2, 23, 'And he took Geshur, and Aram, with the towns of Jair, from them, with Kenath, and the towns thereof, even threescore cities. All these belonged to the sons of Machir, the father of Gilead.', '2~03947~ 3~01650~, 5~0758~, 8~02333~ 10~02971~, 14~07079~, 17~01323~ [19] 20~08346~ 21~05892~. [24 25] 27~01121~ 29~04353~ 31~01~ 33~01568~.'),
  (2406, 2, 30, 19, 'For Aaron and his sons shall wash their hands and their feet thereat:', '1~0175~ 4~01121~ 6~07364~ 8~03027~ 11~07272~'),
  (24244, 41, 1, 19, 'And when he had gone a little farther thence, he saw James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother, who also were in the ship mending their nets.', '0~2532~ 4~4260~ 6~3641~ 7~4260~ 8~1564~, 10~1492~ 11~2385~ [13] 13~3588~ 15~2199~, 16~2532~ 17~2491~ 18~846~ 19~80~, 20~846~ 21~2532~ 23~1722~ 25~4143~ 26~2675~ 28~1350~.'),
  (2552, 2, 35, 16, 'The altar of burnt offering, with his brazen grate, his staves, and all his vessels, the laver and his foot,', '1~04196~ 4~05930~, 7~05178~ 8~04345~, 10~0905~, 14~03627~, 16~03595~ 19~03653~,'),
  (18333, 23, 35, 4, 'Say to them that are of a fearful heart, Be strong, fear not: behold, your God will come with vengeance, even God with a recompense; he will come and save you.', '0~0559~ [3 4] 7~04116~ 8~03820~, 10~02388~, 11~03372~ 15~0430~ 17~0935~ [18] 19~05359~, [20] 21~0430~ [22] 24~01576~; 27~0935~ 29~03467~'),
  (10573, 13, 7, 30, 'The sons of Asher; Imnah, and Isuah, and Ishuai, and Beriah, and Serah their sister.', '1~01121~ 3~0836~; 4~03232~, 6~03440~, 8~03438~, 10~01283~, 12~08294~ 14~0269~.'),
  (466, 1, 19, 5, 'And they called unto Lot, and said unto him, Where are the men which came in to thee this night? bring them out unto us, that we may know them.', '2~07121~ 4~03876~, 6~0559~ [10] 12~0582~ 15~0935~ 19~03915~? 22~03318~ 28~03045~'),
  (28656, 46, 12, 6, 'And there are diversities of operations, but it is the same God which worketh all in all.', '0~2532~ 2~1526~ 3~1243~ 5~1755~, 6~1161~ 8~2076~ 10~846~ 11~2316~ 12~3588~ 13~1754~ 14~3956~ 15~1722~ 16~3956~.'),
  (1599, 2, 3, 15, 'And God said moreover unto Moses, Thus shalt thou say unto the children of Israel, The LORD God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, hath sent me unto you: this is my name for ever, and this is my memorial unto all generations.', '1~0430~ 2~0559~ 3~05750~ 5~04872~, 9~0559~ 12~01121~ 14~03478~, 16~03068~ 17~0430~ 20~01~, 22~0430~ 24~085~, 26~0430~ 28~03327~, 31~0430~ 33~03290~, 35~07971~ [40] 42~08034~ 44~05769~, [47] 49~02143~ 51~01755~ 52~01755~.'),
  (21612, 26, 44, 4, 'Then brought he me the way of the north gate before the house: and I looked, and, behold, the glory of the LORD filled the house of the LORD: and I fell upon my face.', '&para; 1~0935~ 5~01870~ 8~06828~ 9~08179~ 10~06440~ 12~01004~: 15~07200~, 19~03519~ 22~03068~ 23~04390~ 25~01004~ 28~03068~: 31~05307~ 34~06440~.'),
  (15948, 19, 119, 41, 'VAU. Let thy mercies come also unto me, O LORD, even thy salvation, according to thy word.', '&para; 3~02617~ 4~0935~ 9~03068~, [10] 12~08668~, 16~0565~.'),
  (23025, 38, 9, 17, 'For how great is his goodness, and how great is his beauty! corn shall make the young men cheerful, and new wine the maids.', '[3] 5~02898~, [9] 11~03308~! 12~01715~ 17~0970~ 18~05107~, 21~08492~ 23~01330~.'),
  (14526, 19, 39, 5, 'Behold, thou hast made my days as an handbreadth; and mine age is as nothing before thee: verily every man at his best state is altogether vanity. Selah.', '3~05414~ 5~03117~ [6] 8~02947~; 11~02465~ [12] 18~03605~ 19~0120~ 23~05324~ [24] 25~03605~ 26~01892~. 27~05542~.'),
  (19566, 24, 25, 23, 'Dedan, and Tema, and Buz, and all that are in the utmost corners,', '0~01719~, 2~08485~, 4~0938~, [7 8] 11~07112~ 12~06285~,'),
  (31067, 66, 20, 13, 'And the sea gave up the dead which were in it; and death and hell delivered up the dead which were in them: and they were judged every man according to their works.', '0~2532~ 2~2281~ 4~1325~ 6~3498~ 7~3588~ 9~1722~ 10~846~; 11~2532~ 12~2288~ 13~2532~ 14~86~ 16~1325~ 18~3498~ 19~3588~ 21~1722~ 22~846~: 23~2532~ 26~2919~ 28~1538~ 30~2596~ 31~846~ 32~2041~.'),
  (22975, 38, 7, 4, 'Then came the word of the LORD of hosts unto me, saying,', '3~01697~ 6~03068~ 8~06635~ 11~0559~,'),
  (21063, 26, 23, 47, 'And the company shall stone them with stones, and dispatch them with their swords; they shall slay their sons and their daughters, and burn up their houses with fire.', '2~06951~ 4~07275~ 7~068~, 9~01254~ 13~02719~; 16~02026~ 18~01121~ 21~01323~, 24~08313~ 26~01004~ 28~0784~.'),
  (3907, 4, 7, 52, 'One kid of the goats for a sin offering:', '0~0259~ 1~08163~ 4~05795~ 8~02403~:'),
  (14670, 19, 49, 13, 'This their way is their folly: yet their posterity approve their sayings. Selah.', '2~01870~ [3] 5~03689~: 8~0310~ 9~07521~ 11~06310~. 12~05542~.'),
  (13059, 18, 8, 21, 'Till he fill thy mouth with laughing, and thy lips with rejoicing.', '2~04390~ 4~06310~ 6~07814~, 9~08193~ 11~08643~.'),
  (20679, 26, 11, 15, 'Son of man, thy brethren, even thy brethren, the men of thy kindred, and all the house of Israel wholly, are they unto whom the inhabitants of Jerusalem have said, Get you far from the LORD: unto us is this land given in possession.', '0~01121~ 2~0120~, 4~0251~, [5] 7~0251~, 9~0582~ 12~01353~, 16~01004~ 18~03478~ [20] 25~03427~ 27~03389~ 29~0559~, 32~07368~ 35~03068~: 40~0776~ 41~05414~ 43~04181~.'),
  (24965, 42, 1, 60, 'And his mother answered and said, Not so; but he shall be called John.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~3384~ 3~611~ 5~2036~, 6~3780~ [7] 8~235~ 12~2564~ 13~2491~.'),
  (21252, 26, 31, 13, 'Upon his ruin shall all the fowls of the heaven remain, and all the beasts of the field shall be upon his branches:', '2~04658~ 6~05775~ 9~08064~ 10~07931~, 14~02416~ 17~07704~ 22~06288~:'),
  (3184, 3, 15, 11, 'And whomsoever he toucheth that hath the issue, and hath not rinsed his hands in water, he shall wash his clothes, and bathe himself in water, and be unclean until the even.', '3~05060~ 7~02100~, 11~07857~ 13~03027~ 15~04325~, 18~03526~ 20~0899~, 22~07364~ [23] 25~04325~, 28~02930~ 31~06153~.'),
  (16725, 20, 11, 28, 'He that trusteth in his riches shall fall: but the righteous shall flourish as a branch.', '&para; 2~0982~ 5~06239~ 7~05307~: 10~06662~ 12~06524~ 15~05929~.'),
  (9568, 12, 2, 9, 'And it came to pass, when they were gone over, that Elijah said unto Elisha, Ask what I shall do for thee, before I be taken away from thee. And Elisha said, I pray thee, let a double portion of thy spirit be upon me.', '&para; 9~05674~, 11~0452~ 12~0559~ 14~0477~, 15~07592~ 19~06213~ 26~03947~ 30~0477~ 31~0559~, 37~08147~ 38~06310~ 41~07307~'),
  (5357, 5, 16, 9, 'Seven weeks shalt thou number unto thee: begin to number the seven weeks from such time as thou beginnest to put the sickle to the corn.', '0~07651~ 1~07620~ 4~05608~ 7~02490~ 9~05608~ 11~07651~ 12~07620~ [14 16] 18~02490~ [19 20] 22~02770~ 25~07054~.'),
  (2, 1, 1, 2, 'And the earth was without form, and void; and darkness was upon the face of the deep. And the Spirit of God moved upon the face of the waters.', '2~0776~ 3~01961~ 5~08414~, 7~0922~; 9~02822~ [10] 13~06440~ 16~08415~. 19~07307~ 21~0430~ 22~07363~ 23~05921~ 25~06440~ 28~04325~.'),
  (15633, 19, 105, 18, 'Whose feet they hurt with fetters: he was laid in iron:', '1~07272~ 3~06031~ 5~03525~: 6~05315~ 8~0935~ 10~01270~:'),
  (17200, 20, 27, 22, 'Though thou shouldest bray a fool in a mortar among wheat with a pestle, yet will not his foolishness depart from him.', '&para; 3~03806~ 5~0191~ 8~04388~ 9~08432~ 10~07383~ 13~05940~, [14] 18~0200~ 19~05493~'),
  (29310, 49, 4, 22, 'That ye put off concerning the former conversation the old man, which is corrupt according to the deceitful lusts;', '1~5209~ 3~659~ 4~2596~ 6~4387~ 7~391~ 9~3820~ 10~444~, 11~3588~ 13~5351~ 14~2596~ 17~539~ 18~1939~;'),
  (22824, 36, 2, 10, 'This shall they have for their pride, because they have reproached and magnified themselves against the people of the LORD of hosts.', '6~01347~, 10~02778~ 12~01431~ [13] 16~05971~ 19~03068~ 21~06635~.'),
  (24581, 41, 9, 32, 'But they understood not that saying, and were afraid to ask him.', '0~1161~ 3~50~ 5~4487~, 6~2532~ 8~5399~ 10~1905~ 11~846~.'),
  (15858, 19, 116, 1, 'I love the LORD, because he hath heard my voice and my supplications.', '&para; 1~0157~ 3~03068~, 7~08085~ 9~06963~ [10] 12~08469~.'),
  (7376, 9, 7, 17, 'And his return was to Ramah; for there was his house; and there he judged Israel; and there he built an altar unto the LORD.', '2~08666~ [3] 5~07414~; [8] 10~01004~; 14~08199~ 15~03478~; 19~01129~ 21~04196~ 24~03068~.'),
  (15968, 19, 119, 61, 'The bands of the wicked have robbed me: but I have not forgotten thy law.', '&para; 1~02256~ 4~07563~ 6~05749~ [8] 12~07911~ 14~08451~.'),
  (1693, 2, 7, 3, 'And I will harden Pharaoh''s heart, and multiply my signs and my wonders in the land of Egypt.', '3~07185~ 4~06547~ 5~03820~, 7~07235~ 9~0226~ 12~04159~ 15~0776~ 17~04714~.'),
  (24128, 40, 26, 64, 'Jesus saith unto him, Thou hast said: nevertheless I say unto you, Hereafter shall ye see the Son of man sitting on the right hand of power, and coming in the clouds of heaven.', '0~2424~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~4771~ 6~2036~: 7~4133~ 9~3004~ 11~5213~, 12~575~ 13~737~ 15~3700~ 17~5207~ 19~444~ 20~2521~ 21~1537~ 24~1188~ 26~1411~, 27~2532~ 28~2064~ 29~1909~ 31~3507~ 33~3772~.'),
  (11963, 14, 34, 21, 'Go, inquire of the LORD for me, and for them that are left in Israel and in Judah, concerning the words of the book that is found: for great is the wrath of the LORD that is poured out upon us, because our fathers have not kept the word of the LORD, to do after all that is written in this book.', '0~03212~, 1~01875~ 4~03068~ 12~07604~ 14~03478~ 17~03063~, 20~01697~ 23~05612~ 26~04672~: 28~01419~ [29] 31~02534~ 34~03068~ 38~05413~ 43~01~ 46~08104~ 48~01697~ 51~03068~, 53~06213~ 58~03789~ 61~05612~.'),
  (28635, 46, 11, 19, 'For there must be also heresies among you, that they which are approved may be made manifest among you.', '0~1063~ 2~1163~ 3~1511~ 4~2532~ 5~139~ 6~1722~ 7~5213~, 8~2443~ 12~1384~ 15~1096~ 16~5318~ 17~1722~ 18~5213~.'),
  (5543, 5, 24, 12, 'And if the man be poor, thou shalt not sleep with his pledge:', '3~0376~ [4] 5~06041~, 9~07901~ 12~05667~:'),
  (23249, 40, 5, 5, 'Blessed are the meek: for they shall inherit the earth.', '0~3107~ [1] 3~4239~: 4~3754~ 5~846~ 7~2816~ 9~1093~.'),
  (5034, 5, 4, 24, 'For the LORD thy God is a consuming fire, even a jealous God.', '2~03068~ 4~0430~ [5] 7~0398~ 8~0784~, [9] 11~07067~ 12~0410~.'),
  (14978, 19, 69, 34, 'Let the heaven and earth praise him, the seas, and every thing that moveth therein.', '2~08064~ 4~0776~ 5~01984~ 8~03220~, 13~07430~'),
  (13990, 19, 5, 8, 'Lead me, O LORD, in thy righteousness because of mine enemies; make thy way straight before my face.', '0~05148~ 3~03068~, 6~06666~ 10~08324~; 13~01870~ 14~03474~ 17~06440~.'),
  (6397, 6, 21, 9, 'And they gave out of the tribe of the children of Judah, and out of the tribe of the children of Simeon, these cities which are here mentioned by name,', '&para; 2~05414~ 6~04294~ 9~01121~ 11~03063~, 16~04294~ 19~01121~ 21~08095~, 23~05892~ [26] 27~07121~ 29~08034~,'),
  (2455, 2, 32, 12, 'Wherefore should the Egyptians speak, and say, For mischief did he bring them out, to slay them in the mountains, and to consume them from the face of the earth? Turn from thy fierce wrath, and repent of this evil against thy people.', '3~04714~ 4~0559~, 6~0559~, 8~07451~ 11~03318~ 15~02026~ 19~02022~, 22~03615~ 26~06440~ 29~0127~? 30~07725~ 33~02740~ 34~0639~, 36~05162~ 39~07451~ 42~05971~.'),
  (2602, 2, 36, 31, 'And he made bars of shittim wood; five for the boards of the one side of the tabernacle,', '2~06213~ 3~01280~ 5~07848~ 6~06086~; 7~02568~ 10~07175~ 13~0259~ 14~06763~ 17~04908~,'),
  (16997, 20, 21, 4, 'An high look, and a proud heart, and the plowing of the wicked, is sin.', '&para; 1~07312~ 2~05869~, 5~07342~ 6~03820~, [7] 9~05215~ 12~07563~, [13] 14~02403~.'),
  (27518, 44, 16, 19, 'And when her masters saw that the hope of their gains was gone, they caught Paul and Silas, and drew them into the marketplace unto the rulers,', '0~1161~ 2~846~ 3~2962~ 4~1492~ 5~3754~ 7~1680~ 9~846~ 10~2039~ 12~1831~, 14~1949~ 15~3972~ 16~2532~ 17~4609~, 19~1670~ [20] 21~1519~ 23~58~ 24~1909~ 26~758~,'),
  (28383, 46, 1, 4, 'I thank my God always on your behalf, for the grace of God which is given you by Jesus Christ;', '1~2168~ 2~3450~ 3~2316~ 4~3842~ 5~4012~ 6~5216~ 7~4012~, 8~1909~ 10~5485~ 12~2316~ 13~3588~ 15~1325~ 16~5213~ 17~1722~ 18~2424~ 19~5547~;'),
  (5041, 5, 4, 31, '(For the LORD thy God is a merciful God;) he will not forsake thee, neither destroy thee, nor forget the covenant of thy fathers which he sware unto them.', '2~03068~ 4~0430~ [5] 7~07349~ 8~0410~;) 12~07503~ 15~07843~ 18~07911~ 20~01285~ 23~01~ 26~07650~'),
  (9880, 12, 13, 1, 'In the three and twentieth year of Joash the son of Ahaziah king of Judah Jehoahaz the son of Jehu began to reign over Israel in Samaria, and reigned seventeen years.', '&para; 2~08141~ 3~07969~ 4~06242~ 5~08141~ 7~03101~ 9~01121~ 11~0274~ 12~04428~ 14~03063~ 15~03059~ 17~01121~ 19~03058~ 22~04427~ 24~03478~ 26~08111~, [27 28] 29~06240~ 30~07651~* 31~08141~.'),
  (13560, 18, 29, 19, 'My root was spread out by the waters, and the dew lay all night upon my branch.', '1~08328~ [2] 4~06605~ 7~04325~, 10~02919~ 13~03885~ 16~07105~.'),
  (17425, 21, 5, 19, 'Every man also to whom God hath given riches and wealth, and hath given him power to eat thereof, and to take his portion, and to rejoice in his labour; this is the gift of God.', '1~0120~ 5~0430~ 7~05414~ 8~06239~ 10~05233~, 15~07980~ 17~0398~ 21~05375~ 23~02506~, 26~08055~ 29~05999~; 30~02090~ [31] 33~04991~ 35~0430~.'),
  (2045, 2, 19, 14, 'And Moses went down from the mount unto the people, and sanctified the people; and they washed their clothes.', '1~04872~ 3~03381~ 6~02022~ 9~05971~, 11~06942~ 13~05971~; 16~03526~ 18~08071~.'),
  (23125, 39, 2, 12, 'The LORD will cut off the man that doeth this, the master and the scholar, out of the tabernacles of Jacob, and him that offereth an offering unto the LORD of hosts.', '1~03068~ 4~03772~ 6~0376~ 8~06213~ 11~05782~ 14~06030~, 18~0168~ 20~03290~, 24~05066~ 26~04503~ 29~03068~ 31~06635~.'),
  (14848, 19, 62, 12, 'Also unto thee, O Lord, belongeth mercy: for thou renderest to every man according to his work.', '4~0136~, [5] 6~02617~: 9~07999~ 12~0376~ 16~04639~.'),
  (11046, 13, 24, 23, 'And the sons of Hebron; Jeriah the first, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third, Jekameam the fourth.', '2~01121~ [3 4] 5~03404~ [6 7] 8~0568~ 10~08145~, 11~03166~ 13~07992~, 14~03360~ 16~07243~.'),
  (28304, 45, 14, 8, 'For whether we live, we live unto the Lord; and whether we die, we die unto the Lord: whether we live therefore, or die, we are the Lord''s.', '0~1063~ 1~5037~ 2~1437~ 3~2198~, 5~2198~ 8~2962~; 10~5037~ 11~1437~ 12~599~, 14~599~ 17~2962~: 18~5037~ 19~1437~ 20~2198~ 21~3767~, 22~5037~ 23~1437~* 24~599~, 26~2070~ 28~2962~.'),
  (13185, 18, 13, 23, 'How many are mine iniquities and sins? make me to know my transgression and my sin.', '&para; [2] 4~05771~ 6~02403~? 10~03045~ 12~06588~ 15~02403~.'),
  (15153, 19, 78, 31, 'The wrath of God came upon them, and slew the fattest of them, and smote down the chosen men of Israel.', '1~0639~ 3~0430~ 4~05927~ 8~02026~ 10~04924~ 15~03766~ 17~0970~ [18] 20~03478~.'),
  (23128, 39, 2, 15, 'And did not he make one? Yet had he the residue of the spirit. And wherefore one? That he might seek a godly seed. Therefore take heed to your spirit, and let none deal treacherously against the wife of his youth.', '4~06213~ 5~0259~? 10~07605~ 13~07307~. 16~0259~? 20~01245~ 22~0430~ 23~02233~. 26~08104~ 29~07307~, 34~0898~ 37~0802~ 40~05271~.'),
  (11087, 13, 26, 2, 'And the sons of Meshelemiah were, Zechariah the firstborn, Jediael the second, Zebadiah the third, Jathniel the fourth,', '2~01121~ 4~04920~ [5] 6~02148~ 8~01060~, 9~03043~ 11~08145~, 12~02069~ 14~07992~, 15~03496~ 17~07243~,'),
  (346, 1, 14, 6, 'And the Horites in their mount Seir, unto Elparan, which is by the wilderness.', '2~02752~ 5~02042~ 6~08165~, 8~0364~, [10] 11~05921~ 13~04057~.'),
  (13568, 18, 30, 2, 'Yea, whereto might the strength of their hands profit me, in whom old age was perished?', '1~04100~ [2] 4~03581~ 7~03027~ [8] 13~03624~ 15~06~?'),
  (7102, 7, 20, 41, 'And when the men of Israel turned again, the men of Benjamin were amazed: for they saw that evil was come upon them.', '3~0376~ 5~03478~ 7~02015~, 9~0376~ 11~01144~ 13~0926~: 16~07200~ 18~07451~ 20~05060~'),
  (9488, 11, 21, 29, 'Seest thou how Ahab humbleth himself before me? because he humbleth himself before me, I will not bring the evil in his days: but in his son''s days will I bring the evil upon his house.', '0~07200~ 3~0256~ 4~03665~ 6~06440~ 8~03282~ 10~03665~ 12~06440~ 17~0935~ 19~07451~ 22~03117~: [23] 26~01121~ 27~03117~ 30~0935~ 32~07451~ 35~01004~.'),
  (29451, 50, 3, 14, 'I press toward the mark for the prize of the high calling of God in Christ Jesus.', '1~1377~ 2~2596~ 4~4649~ 5~1909~ 7~1017~ 10~507~ 11~2821~ 13~2316~ 14~1722~ 15~5547~ 16~2424~.'),
  (22063, 27, 11, 18, 'After this shall he turn his face unto the isles, and shall take many: but a prince for his own behalf shall cause the reproach offered by him to cease; without his own reproach he shall cause it to turn upon him.', '4~07760~ 6~06440~ 9~0339~, 12~03920~ 13~07227~: 16~07101~ 24~02781~ 29~07673~; 30~01115~ 33~02781~ [37] 39~07725~'),
  (21352, 26, 34, 30, 'Thus shall they know that I the LORD their God am with them, and that they, even the house of Israel, are my people, saith the Lord GOD.', '3~03045~ 7~03068~ 9~0430~ [10] [14] [16] 18~01004~ 20~03478~, [21] 23~05971~, 24~05002~ 26~0136~ 27~03069~.'),
  (29114, 48, 2, 17, 'But if, while we seek to be justified by Christ, we ourselves also are found sinners, is therefore Christ the minister of sin? God forbid.', '0~1161~ 1~1487~, 4~2212~ 7~1344~ 8~1722~ 9~5547~, 10~2147~ 11~846~ 12~2532~ 14~2147~ 15~268~, [16] 17~687~ 18~5547~ 20~1249~ 22~266~? 24~1096~ 25~3361~.*'),
  (16155, 19, 130, 6, 'My soul waiteth for the Lord more than they that watch for the morning: I say, more than they that watch for the morning.', '1~05315~ [2] 5~0136~ 10~08104~ 13~01242~: [14 17] 20~08104~ 23~01242~.');
