VALUES
  (6216, 6, 15, 7, 'And the border went up toward Debir from the valley of Achor, and so northward, looking toward Gilgal, that is before the going up to Adummim, which is on the south side of the river: and the border passed toward the waters of Enshemesh, and the goings out thereof were at Enrogel:', '2~01366~ 4~05927~ 6~01688~ 9~06010~ 11~05911~, 14~06828~, 15~06437~ 17~01537~, [19] 20~05227~ 23~04608~ 25~0131~, [27] 31~05045~ 34~05158~: 37~01366~ 38~05674~ 41~04325~ 43~05885~, 47~08444~ 51~05883~:'),
  (23874, 40, 21, 38, 'But when the husbandmen saw the son, they said among themselves, This is the heir; come, let us kill him, and let us seize on his inheritance.', '0~1161~ 3~1092~ 4~1492~ 6~5207~, 8~2036~ 9~1722~ 10~1438~, 11~3778~ 12~2076~ 14~2818~; 15~1205~, 18~615~ 19~846~, 20~2532~ 23~2722~ 25~846~ 26~2817~.'),
  (24474, 41, 7, 1, 'Then came together unto him the Pharisees, and certain of the scribes, which came from Jerusalem.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~4863~ 3~4314~ 4~846~ 6~5330~, 7~2532~ 8~5100~ 11~1122~, 13~2064~ 14~575~ 15~2414~.'),
  (20262, 24, 51, 41, 'How is Sheshach taken! and how is the praise of the whole earth surprised! how is Babylon become an astonishment among the nations!', '2~08347~ 3~03920~! 8~08416~ 12~0776~ 13~08610~! 16~0894~ 19~08047~ 22~01471~!'),
  (24562, 41, 9, 13, 'But I say unto you, That Elias is indeed come, and they have done unto him whatsoever they listed, as it is written of him.', '0~235~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 5~3754~ 6~2243~ 7~2064~ 8~2532~ 9~2064~, 10~2532~ 13~4160~ 15~846~ 16~3745~ 18~2309~, 19~2531~ 22~1125~ 23~1909~ 24~846~.'),
  (4288, 4, 18, 26, 'Thus speak unto the Levites, and say unto them, When ye take of the children of Israel the tithes which I have given you from them for your inheritance, then ye shall offer up an heave offering of it for the LORD, even a tenth part of the tithe.', '1~01696~ 4~03881~, 6~0559~ 11~03947~ 14~01121~ 16~03478~ 18~04643~ 22~05414~ 28~05159~, 32~07311~ 36~08641~ 41~03068~, [42] 44~04643~ [45] 48~04643~.'),
  (19288, 24, 13, 13, 'Then shalt thou say unto them, Thus saith the LORD, Behold, I will fill all the inhabitants of this land, even the kings that sit upon David''s throne, and the priests, and the prophets, and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, with drunkenness.', '3~0559~ 7~0559~ 9~03068~, 13~04390~ 16~03427~ 19~0776~, 22~04428~ 24~03427~ 26~01732~ 27~03678~, 30~03548~, 33~05030~, 37~03427~ 39~03389~, 41~07943~.'),
  (22340, 29, 2, 20, 'But I will remove far off from you the northern army, and will drive him into a land barren and desolate, with his face toward the east sea, and his hinder part toward the utmost sea, and his stink shall come up, and his ill savour shall come up, because he hath done great things.', '5~07368~ 9~06830~ [10] 13~05080~ 17~0776~ 18~06723~ 20~08077~, 23~06440~ 26~06931~ 27~03220~, 31~05490~ 34~0314~ 35~03220~, 38~0889~ 41~05927~, 45~06709~ 48~05927~, 52~06213~ 54~01431~.'),
  (14920, 19, 68, 11, 'The Lord gave the word: great was the company of those that published it.', '1~0136~ 2~05414~ 4~0562~: 5~07227~ [6] 8~06635~ 12~01319~ [13]'),
  (4385, 4, 22, 5, 'He sent messengers therefore unto Balaam the son of Beor to Pethor, which is by the river of the land of the children of his people, to call him, saying, Behold, there is a people come out from Egypt: behold, they cover the face of the earth, and they abide over against me:', '1~07971~ 2~04397~ 5~01109~ 7~01121~ 9~01160~ 11~06604~, [13] 16~05104~ 19~0776~ 22~01121~ 25~05971~, 27~07121~ 29~0559~, 34~05971~ 36~03318~ 38~04714~: 41~03680~ 43~05869~ 46~0776~, 49~03427~ 51~04136~'),
  (17817, 23, 8, 1, 'Moreover the LORD said unto me, Take thee a great roll, and write in it with a man''s pen concerning Mahershalalhashbaz.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 6~03947~ 9~01419~ 10~01549~, 12~03789~ 17~0582~ 18~02747~ 20~04122~.'),
  (18922, 23, 65, 16, 'That he who blesseth himself in the earth shall bless himself in the God of truth; and he that sweareth in the earth shall swear by the God of truth; because the former troubles are forgotten, and because they are hid from mine eyes.', '3~01288~ 7~0776~ 9~01288~ 13~0430~ 15~0543~; 19~07650~ 22~0776~ 24~07650~ 27~0430~ 29~0543~; 32~07223~ 33~06869~ 35~07911~, 40~05641~ 43~05869~.'),
  (28859, 47, 3, 2, 'Ye are our epistle written in our hearts, known and read of all men:', '0~5210~ 1~2075~ 2~2257~ 3~1992~ 4~1449~ 5~1722~ 6~2257~ 7~2588~, 8~1097~ 9~2532~ 10~314~ 11~5259~ 12~3956~ 13~444~:'),
  (18773, 23, 56, 11, 'Yea, they are greedy dogs which can never have enough, and they are shepherds that cannot understand: they all look to their own way, every one for his gain, from his quarter.', '[1 2] 3~05315~ 4~05794~* 5~03611~ [6] 7~03045~ 9~03045~ 10~07654~, [13] 14~07462~ [15] 17~0995~: 20~06437~ 24~01870~, 26~0376~ 29~01215~, 32~07097~.'),
  (5657, 5, 28, 40, 'Thou shalt have olive trees throughout all thy coasts, but thou shalt not anoint thyself with the oil; for thine olive shall cast his fruit.', '4~02132~ 8~01366~, 13~05480~ [14] 17~08081~; 20~02132~ 22~05394~ [23 24]'),
  (16442, 20, 1, 33, 'But whoso hearkeneth unto me shall dwell safely, and shall be quiet from fear of evil.', '2~08085~ 6~07931~ 7~0983~, 11~07599~ 13~06343~ 15~07451~.'),
  (6654, 7, 5, 24, 'Blessed above women shall Jael the wife of Heber the Kenite be, blessed shall she be above women in the tent.', '&para; 0~01288~ 2~0802~ 4~03278~ 6~0802~ 8~02268~ 10~07017~ 12~01288~ 17~0802~ 20~0168~.'),
  (11297, 14, 6, 7, 'Now it was in the heart of David my father to build an house for the name of the LORD God of Israel.', '5~03824~ 7~01732~ 9~01~ 11~01129~ 13~01004~ 16~08034~ 19~03068~ 20~0430~ 22~03478~.'),
  (17126, 20, 25, 4, 'Take away the dross from the silver, and there shall come forth a vessel for the finer.', '&para; 1~01898~ 3~05509~ 6~03701~, 11~03318~ 13~03627~ 16~06884~.'),
  (21188, 26, 28, 22, 'And say, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I am against thee, O Zidon; and I will be glorified in the midst of thee: and they shall know that I am the LORD, when I shall have executed judgments in her, and shall be sanctified in her.', '1~0559~, 3~0559~ 5~0136~ 6~03069~; [9] 13~06721~; 18~03513~ 21~08432~ 27~03045~ [30] 32~03068~, 37~06213~ 38~08201~ 44~06942~'),
  (11412, 14, 10, 8, 'But he forsook the counsel which the old men gave him, and took counsel with the young men that were brought up with him, that stood before him.', '2~05800~ 4~06098~ 8~02205~ 9~03289~ 13~03289~ 17~03206~ 21~01431~ 25~05975~ 26~06440~'),
  (25907, 42, 22, 29, 'And I appoint unto you a kingdom, as my Father hath appointed unto me;', '1~2504~ 2~1303~ 4~5213~ 6~932~, 7~2531~ 8~3450~ 9~3962~ 11~1303~ 13~3427~;'),
  (18050, 23, 21, 6, 'For thus hath the Lord said unto me, Go, set a watchman, let him declare what he seeth.', '4~0136~ 5~0559~ 8~03212~, 9~05975~ 11~06822~, 14~05046~ 17~07200~.'),
  (8150, 10, 5, 11, 'And Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, and cedar trees, and carpenters, and masons: and they built David an house.', '&para; 1~02438~ 2~04428~ 4~06865~ 5~07971~ 6~04397~ 8~01732~, 10~0730~ 11~06086~, 13~02796~, 15~068~ 16~07023~:* 19~01129~ 20~01732~ 22~01004~.'),
  (154, 1, 6, 16, 'A window shalt thou make to the ark, and in a cubit shalt thou finish it above; and the door of the ark shalt thou set in the side thereof; with lower, second, and third stories shalt thou make it.', '1~06672~ 4~06213~ 7~08392~, 11~0520~ 14~03615~ 16~04605~; 19~06607~ 22~08392~ 25~07760~ 29~06654~; [30] 31~08482~, 32~08145~, 34~07992~ [35] 38~06213~'),
  (16756, 20, 12, 28, 'In the way of righteousness is life; and in the pathway thereof there is no death.', '&para; 2~0734~ 4~06666~ [5] 6~02416~; [8] 10~01870~ [11 11~05410~ 13] 15~04194~.'),
  (8660, 10, 22, 50, 'Therefore I will give thanks unto thee, O LORD, among the heathen, and I will sing praises unto thy name.', '4~03034~ 8~03068~, 11~01471~, 16~02167~ 19~08034~.'),
  (30626, 62, 4, 7, 'Beloved, let us love one another: for love is of God; and every one that loveth is born of God, and knoweth God.', '&para; 0~27~, 3~25~ 5~240~: 6~3754~ 7~26~ 8~2076~ 9~1537~ 10~2316~; 11~2532~ 13~3956~ 15~25~ 17~1080~ 18~1537~ 19~2316~, 20~2532~ 21~1097~ 22~2316~.'),
  (24830, 41, 14, 65, 'And some began to spit on him, and to cover his face, and to buffet him, and to say unto him, Prophesy: and the servants did strike him with the palms of their hands.', '0~2532~ 1~5100~ 2~756~ 4~1716~ 6~846~, 7~2532~ 9~4028~ 10~846~ 11~4383~, 12~2532~ 14~2852~ 15~846~, 16~2532~ 18~3004~ 20~846~, 21~4395~: 22~2532~ 24~5257~ 26~906~ 27~846~ 33~4475~.'),
  (11219, 14, 1, 17, 'And they fetched up, and brought forth out of Egypt a chariot for six hundred shekels of silver, and an horse for an hundred and fifty: and so brought they out horses for all the kings of the Hittites, and for the kings of Syria, by their means.', '3~05927~, 6~03318~ 9~04714~ 11~04818~ 13~08337~ 14~03967~ [15] 17~03701~, 20~05483~ 23~03967~ 25~02572~: 30~03318~ [31] 35~04428~ 38~02850~, 42~04428~ 44~0758~, 47~03027~.'),
  (27409, 44, 13, 31, 'And he was seen many days of them which came up with him from Galilee to Jerusalem, who are his witnesses unto the people.', '1~3739~ 3~3700~ 4~4119~ 5~1909~* 6~2250~ 12~4872~ 13~846~ 14~575~ 15~1056~ 16~1519~ 17~2419~, 18~3748~ 19~1526~ 20~846~ 21~3144~ 22~4314~ 24~2992~.'),
  (28699, 46, 14, 5, 'I would that ye all spake with tongues, but rather that ye prophesied: for greater is he that prophesieth than he that speaketh with tongues, except he interpret, that the church may receive edifying.', '0~1161~ 1~2309~ 3~5209~ 4~3956~ 5~2980~ 7~1100~, 8~1161~ 9~3123~ 10~2443~ 12~4395~: 13~1063~ 14~3187~ [15] 18~4395~ 19~2228~ 22~2980~ 24~1100~, 25~1508~ 26~1622~ 27~1329~, 28~2443~ 30~1577~ 32~2983~ 33~3619~.'),
  (7371, 9, 7, 12, 'Then Samuel took a stone, and set it between Mizpeh and Shen, and called the name of it Ebenezer, saying, Hitherto hath the LORD helped us.', '1~08050~ 2~03947~ 3~0259~ 4~068~, 6~07760~ [7] 9~04709~ 11~08129~, 13~07121~ 15~08034~ 18~072~, 19~0559~, 23~03068~ 24~05826~'),
  (1921, 2, 14, 27, 'And Moses stretched forth his hand over the sea, and the sea returned to his strength when the morning appeared; and the Egyptians fled against it; and the LORD overthrew the Egyptians in the midst of the sea.', '1~04872~ 3~05186~ 5~03027~ 8~03220~, 11~03220~ 12~07725~ 15~0386~ 18~01242~ 19~06437~; 22~04714~ 23~05127~ 24~07125~ 28~03068~ 29~05287~ 31~04714~ 34~08432~ 37~03220~.'),
  (17494, 21, 9, 10, 'Whatsoever thy hand findeth to do, do it with thy might; for there is no work, nor device, nor knowledge, nor wisdom, in the grave, whither thou goest.', '2~03027~ 3~04672~ 5~06213~, 6~06213~ [7] 10~03581~; [12 13] 15~04639~, 17~02808~, 19~01847~, 21~02451~, 24~07585~, 27~01980~.'),
  (15554, 19, 102, 24, 'I said, O my God, take me not away in the midst of my days: thy years are throughout all generations.', '1~0559~, 4~0410~, 8~05927~ 11~02677~ 14~03117~: 16~08141~ [17] 19~01755~ 20~01755~.'),
  (29338, 49, 5, 18, 'And be not drunk with wine, wherein is excess; but be filled with the Spirit;', '0~2532~ 1~3182~ 2~3361~ 3~3182~ 5~3631~, 6~3739~ 7~1722~* 8~2076~ 9~810~; 10~235~ 12~4137~ 13~1722~ 15~4151~;'),
  (20553, 26, 4, 15, 'Then he said unto me, Lo, I have given thee cow''s dung for man''s dung, and thou shalt prepare thy bread therewith.', '2~0559~ 5~07200~, 8~05414~ 10~01241~ 11~06832~ 12~06832~* 14~0120~ 15~01561~, 19~06213~ 21~03899~'),
  (25516, 42, 12, 44, 'Of a truth I say unto you, that he will make him ruler over all that he hath.', '2~230~ 4~3004~ 6~5213~, 7~3754~ 11~846~ 12~2525~ 13~1909~ 14~3956~ 16~846~ 17~5224~.'),
  (13713, 18, 34, 21, 'For his eyes are upon the ways of man, and he seeth all his goings.', '2~05869~ [3] 6~01870~ 8~0376~, 11~07200~ 14~06806~.'),
  (6384, 6, 20, 5, 'And if the avenger of blood pursue after him, then they shall not deliver the slayer up into his hand; because he smote his neighbour unwittingly, and hated him not beforetime.', '3~01350~ 5~01818~ 6~07291~ 7~0310~ 13~05462~ 15~07523~ 19~03027~; 22~05221~ 24~07453~ 25~01847~ 26~01097~,* 28~08130~ 31~08032~ 32~08543~.*'),
  (25917, 42, 22, 39, 'And he came out, and went, as he was wont, to the mount of Olives; and his disciples also followed him.', '&para; 0~2532~ 3~1831~, 5~4198~, 6~2596~ 9~1485~, 10~1519~ 12~3735~ 14~1636~; 15~1161~ 16~846~ 17~3101~ 18~2532~ 19~190~ 20~846~.'),
  (11961, 14, 34, 19, 'And it came to pass, when the king had heard the words of the law, that he rent his clothes.', '7~04428~ 9~08085~ 11~01697~ 14~08451~, 17~07167~ 19~0899~.'),
  (26, 1, 1, 26, 'And God said, Let us make man in our image, after our likeness: and let them have dominion over the fish of the sea, and over the fowl of the air, and over the cattle, and over all the earth, and over every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth.', '&para; 1~0430~ 2~0559~, 5~06213~ 6~0120~ 9~06754~, 12~01823~: 17~07287~ 20~01710~ 23~03220~, 27~05775~ 30~08064~, 34~0929~, 39~0776~, 44~07431~ 46~07430~ 49~0776~.'),
  (18580, 23, 45, 10, 'Woe unto him that saith unto his father, What begettest thou? or to the woman, What hast thou brought forth?', '0~01945~ 4~0559~ [6] 7~01~, 9~03205~ 14~0802~, 19~02342~?'),
  (6413, 6, 21, 25, 'And out of the half tribe of Manasseh, Tanach with her suburbs, and Gathrimmon with her suburbs; two cities.', '4~04276~ 5~04294~ 7~04519~, 8~08590~ 11~04054~, 13~01667~ 16~04054~; 17~08147~ 18~05892~.'),
  (7597, 9, 15, 30, 'Then he said, I have sinned: yet honour me now, I pray thee, before the elders of my people, and before Israel, and turn again with me, that I may worship the LORD thy God.', '2~0559~, 5~02398~: [6] 7~03513~ 15~02205~ 18~05971~, 21~03478~, 24~07725~ 30~07812~ 32~03068~ 34~0430~.'),
  (2796, 3, 3, 13, 'And he shall lay his hand upon the head of it, and kill it before the tabernacle of the congregation: and the sons of Aaron shall sprinkle the blood thereof upon the altar round about.', '3~05564~ 5~03027~ 8~07218~ 12~07819~ 14~06440~ 16~0168~ 19~04150~: 22~01121~ 24~0175~ 26~02236~ 28~01818~ 32~04196~ 34~05439~.'),
  (10999, 13, 23, 8, 'The sons of Laadan; the chief was Jehiel, and Zetham, and Joel, three.', '1~01121~ 3~03936~; 5~07218~ [6] 7~03171~, 9~02241~, 11~03100~, 12~07969~.'),
  (13852, 18, 39, 9, 'Will the unicorn be willing to serve thee, or abide by thy crib?', '2~07214~ 4~014~ 6~05647~ 9~03885~ 12~018~?'),
  (28881, 47, 4, 6, 'For God, who commanded the light to shine out of darkness, hath shined in our hearts, to give the light of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.', '0~3754~ 1~2316~, 2~3588~ 3~2036~ 5~5457~ 7~2989~ 9~1537~ 10~4655~ 11~3739~,* 13~2989~ 14~1722~ 15~2257~ 16~2588~, 17~4314~ [18] 20~5462~ 23~1108~ 26~1391~ 28~2316~ 29~1722~ 31~4383~ 33~2424~ 34~5547~.'),
  (1962, 2, 16, 10, 'And it came to pass, as Aaron spake unto the whole congregation of the children of Israel, that they looked toward the wilderness, and, behold, the glory of the LORD appeared in the cloud.', '6~0175~ 7~01696~ 11~05712~ 14~01121~ 16~03478~, 19~06437~ 22~04057~, 26~03519~ 29~03068~ 30~07200~ 33~06051~.'),
  (6834, 7, 10, 16, 'And they put away the strange gods from among them, and served the LORD: and his soul was grieved for the misery of Israel.', '3~05493~ 5~05236~ 6~0430~ 8~07130~ 11~05647~ 13~03068~: 16~05315~ 18~07114~ 21~05999~ 23~03478~.'),
  (16553, 20, 6, 4, 'Give not sleep to thine eyes, nor slumber to thine eyelids.', '0~05414~ 2~08142~ 5~05869~, 7~08572~ 10~06079~.'),
  (2232, 2, 25, 32, 'And six branches shall come out of the sides of it; three branches of the candlestick out of the one side, and three branches of the candlestick out of the other side:', '1~08337~ 2~07070~ 4~03318~ 8~06654~ 11~07969~ 12~07070~ 15~04501~ 19~0259~ 20~06654~, 22~07969~ 23~07070~ 26~04501~ 30~08145~ 31~06654~:'),
  (15193, 19, 78, 71, 'From following the ewes great with young he brought him to feed Jacob his people, and Israel his inheritance.', '1~0310~ 6~05763~ 8~0935~ 11~07462~ 12~03290~ 14~05971~, 16~03478~ 18~05159~.'),
  (27778, 44, 23, 28, 'And when I would have known the cause wherefore they accused him, I brought him forth into their council:', '0~1161~ 1~1014~ 3~1014~ 5~1097~ 7~156~ 8~3739~ 9~1223~ 10~1458~ 11~846~, 13~2609~ 14~846~ 15~2609~ 16~1519~ 17~846~ 18~4892~:'),
  (21672, 26, 46, 8, 'And when the prince shall enter, he shall go in by the way of the porch of that gate, and he shall go forth by the way thereof.', '3~05387~ 5~0935~, 8~0935~ 12~01870~ 15~0197~ [17] 18~08179~, 23~03318~ 26~01870~'),
  (18102, 23, 23, 16, 'Take an harp, go about the city, thou harlot that hast been forgotten; make sweet melody, sing many songs, that thou mayest be remembered.', '0~03947~ 2~03658~, 4~05437~ 6~05892~, 8~02181~ 12~07911~; 14~03190~ 15~05059~, 17~07235~ 18~07892~, 23~02142~.'),
  (11707, 14, 24, 21, 'And they conspired against him, and stoned him with stones at the commandment of the king in the court of the house of the LORD.', '2~07194~ 6~07275~ 9~068~ 12~04687~ 15~04428~ 18~02691~ 21~01004~ 24~03068~.'),
  (1099, 1, 37, 11, 'And his brethren envied him; but his father observed the saying.', '2~0251~ 3~07065~ 7~01~ 8~08104~ 10~01697~.'),
  (5712, 5, 29, 27, 'And the anger of the LORD was kindled against this land, to bring upon it all the curses that are written in this book:', '2~0639~ 5~03068~ 7~02734~ 10~0776~, 12~0935~ 17~07045~ 20~03789~ 23~05612~:'),
  (21538, 26, 41, 3, 'Then went he inward, and measured the post of the door, two cubits; and the door, six cubits; and the breadth of the door, seven cubits.', '1~0935~ 3~06441~, 5~04058~ 7~0352~ 10~06607~, 11~08147~ 12~0520~; 15~06607~, 16~08337~ 17~0520~; 20~07341~ 23~06607~, 24~07651~ 25~0520~.'),
  (26742, 43, 16, 1, 'These things have I spoken unto you, that ye should not be offended.', '&para; 1~5023~ 4~2980~ 6~5213~, 7~3363~ 9~4624~ 10~3363~ 12~4624~.'),
  (24729, 41, 13, 1, 'And as he went out of the temple, one of his disciples saith unto him, Master, see what manner of stones and what buildings are here!', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~846~ 3~1607~ 5~1537~ 7~2411~, 8~1520~ 10~846~ 11~3101~ 12~3004~ 14~846~, 15~1320~, 16~2396~ 18~4217~ 20~3037~ 21~2532~ 22~4217~ 23~3619~ [24 25]'),
  (24388, 41, 5, 14, 'And they that fed the swine fled, and told it in the city, and in the country. And they went out to see what it was that was done.', '0~1161~ 3~1006~ 5~5519~ 6~5343~, 7~2532~ 8~312~ [9] 10~1519~ 12~4172~, 13~2532~ 14~1519~ 16~68~. 17~2532~ 20~1831~ 22~1492~ 23~5101~ 25~2076~ 28~1096~.'),
  (21033, 26, 23, 17, 'And the Babylonians came to her into the bed of love, and they defiled her with their whoredom, and she was polluted with them, and her mind was alienated from them.', '2~0894~ 3~01121~* 4~0935~ 9~04904~ 11~01730~, 14~02930~ 18~08457~, 22~02930~ 27~05315~ 29~03363~'),
  (26768, 43, 16, 27, 'For the Father himself loveth you, because ye have loved me, and have believed that I came out from God.', '0~1063~ 2~3962~ 3~846~ 4~5368~ 5~5209~, 6~3754~ 7~5210~ 9~5368~ 10~1691~, 11~2532~ 13~4100~ 14~3754~ 15~1473~ 17~1831~ 18~3844~ 19~2316~.'),
  (25660, 42, 16, 26, 'And beside all this, between us and you there is a great gulf fixed: so that they which would pass from hence to you cannot; neither can they pass to us, that would come from thence.', '0~2532~ 1~1909~ 2~3956~ 3~5125~, 4~3342~ 5~2257~ 6~2532~ 7~5216~ 9~4741~ 11~3173~ 12~5490~ 13~4741~: 15~3704~ 18~2309~ 19~1224~ 21~1782~ 22~4314~ 23~5209~ 24~1410~ 25~3361~;* 26~3366~ 29~1276~ 30~4314~ 31~2248~, [33 34] 36~1564~.'),
  (22445, 30, 5, 13, 'Therefore the prudent shall keep silence in that time; for it is an evil time.', '2~07919~ 5~01826~ 8~06256~; [11] 13~07451~ 14~06256~.'),
  (7184, 8, 3, 5, 'And she said unto her, All that thou sayest unto me I will do.', '2~0559~ 8~0559~ 13~06213~.'),
  (4929, 5, 1, 31, 'And in the wilderness, where thou hast seen how that the LORD thy God bare thee, as a man doth bear his son, in all the way that ye went, until ye came into this place.', '3~04057~, 7~07200~ 11~03068~ 13~0430~ 14~05375~ 18~0376~ 20~05375~ 22~01121~, 26~01870~ 29~01980~, 32~0935~ 35~04725~.'),
  (16460, 20, 2, 18, 'For her house inclineth unto death, and her paths unto the dead.', '2~01004~ 3~07743~ 5~04194~, 8~04570~ 11~07496~.'),
  (11272, 14, 4, 18, 'Thus Solomon made all these vessels in great abundance: for the weight of the brass could not be found out.', '1~08010~ 2~06213~ 5~03627~ 7~03966~ 8~07230~: 11~04948~ 14~05178~ 19~02713~.'),
  (2115, 2, 21, 33, 'And if a man shall open a pit, or if a man shall dig a pit, and not cover it, and an ox or an ass fall therein;', '3~0376~ 5~06605~ 7~0953~, 11~0376~ 13~03738~ 15~0953~, 18~03680~ 22~07794~ 25~02543~ 26~05307~'),
  (16303, 19, 143, 1, 'A Psalm of David. Hear my prayer, O LORD, give ear to my supplications: in thy faithfulness answer me, and in thy righteousness.', '&para; [0 1~04210~ 3] 3~01732~ 4~08085~ 6~08605~, 8~03068~, 10~0238~ 13~08469~: 16~0530~ 17~06030~ [19] 22~06666~.'),
  (21944, 27, 7, 2, 'Daniel spake and said, I saw in my vision by night, and, behold, the four winds of the heaven strove upon the great sea.', '0~01841~ 1~06032~ 3~0560~, 5~02370~ 6~01934~* 9~02376~ 10~05974~ 11~03916~, 13~0718~, 15~0703~ 16~07308~ 19~08065~ 20~01519~ 23~07229~ 24~03221~.'),
  (26995, 44, 2, 30, 'Therefore being a prophet, and knowing that God had sworn with an oath to him, that of the fruit of his loins, according to the flesh, he would raise up Christ to sit on his throne;', '0~3767~ 1~5225~ 3~4396~, 4~2532~ 5~1492~ 6~3754~ 7~2316~ 9~3660~ 12~3727~ 14~846~, 16~1537~ 18~2590~ 20~846~ 21~3751~, 23~2596~ 25~4561~, 29~450~ 30~5547~ 32~2523~ 33~1909~ 34~846~ 35~2362~;'),
  (17675, 23, 1, 12, 'When ye come to appear before me, who hath required this at your hand, to tread my courts?', '2~0935~ 4~07200~ 5~06440~ 9~01245~ 13~03027~, 15~07429~ 17~02691~?'),
  (23760, 40, 18, 23, 'Therefore is the kingdom of heaven likened unto a certain king, which would take account of his servants.', '0~5124~ 1~1223~ 3~932~ 5~3772~ 6~3666~ 9~444~ 10~935~, 11~3739~ 12~2309~ 13~4868~ 14~3056~ 15~3326~ 16~846~ 17~1401~.'),
  (12721, 17, 1, 10, 'On the seventh day, when the heart of the king was merry with wine, he commanded Mehuman, Biztha, Harbona, Bigtha, and Abagtha, Zethar, and Carcas, the seven chamberlains that served in the presence of Ahasuerus the king,', '&para; 2~07637~ 3~03117~, 6~03820~ 9~04428~ 11~02896~ 13~03196~, 15~0559~ 16~04104~, 17~0968~, 18~02726~, 19~0903~, 21~05~, 22~02242~, 24~03752~, 26~07651~ 27~05631~ 29~08334~ 32~06440~ 34~0325~ 36~04428~,'),
  (3535, 3, 26, 6, 'And I will give peace in the land, and ye shall lie down, and none shall make you afraid: and I will rid evil beasts out of the land, neither shall the sword go through your land.', '3~05414~ 4~07965~ 7~0776~, 12~07901~, [17] 18~02729~: 22~07673~ 23~07451~ 24~02416~ 28~0776~, 32~02719~ 33~05674~ 36~0776~.'),
  (417, 1, 17, 16, 'And I will bless her, and give thee a son also of her: yea, I will bless her, and she shall be a mother of nations; kings of people shall be of her.', '3~01288~ 6~05414~ 9~01121~ 16~01288~ [22 23] 25~01471~; 26~04428~ 28~05971~'),
  (25158, 42, 5, 39, 'No man also having drunk old wine straightway desireth new: for he saith, The old is better.', '1~3762~ 2~2532~ 4~4095~ 5~3820~ [6] 7~2112~ 8~2309~ 9~3501~: 10~1063~ 12~3004~, 14~3820~ 15~2076~ 16~5543~.'),
  (16176, 19, 132, 16, 'I will also clothe her priests with salvation: and her saints shall shout aloud for joy.', '3~03847~ 5~03548~ 7~03468~: 10~02623~ 13~07442~ 15~07444~.'),
  (9280, 11, 15, 23, 'The rest of all the acts of Asa, and all his might, and all that he did, and the cities which he built, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? Nevertheless in the time of his old age he was diseased in his feet.', '1~03499~ 5~01697~ 7~0609~, 11~01369~, 16~06213~, 19~05892~ 22~01129~, [23] 26~03789~ 29~05612~ 32~03117~ 33~01697~ 35~04428~ 37~03063~? 41~06256~ 45~02209~ 48~02470~ 51~07272~.'),
  (10990, 13, 22, 18, 'Is not the LORD your God with you? and hath he not given you rest on every side? for he hath given the inhabitants of the land into mine hand; and the land is subdued before the LORD, and before his people.', '[0] 3~03068~ 5~0430~ [11] 14~05117~ 17~05439~? 21~05414~ 23~03427~ 26~0776~ 29~03027~; 32~0776~ 34~03533~ 35~06440~ 37~03068~, 39~06440~ 41~05971~.'),
  (12007, 14, 36, 5, 'Jehoiakim was twenty and five years old when he began to reign, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem: and he did that which was evil in the sight of the LORD his God.', '0~03079~ [1] 2~06242~ 4~02568~ 5~08141~ 6~01121~ 11~04427~, 14~04427~ 15~06240~ 16~0259~* 17~08141~ 19~03389~: 22~06213~ [23 25] 26~07451~ 29~05869~ 32~03068~ 34~0430~.'),
  (21347, 26, 34, 25, 'And I will make with them a covenant of peace, and will cause the evil beasts to cease out of the land: and they shall dwell safely in the wilderness, and sleep in the woods.', '3~03772~ 7~01285~ 9~07965~, 14~07451~ 15~02416~ 17~07673~ 21~0776~: 25~03427~ 26~0983~ 29~04057~, 31~03462~ 34~03293~ 35~03264~.*'),
  (6293, 6, 17, 11, 'And Manasseh had in Issachar and in Asher Bethshean and her towns, and Ibleam and her towns, and the inhabitants of Dor and her towns, and the inhabitants of Endor and her towns, and the inhabitants of Taanach and her towns, and the inhabitants of Megiddo and her towns, even three countries.', '1~04519~ 4~03485~ 7~0836~ 8~01052~ 11~01323~, 13~02991~ 16~01323~, 19~03427~ 21~01756~ 24~01323~, 27~03427~ 29~05874~ 32~01323~, 35~03427~ 37~08590~ 40~01323~, 43~03427~ 45~04023~ 48~01323~, [49] 50~07969~ 51~05316~.'),
  (14622, 19, 45, 16, 'Instead of thy fathers shall be thy children, whom thou mayest make princes in all the earth.', '3~01~ 7~01121~, 11~07896~ 12~08269~ 16~0776~.'),
  (5727, 5, 30, 13, 'Neither is it beyond the sea, that thou shouldest say, Who shall go over the sea for us, and bring it unto us, that we may hear it, and do it?', '[1] 3~05676~ 5~03220~, 9~0559~, 12~05674~ 13~05676~ 15~03220~ 19~03947~ 26~08085~ 29~06213~'),
  (28220, 45, 10, 16, 'But they have not all obeyed the gospel. For Esaias saith, Lord, who hath believed our report?', '0~235~ 2~5219~ 3~3756~ 4~3956~ 5~5219~ 7~2098~. 8~1063~ 9~2268~ 10~3004~, 11~2962~, 12~5101~ 14~4100~ 15~2257~ 16~189~?'),
  (12182, 15, 6, 22, 'And kept the feast of unleavened bread seven days with joy: for the LORD had made them joyful, and turned the heart of the king of Assyria unto them, to strengthen their hands in the work of the house of God, the God of Israel.', '1~06213~ 3~02282~ 6~04682~ 7~07651~ 8~03117~ 10~08057~: 13~03068~ 17~08055~, 19~05437~ 21~03820~ 24~04428~ 26~0804~ 30~02388~ 32~03027~ 35~04399~ 38~01004~ 40~0430~, 42~0430~ 44~03478~.'),
  (4902, 5, 1, 4, 'After he had slain Sihon the king of the Amorites, which dwelt in Heshbon, and Og the king of Bashan, which dwelt at Astaroth in Edrei:', '0~0310~ 3~05221~ 4~05511~ 6~04428~ 9~0567~, 11~03427~ 13~02809~, 15~05747~ 17~04428~ 19~01316~, 21~03427~ 23~06252~ 25~0154~:'),
  (8575, 10, 20, 13, 'When he was removed out of the highway, all the people went on after Joab, to pursue after Sheba the son of Bichri.', '3~03014~ 7~04546~, 10~0376~ 12~05674~ 13~0310~ 14~03097~, 16~07291~ 17~0310~ 18~07652~ 20~01121~ 22~01075~.'),
  (27449, 44, 14, 19, 'And there came thither certain Jews from Antioch and Iconium, who persuaded the people, and, having stoned Paul, drew him out of the city, supposing he had been dead.', '&para; 0~1161~ 3~1904~ [4] 5~2453~ 6~575~ 7~490~ 8~2532~ 9~2430~, 10~2532~ 11~3982~ 13~3793~, 14~2532~, 16~3034~ 17~3972~, 18~4951~ [19] 21~1854~ 23~4172~, 24~3543~ 25~846~ 28~2348~.'),
  (18760, 23, 55, 11, 'So shall my word be that goeth forth out of my mouth: it shall not return unto me void, but it shall accomplish that which I please, and it shall prosper in the thing whereto I sent it.', '3~01697~ 7~03318~ 11~06310~: 15~07725~ 18~07387~, 22~06213~ 26~02654~, 30~06743~ [31 33] 36~07971~'),
  (3410, 3, 23, 3, 'Six days shall work be done: but the seventh day is the sabbath of rest, an holy convocation; ye shall do no work therein: it is the sabbath of the LORD in all your dwellings.', '0~08337~ 1~03117~ 3~04399~ 5~06213~: 8~07637~ 9~03117~ [10] 12~07676~ 14~07677~, 16~06944~ 17~04744~; 20~06213~ 22~04399~ [23] [25] 27~07676~ 30~03068~ 34~04186~.'),
  (24921, 42, 1, 17, 'And he shall go before him in the spirit and power of Elias, to turn the hearts of the fathers to the children, and the disobedient to the wisdom of the just; to make ready a people prepared for the Lord.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 3~4281~ 4~1799~ 5~846~ 6~1722~ 8~4151~ 9~2532~ 10~1411~ 12~2243~, 14~1994~ 16~2588~ 19~3962~ 20~1909~ 22~5043~, 23~2532~ 25~545~ 26~1722~ 28~5428~ 31~1342~; 34~2090~ 36~2992~ 37~2680~ 40~2962~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (15317, 19, 87, 7, 'As well the singers as the players on instruments shall be there: all my springs are in thee.', '3~07891~ 6~02490~ [9 11] 14~04599~ [15]'),
  (273, 1, 11, 6, 'And the LORD said, Behold, the people is one, and they have all one language; and this they begin to do: and now nothing will be restrained from them, which they have imagined to do.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~, 6~05971~ [7] 8~0259~, 13~0259~ 14~08193~; 18~02490~ 20~06213~: 23~03605~ 24~03808~ 26~01219~ 32~02161~ 34~06213~.'),
  (19704, 24, 31, 4, 'Again I will build thee, and thou shalt be built, O virgin of Israel: thou shalt again be adorned with thy tabrets, and shalt go forth in the dances of them that make merry.', '3~01129~ 9~01129~, 11~01330~ 13~03478~: 18~05710~ 21~08596~, 25~03318~ 28~04234~ 33~07832~.'),
  (26095, 43, 1, 36, 'And looking upon Jesus as he walked, he saith, Behold the Lamb of God!', '0~2532~ 2~1689~ 3~2424~ 6~4043~, 8~3004~, 9~2396~ 11~286~ 13~2316~!'),
  (20374, 25, 3, 11, 'He hath turned aside my ways, and pulled me in pieces: he hath made me desolate.', '3~05493~ 5~01870~, 10~06582~: 13~07760~ 15~08074~.'),
  (16186, 19, 135, 2, 'Ye that stand in the house of the LORD, in the courts of the house of our God,', '2~05975~ 5~01004~ 8~03068~, 11~02691~ 14~01004~ 17~0430~,'),
  (26287, 43, 6, 15, 'When Jesus therefore perceived that they would come and take him by force, to make him a king, he departed again into a mountain himself alone.', '&para; 1~2424~ 2~3767~ 3~1097~ 4~3754~ 6~3195~ 7~2064~ 8~2532~ 9~726~ 10~846~ 12~726~, 13~2443~ 14~4160~ 15~846~ 17~935~, 19~402~ 20~3825~ 21~1519~ 23~3735~ 24~846~ 25~3441~.'),
  (10915, 13, 18, 17, 'And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the Cherethites and the Pelethites; and the sons of David were chief about the king.', '1~01141~ 3~01121~ 5~03077~ [6] 9~03774~ 12~06432~; 15~01121~ 17~01732~ [18] 19~07223~ 20~03027~ 22~04428~.'),
  (15506, 19, 98, 7, 'Let the sea roar, and the fulness thereof; the world, and they that dwell therein.', '2~03220~ 3~07481~, 6~04393~ 9~08398~, 13~03427~'),
  (20037, 24, 44, 18, 'But since we left off to burn incense to the queen of heaven, and to pour out drink offerings unto her, we have wanted all things, and have been consumed by the sword and by the famine.', '4~02308~ 7~06999~ 10~04446~ 12~08064~, 16~05258~ 18~05262~ 23~02637~ [25] 29~08552~ 32~02719~ 36~07458~.'),
  (29874, 55, 3, 5, 'Having a form of godliness, but denying the power thereof: from such turn away.', '0~2192~ 2~3446~ 4~2150~, 5~1161~ 6~720~ 8~1411~ 9~846~: 10~2532~ 11~5128~ 13~665~.'),
  (21929, 27, 6, 15, 'Then these men assembled unto the king, and said unto the king, Know, O king, that the law of the Medes and Persians is, That no decree nor statute which the king establisheth may be changed.', '0~0116~ 1~0479~ 2~01400~ 3~07284~ 4~05922~ 6~04430~, 8~0560~ 11~04430~, 12~03046~, 14~04430~, 17~01882~ 20~04076~ 22~06540~ [23] 25~03606~ 26~0633~ 28~07010~ 31~04430~ 32~06966~ 35~08133~.'),
  (18069, 23, 22, 8, 'And he discovered the covering of Judah, and thou didst look in that day to the armour of the house of the forest.', '&para; 2~01540~ 4~04539~ 6~03063~, 10~05027~ 13~03117~ 16~05402~ 19~01004~ 22~03293~.'),
  (11373, 14, 9, 1, 'And when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon, she came to prove Solomon with hard questions at Jerusalem, with a very great company, and camels that bare spices, and gold in abundance, and precious stones: and when she was come to Solomon, she communed with him of all that was in her heart.', '&para; 3~04436~ 5~07614~ 6~08085~ 9~08088~ 11~08010~, 13~0935~ 15~05254~ 16~08010~ 19~02420~ 21~03389~, 24~03966~ 25~03515~ 26~02428~, 28~01581~ 30~05375~ 31~01314~, 33~02091~ 35~07230~, 37~03368~ 38~068~: 43~0935~ 45~08010~, 47~01696~ 56~03824~.'),
  (20185, 24, 50, 10, 'And Chaldea shall be a spoil: all that spoil her shall be satisfied, saith the LORD.', '1~03778~ 5~07998~: 8~07997~ 12~07646~, 13~05002~ 15~03068~.'),
  (26457, 43, 9, 2, 'And his disciples asked him, saying, Master, who did sin, this man, or his parents, that he was born blind?', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~3101~ 3~2065~ 4~846~, 5~3004~, 6~4461~, 7~5101~ 9~264~, 11~3778~, 12~2228~ 13~846~ 14~1118~, 15~2443~ 18~1080~ 19~5185~?'),
  (25296, 42, 8, 39, 'Return to thine own house, and shew how great things God hath done unto thee. And he went his way, and published throughout the whole city how great things Jesus had done unto him.', '0~5290~ 1~1519~ 3~4675~ 4~3624~, 5~2532~ 6~1334~ 9~3745~ 10~2316~ 12~4160~ 14~4671~. 15~2532~ 19~565~, 21~2784~ 22~2596~ 24~3650~ 25~4172~ 28~3745~ 29~2424~ 31~4160~ 33~846~.'),
  (21850, 27, 4, 4, 'I Nebuchadnezzar was at rest in mine house, and flourishing in my palace:', '&para; 0~0576~ 1~05020~ 2~01934~ 4~07954~ 7~01005~, 9~07487~ 12~01965~:'),
  (10730, 13, 12, 2, 'They were armed with bows, and could use both the right hand and the left in hurling stones and shooting arrows out of a bow, even of Saul''s brethren of Benjamin.', '[0 1] 2~05401~ 4~07198~, 11~03231~ 14~08041~ [16] 17~068~ [19] 20~02671~ 24~07198~, [25] 27~07586~ 28~0251~ 30~01144~.'),
  (6430, 6, 21, 42, 'These cities were every one with their suburbs round about them: thus were all these cities.', '1~05892~ 4~05892~ 5~05892~ 7~04054~ 9~05439~ [12] 15~05892~.'),
  (16819, 20, 15, 3, 'The eyes of the LORD are in every place, beholding the evil and the good.', '&para; 1~05869~ 4~03068~ [5] 8~04725~, 9~06822~ 11~07451~ 14~02896~.'),
  (18000, 23, 17, 8, 'And he shall not look to the altars, the work of his hands, neither shall respect that which his fingers have made, either the groves, or the images.', '4~08159~ 7~04196~, 9~04639~ 12~03027~, 15~07200~ [16] 19~0676~ 21~06213~, 24~0842~, 27~02553~.'),
  (15605, 19, 104, 25, 'So is this great and wide sea, wherein are things creeping innumerable, both small and great beasts.', '[0 1] 3~01419~ 5~03027~ 6~07342~* 7~03220~, [9] 11~07431~ 12~04557~, 14~06996~ 16~01419~ 17~02416~.'),
  (26848, 43, 19, 8, 'When Pilate therefore heard that saying, he was the more afraid;', '0~3753~ 1~4091~ 2~3767~ 3~191~ 4~5126~ 5~3056~, 7~5399~ 9~3123~ 10~5399~;'),
  (649, 1, 24, 54, 'And they did eat and drink, he and the men that were with him, and tarried all night; and they rose up in the morning, and he said, Send me away unto my master.', '&para; 3~0398~ 5~08354~, 9~0582~ [11] 17~03885~; 21~06965~ 24~01242~, 27~0559~, 30~07971~ 33~0113~.'),
  (24409, 41, 5, 35, 'While he yet spake, there came from the ruler of the synagogue''s house certain which said, Thy daughter is dead: why troublest thou the Master any further?', '&para; 0~2089~ 1~846~ 2~2089~ 3~2980~, 5~2064~ 6~575~ 11~752~ [12 13] 15~3004~ 16~3754~,* 17~4675~ 18~2364~ 20~599~: 21~5101~ 23~4660~ 25~1320~ 27~2089~?'),
  (6848, 7, 11, 12, 'And Jephthah sent messengers unto the king of the children of Ammon, saying, What hast thou to do with me, that thou art come against me to fight in my land?', '&para; 1~03316~ 2~07971~ 3~04397~ 6~04428~ 9~01121~ 11~05983~, 12~0559~, 23~0935~ 27~03898~ 30~0776~?'),
  (26114, 43, 2, 4, 'Jesus saith unto her, Woman, what have I to do with thee? mine hour is not yet come.', '0~2424~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~1135~, 5~5101~ 7~1698~ 10~2532~ 11~4671~? 12~3450~ 13~5610~ 14~2240~ 16~3768~ 17~2240~.'),
  (31023, 66, 18, 14, 'And the fruits that thy soul lusted after are departed from thee, and all things which were dainty and goodly are departed from thee, and thou shalt find them no more at all.', '0~2532~ 2~3703~ 4~4675~ 5~5590~ 7~1939~ 9~565~ 10~575~ 11~4675~, 12~2532~ 14~3956~ 15~3588~ 17~3045~ 18~2532~ 19~2986~ 21~565~ 22~575~ 23~4675~, 24~2532~ 27~2147~ 28~846~ 30~3765~ 32~3364~.'),
  (20598, 26, 7, 12, 'The time is come, the day draweth near: let not the buyer rejoice, nor the seller mourn: for wrath is upon all the multitude thereof.', '1~06256~ 3~0935~, 5~03117~ 7~05060~: 11~07069~ 12~08055~, 15~04376~ 16~056~: 18~02740~ [19] 23~01995~'),
  (13566, 18, 29, 25, 'I chose out their way, and sat chief, and dwelt as a king in the army, as one that comforteth the mourners.', '1~0977~ 4~01870~, 6~03427~ 7~07218~, 9~07931~ 12~04428~ 15~01416~, [18] 19~05162~ 21~057~.'),
  (27882, 44, 27, 11, 'Nevertheless the centurion believed the master and the owner of the ship, more than those things which were spoken by Paul.', '0~1161~ 2~1543~ 3~3982~ 5~2942~ 6~2532~ 11~3490~, 12~3123~ 13~2228~ 18~3004~ 19~5259~ 20~3972~.'),
  (28021, 45, 3, 14, 'Whose mouth is full of cursing and bitterness:', '0~3739~ 1~4750~ [2] 3~1073~ 5~685~ 6~2532~ 7~4088~:'),
  (11987, 14, 35, 12, 'And they removed the burnt offerings, that they might give according to the divisions of the families of the people, to offer unto the LORD, as it is written in the book of Moses. And so did they with the oxen.', '2~05493~ 5~05930~, 9~05414~ 13~04653~ 16~01004~ 17~01~ 19~05971~ 20~01121~,* 22~07126~ 25~03068~, [27 28] 29~03789~ 32~05612~ 34~04872~. [37 38] 41~01241~.'),
  (17681, 23, 1, 18, 'Come now, and let us reason together, saith the LORD: though your sins be as scarlet, they shall be as white as snow; though they be red like crimson, they shall be as wool.', '1~03212~, 6~03198~, 7~0559~ 9~03068~: 12~02399~ 15~08144~, 20~03835~ 22~07950~; 26~0119~ 28~08438~, 33~06785~.'),
  (23076, 38, 13, 8, 'And it shall come to pass, that in all the land, saith the LORD, two parts therein shall be cut off and die; but the third shall be left therein.', '[6] 10~0776~, 11~05002~ 13~03068~, 14~08147~ 15~06310~ 20~03772~ [21] 22~01478~; 25~07992~ 28~03498~'),
  (11052, 13, 24, 29, 'Concerning Kish: the son of Kish was Jerahmeel.', '1~07027~: 3~01121~ 5~07027~ [6] 7~03396~.'),
  (2726, 2, 40, 14, 'And thou shalt bring his sons, and clothe them with coats:', '3~07126~ 5~01121~, 7~03847~ 10~03801~:'),
  (17530, 21, 11, 8, 'But if a man live many years, and rejoice in them all; yet let him remember the days of darkness; for they shall be many. All that cometh is vanity.', '3~0120~ 4~02421~ 5~07235~ 6~08141~, [7] 8~08055~ 15~02142~ 17~03117~ 19~02822~; 24~07235~. 27~0935~ [28] 29~01892~.'),
  (8906, 11, 6, 2, 'And the house which king Solomon built for the LORD, the length thereof was threescore cubits, and the breadth thereof twenty cubits, and the height thereof thirty cubits.', '2~01004~ 4~04428~ 5~08010~ 6~01129~ 9~03068~, 11~0753~ [13] 14~08346~ 15~0520~, 18~07341~ 20~06242~ [21] 24~06967~ 26~07970~ 27~0520~.'),
  (30659, 62, 5, 19, 'And we know that we are of God, and the whole world lieth in wickedness.', '[0] 2~1492~ 3~3754~ 5~2070~ 6~1537~ 7~2316~, 8~2532~ 10~3650~ 11~2889~ 12~2749~ 13~1722~ 14~4190~.'),
  (14206, 19, 21, 6, 'For thou hast made him most blessed for ever: thou hast made him exceeding glad with thy countenance.', '3~07896~ 6~01293~ 8~05703~: 11~02302~ 14~08057~ 17~06440~.'),
  (2761, 3, 1, 11, 'And he shall kill it on the side of the altar northward before the LORD: and the priests, Aaron''s sons, shall sprinkle his blood round about upon the altar.', '3~07819~ 7~03409~ 10~04196~ 11~06828~ 12~06440~ 14~03068~: 17~03548~, 18~0175~ 19~01121~, 21~02236~ 23~01818~ 25~05439~ 28~04196~.'),
  (9666, 12, 5, 11, 'But Naaman was wroth, and went away, and said, Behold, I thought, He will surely come out to me, and stand, and call on the name of the LORD his God, and strike his hand over the place, and recover the leper.', '1~05283~ 3~07107~, 6~03212~, 8~0559~, 11~0559~, 14~03318~ 16~03318~ 20~05975~, 22~07121~ 25~08034~ 28~03068~ 30~0430~, 32~05130~ 34~03027~ 37~04725~, 39~0622~ 41~06879~.'),
  (9865, 12, 12, 7, 'Then king Jehoash called for Jehoiada the priest, and the other priests, and said unto them, Why repair ye not the breaches of the house? now therefore receive no more money of your acquaintance, but deliver it for the breaches of the house.', '1~04428~ 2~03060~ 3~07121~ 5~03077~ 7~03548~, [10] 11~03548~, 13~0559~ 17~02388~ 21~0919~ 24~01004~? 27~03947~ [29] 30~03701~ 33~04378~, 35~05414~ 39~0919~ 42~01004~.'),
  (24694, 41, 12, 10, 'And have ye not read this scripture; The stone which the builders rejected is become the head of the corner:', '2~314~ 3~3761~ 4~314~ 5~5026~ 6~1124~; 8~3037~ 9~3739~ 11~3618~ 12~593~ 13~1096~ 14~3778~* 15~1519~ 17~2776~ 20~1137~:'),
  (3248, 3, 17, 8, 'And thou shalt say unto them, Whatsoever man there be of the house of Israel, or of the strangers which sojourn among you, that offereth a burnt offering or sacrifice,', '3~0559~ 7~0376~ [8 9] 12~01004~ 14~03478~, 18~01616~ 20~01481~ 21~08432~ 24~05927~ 27~05930~ 29~02077~,'),
  (12754, 17, 2, 21, 'In those days, while Mordecai sat in the king''s gate, two of the king''s chamberlains, Bigthan and Teresh, of those which kept the door, were wroth, and sought to lay hand on the king Ahasuerus.', '&para; 2~03117~, 4~04782~ 5~03427~ 8~04428~ 9~08179~, 10~08147~ 13~04428~ 14~05631~, 15~0904~ 17~08657~, 21~08104~ 23~05592~, 25~07107~, 27~01245~ 29~07971~ 30~03027~ 33~04428~ 34~0325~.'),
  (19972, 24, 41, 6, 'And Ishmael the son of Nethaniah went forth from Mizpah to meet them, weeping all along as he went: and it came to pass, as he met them, he said unto them, Come to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam.', '1~03458~ 3~01121~ 5~05418~ 7~03318~ 9~04709~ 11~07125~ 13~01058~ 15~01980~ 18~01980~: 26~06298~ 29~0559~ 32~0935~ 34~01436~ 36~01121~ 38~0296~.'),
  (9115, 11, 10, 28, 'And Solomon had horses brought out of Egypt, and linen yarn: the king''s merchants received the linen yarn at a price.', '1~08010~ 3~05483~ 4~04161~ 7~04714~, 10~04723~: 12~04428~ 13~05503~ 14~03947~ 17~04723~ 20~04242~.'),
  (4409, 4, 22, 29, 'And Balaam said unto the ass, Because thou hast mocked me: I would there were a sword in mine hand, for now would I kill thee.', '1~01109~ 2~0559~ 5~0860~, 9~05953~ 12~03863~ 14~03426~ 16~02719~ 19~03027~, 24~02026~'),
  (18831, 23, 60, 1, 'Arise, shine; for thy light is come, and the glory of the LORD is risen upon thee.', '&para; 0~06965~, 1~0215~; 4~0216~ 6~0935~, 9~03519~ 12~03068~ 14~02224~'),
  (13317, 18, 19, 11, 'He hath also kindled his wrath against me, and he counteth me unto him as one of his enemies.', '3~02734~ 5~0639~ 10~02803~ [15 16] 18~06862~.'),
  (10034, 12, 18, 2, 'Twenty and five years old was he when he began to reign; and he reigned twenty and nine years in Jerusalem. His mother''s name also was Abi, the daughter of Zachariah.', '0~06242~ 2~02568~ 3~08141~ 4~01121~ 11~04427~; 14~04427~ 15~06242~ 17~08672~ 18~08141~ 20~03389~. 22~0517~ 23~08034~ [25] 26~021~, 28~01323~ 30~02148~.'),
  (8353, 10, 13, 29, 'And the servants of Absalom did unto Amnon as Absalom had commanded. Then all the king''s sons arose, and every man gat him up upon his mule, and fled.', '2~05288~ 4~053~ 5~06213~ 7~0550~ 9~053~ 11~06680~. 15~04428~ 16~01121~ 17~06965~, 20~0376~ 23~07392~ 26~06505~, 28~05127~.'),
  (5265, 5, 12, 19, 'Take heed to thyself that thou forsake not the Levite as long as thou livest upon the earth.', '1~08104~ 6~05800~ 9~03881~ 14~03117~ 17~0127~.'),
  (24960, 42, 1, 55, 'As he spake to our fathers, to Abraham, and to his seed for ever.', '0~2531~ 2~2980~ 3~4314~ 4~2257~ 5~3962~, 7~11~, 8~2532~ 10~846~ 11~4690~ 12~1519~ 13~165~.'),
  (14668, 19, 49, 11, 'Their inward thought is, that their houses shall continue for ever, and their dwelling places to all generations; they call their lands after their own names.', '1~07130~ [3 4] 6~01004~ [7 8] 10~05769~, [11] 13~04908~ 16~01755~ 17~01755~; 19~07121~ [20] 21~0127~ 25~08034~.'),
  (21942, 27, 6, 28, 'So this Daniel prospered in the reign of Darius, and in the reign of Cyrus the Persian.', '1~01836~ 2~01841~ 3~06744~ 6~04437~ 8~01868~, 12~04437~ 14~03567~ 16~06543~.'),
  (680, 1, 25, 18, 'And they dwelt from Havilah unto Shur, that is before Egypt, as thou goest toward Assyria: and he died in the presence of all his brethren.', '2~07931~ 4~02341~ 6~07793~, [8] 9~06440~ 10~04714~, 13~0935~ 15~0804~: [16] 18~05307~ 21~06440~ 25~0251~.'),
  (5693, 5, 29, 8, 'And we took their land, and gave it for an inheritance unto the Reubenites, and to the Gadites, and to the half tribe of Manasseh.', '2~03947~ 4~0776~, 6~05414~ 10~05159~ 13~07206~, 17~01425~, 21~02677~ 22~07626~ 24~04520~.'),
  (29195, 48, 5, 17, 'For the flesh lusteth against the Spirit, and the Spirit against the flesh: and these are contrary the one to the other: so that ye cannot do the things that ye would.', '0~1063~ 2~4561~ 3~1937~ 4~2596~ 6~4151~, 7~1161~ 9~4151~ 10~2596~ 12~4561~: 13~1161~ 14~5023~ 16~480~ 21~240~: 23~2443~ 25~3363~ 26~4160~ 28~5023~ 29~302~ 30~3739~ 31~2309~.'),
  (8213, 10, 7, 26, 'And let thy name be magnified for ever, saying, The LORD of hosts is the God over Israel: and let the house of thy servant David be established before thee.', '3~08034~ 5~01431~ 6~05704~ 7~05769~, 8~0559~, 10~03068~ 12~06635~ [13] 15~0430~ 17~03478~: 21~01004~ 24~05650~ 25~01732~ 27~03559~ 28~06440~'),
  (7946, 9, 27, 9, 'And David smote the land, and left neither man nor woman alive, and took away the sheep, and the oxen, and the asses, and the camels, and the apparel, and returned, and came to Achish.', '1~01732~ 2~05221~ 4~0776~, 8~0376~ 10~0802~ 11~02421~, 14~03947~ 16~06629~, 19~01241~, 22~02543~, 25~01581~, 28~0899~, 30~07725~, 32~0935~ 34~0397~.'),
  (16203, 19, 135, 19, 'Bless the LORD, O house of Israel: bless the LORD, O house of Aaron:', '0~01288~ 2~03068~, 4~01004~ 6~03478~: 7~01288~ 9~03068~, 11~01004~ 13~0175~:'),
  (7125, 7, 21, 16, 'Then the elders of the congregation said, How shall we do for wives for them that remain, seeing the women are destroyed out of Benjamin?', '&para; 2~02205~ 5~05712~ 6~0559~, 10~06213~ 12~0802~ 16~03498~, 19~0802~ 21~08045~ 24~01144~?'),
  (21685, 26, 46, 21, 'Then he brought me forth into the utter court, and caused me to pass by the four corners of the court; and, behold, in every corner of the court there was a court.', '4~03318~ 7~02435~ 8~02691~, 14~05674~ 16~0702~ 17~04740~ 20~02691~; 24~04740~ 25~04740~ 28~02691~ [29 29~02691~ 30] 32~02691~.'),
  (11840, 14, 30, 4, 'And the thing pleased the king and all the congregation.', '2~01697~ 3~03474~ 4~05869~* 6~04428~ 10~06951~.'),
  (12035, 15, 1, 10, 'Thirty basins of gold, silver basins of a second sort four hundred and ten, and other vessels a thousand.', '0~07970~ 1~03713~ 3~02091~, 4~03701~ 5~03713~ 8~04932~ [9] 10~0702~ 11~03967~ 13~06235~, [14] 15~0312~ 16~03627~ 18~0505~.'),
  (4760, 4, 32, 36, 'And Bethnimrah, and Bethharan, fenced cities: and folds for sheep.', '1~01039~, 3~01028~, 4~04013~ 5~05892~: 7~01448~ 9~06629~.'),
  (5867, 6, 1, 10, 'Then Joshua commanded the officers of the people, saying,', '&para; 1~03091~ 2~06680~ 4~07860~ 7~05971~, 8~0559~,'),
  (27327, 44, 11, 4, 'But Peter rehearsed the matter from the beginning, and expounded it by order unto them, saying,', '0~1161~ 1~4074~ [3 4] 7~756~, 9~1620~ [10] 12~2517~ 14~846~, 15~3004~,'),
  (11064, 13, 25, 10, 'The third to Zaccur, he, his sons, and his brethren, were twelve:', '1~07992~ 3~02139~, [4] 6~01121~, 9~0251~, [10] 11~06240~ 12~08147~:*'),
  (11390, 14, 9, 18, 'And there were six steps to the throne, with a footstool of gold, which were fastened to the throne, and stays on each side of the sitting place, and two lions standing by the stays:', '[1 2] 3~08337~ 4~04609~ 7~03678~, 10~03534~ 12~02091~, [13 14] 15~0270~ 18~03678~, 20~03027~ 26~03427~ 27~04725~, 29~08147~ 30~0738~ 31~05975~ 32~0681~ 34~03027~:'),
  (25858, 42, 21, 18, 'But there shall not an hair of your head perish.', '0~2532~ 3~3364~ 5~2359~ 6~1537~ 7~5216~ 8~2776~ 9~622~.'),
  (8666, 10, 23, 5, 'Although my house be not so with God; yet he hath made with me an everlasting covenant, ordered in all things, and sure: for this is all my salvation, and all my desire, although he make it not to grow.', '2~01004~ [3] 7~0410~; 11~07760~ 15~05769~ 16~01285~, 17~06186~ [20] 22~08104~: [24 25] 28~03468~, [31] 32~02656~, [36] 39~06779~.'),
  (763, 1, 27, 32, 'And Isaac his father said unto him, Who art thou? And he said, I am thy son, thy firstborn Esau.', '1~03327~ 3~01~ 4~0559~ [8] 12~0559~, [14] 16~01121~, 18~01060~ 19~06215~.'),
  (22042, 27, 10, 18, 'Then there came again and touched me one like the appearance of a man, and he strengthened me,', '3~03254~ 5~05060~ [7] 10~04758~ 13~0120~, 16~02388~'),
  (13130, 18, 11, 13, 'If thou prepare thine heart, and stretch out thine hands toward him;', '&para; 2~03559~ 4~03820~, 6~06566~ 9~03709~'),
  (27503, 44, 16, 4, 'And as they went through the cities, they delivered them the decrees for to keep, that were ordained of the apostles and elders which were at Jerusalem.', '0~1161~ 1~5613~ 4~1279~ 6~4172~, 8~3860~ 9~846~ 11~1378~ 14~5442~, 17~2919~ 18~5259~ 20~652~ 21~2532~ 22~4245~ 23~3588~ 25~1722~ 26~2419~.'),
  (16129, 19, 126, 5, 'They that sow in tears shall reap in joy.', '2~02232~ 4~01832~ 6~07114~ 8~07440~.'),
  (23216, 40, 3, 14, 'But John forbad him, saying, I have need to be baptized of thee, and comest thou to me?', '0~1161~ 1~2491~ 2~1254~ 4~3004~, 5~1473~ 6~2192~ 7~5532~ 10~907~ 11~5259~ 12~4675~, 13~2532~ 14~2064~ 15~4771~ 16~4314~ 17~3165~?'),
  (16321, 19, 144, 7, 'Send thine hand from above; rid me, and deliver me out of great waters, from the hand of strange children;', '0~07971~ 2~03027~ 4~04791~; 5~06475~ 8~05337~ 12~07227~ 13~04325~, 16~03027~ 18~05236~ 19~01121~;'),
  (22521, 31, 1, 2, 'Behold, I have made thee small among the heathen: thou art greatly despised.', '3~05414~ 5~06996~ 8~01471~: 11~03966~ 12~0959~.'),
  (8194, 10, 7, 7, 'In all the places wherein I have walked with all the children of Israel spake I a word with any of the tribes of Israel, whom I commanded to feed my people Israel, saying, Why build ye not me an house of cedar?', '[2 3] 7~01980~ 11~01121~ 13~03478~ 14~01696~ 17~01697~ 19~0259~ 22~07626~ 24~03478~, 27~06680~ 29~07462~ 31~05971~ 32~03478~, 33~0559~, 35~01129~ 40~01004~ 42~0730~?'),
  (10663, 13, 9, 40, 'And the son of Jonathan was Meribbaal: and Meribbaal begat Micah.', '2~01121~ 4~03083~ [5] 6~04807~: 8~04810~ 9~03205~ 10~04318~.'),
  (16895, 20, 17, 13, 'Whoso rewardeth evil for good, evil shall not depart from his house.', '&para; 1~07725~ 2~07451~ 4~02896~, 5~07451~ 8~04185~ 11~01004~.'),
  (26560, 43, 11, 22, 'But I know, that even now, whatsoever thou wilt ask of God, God will give it thee.', '0~235~ 2~1492~, 4~2532~ 5~3568~, 6~302~ 7~3754~* 8~3745~ 10~154~ 12~2316~, 13~2316~ 15~1325~ [16] 17~4671~.'),
  (2664, 2, 38, 26, 'A bekah for every man, that is, half a shekel, after the shekel of the sanctuary, for every one that went to be numbered, from twenty years old and upward, for six hundred thousand and three thousand and five hundred and fifty men.', '1~01235~ 4~01538~, [5 6] 7~04276~ 9~08255~, 12~08255~ 15~06944~, 20~05674~ 23~06485~, 25~06242~ 26~08141~ 27~01121~ 29~04605~, 31~08337~ 32~03967~ 33~0505~ 35~07969~ 36~0505~ 38~02568~ 39~03967~ 41~02572~ [42]'),
  (22691, 33, 7, 18, 'Who is a God like unto thee, that pardoneth iniquity, and passeth by the transgression of the remnant of his heritage? he retaineth not his anger for ever, because he delighteth in mercy.', '[1] 3~0410~ 8~05375~ 9~05771~, 12~05674~ 14~06588~ 17~07611~ 20~05159~? 22~02388~ 25~0639~ 27~05703~, 30~02654~ [31] 32~02617~.'),
  (17177, 20, 26, 27, 'Whoso diggeth a pit shall fall therein: and he that rolleth a stone, it will return upon him.', '&para; 1~03738~ 3~07845~ 5~05307~ 10~01556~ 12~068~, 15~07725~'),
  (20326, 25, 1, 7, 'Jerusalem remembered in the days of her affliction and of her miseries all her pleasant things that she had in the days of old, when her people fell into the hand of the enemy, and none did help her: the adversaries saw her, and did mock at her sabbaths.', '0~03389~ 1~02142~ 4~03117~ 7~06040~ 11~04788~ 15~04262~ 21~03117~ 23~06924~, 26~05971~ 27~05307~ 30~03027~ 33~06862~, 37~05826~ 40~06862~ 41~07200~ [43] 45~07832~ 48~04868~.'),
  (7707, 9, 18, 24, 'And the servants of Saul told him, saying, On this manner spake David.', '2~05650~ 4~07586~ 5~05046~ 7~0559~, 10~01697~ 11~01696~ 12~01732~.'),
  (16302, 19, 142, 7, 'Bring my soul out of prison, that I may praise thy name: the righteous shall compass me about; for thou shalt deal bountifully with me.', '0~03318~ 2~05315~ 5~04525~, 9~03034~ 11~08034~: 13~06662~ 17~03803~; 22~01580~'),
  (23592, 40, 13, 43, 'Then shall the righteous shine forth as the sun in the kingdom of their Father. Who hath ears to hear, let him hear.', '0~5119~ 3~1342~ 5~1584~ 6~5613~ 8~2246~ 9~1722~ 11~932~ 13~846~ 14~3962~. 15~3588~ 16~2192~ 17~3775~ 19~191~, 22~191~.'),
  (18044, 23, 20, 6, 'And the inhabitant of this isle shall say in that day, Behold, such is our expectation, whither we flee for help to be delivered from the king of Assyria: and how shall we escape?', '2~03427~ 5~0339~ 7~0559~ 10~03117~, 12~03541~ [13] 15~04007~, 18~05127~ 20~05833~ 23~05337~ 24~06440~ 26~04428~ 28~0804~: 33~04422~?'),
  (16693, 20, 10, 28, 'The hope of the righteous shall be gladness: but the expectation of the wicked shall perish.', '1~08431~ 4~06662~ [5 6] 7~08057~: 10~08615~ 13~07563~ 15~06~.'),
  (4021, 4, 10, 28, 'Thus were the journeyings of the children of Israel according to their armies, when they set forward.', '[1] 1~0428~ 3~04550~ 6~01121~ 8~03478~ 12~06635~, 16~05265~.'),
  (23205, 40, 3, 3, 'For this is he that was spoken of by the prophet Esaias, saying, The voice of one crying in the wilderness, Prepare ye the way of the Lord, make his paths straight.', '0~1063~ 1~3778~ 3~2076~ 6~4483~ 8~5259~ 10~4396~ 11~2268~, 12~3004~, 14~5456~ 17~994~ 18~1722~ 20~2048~, 22~2090~ 24~3598~ 27~2962~, 28~4160~ 29~846~ 30~5147~ 31~2117~.'),
  (13887, 18, 40, 14, 'Then will I also confess unto thee that thine own right hand can save thee.', '4~03034~ 11~03225~ 13~03467~');
