  (11365, 14, 8, 11, 'And Solomon brought up the daughter of Pharaoh out of the city of David unto the house that he had built for her: for he said, My wife shall not dwell in the house of David king of Israel, because the places are holy, whereunto the ark of the LORD hath come.', '1~08010~ 3~05927~ 5~01323~ 7~06547~ 11~05892~ 13~01732~ 16~01004~ 20~01129~ 25~0559~, 27~0802~ 30~03427~ 33~01004~ 35~01732~ 36~04428~ 38~03478~, [40 42] 43~06944~, 46~0727~ 49~03068~ 51~0935~.'),
  (22432, 30, 4, 13, 'For, lo, he that formeth the mountains, and createth the wind, and declareth unto man what is his thought, that maketh the morning darkness, and treadeth upon the high places of the earth, The LORD, The God of hosts, is his name.', '4~03335~ 6~02022~, 8~01254~ 10~07307~, 12~05046~ 14~0120~ [16] 18~07808~, 20~06213~ 22~07837~ 23~05890~, 25~01869~ 29~01116~ 32~0776~, 34~03068~, 36~0430~ 38~06635~, [39] 41~08034~.'),
  (14431, 19, 35, 12, 'They rewarded me evil for good to the spoiling of my soul.', '1~07999~ 3~07451~ 5~02896~ [6] 8~07908~ 11~05315~.'),
  (21897, 27, 5, 14, 'I have even heard of thee, that the spirit of the gods is in thee, and that light and understanding and excellent wisdom is found in thee.', '3~08086~ 8~07308~ 11~0426~ [12] 14~05922~, [16] 17~05094~ 19~07924~ 21~03493~ 22~02452~ 24~07912~'),
  (5935, 6, 4, 19, 'And the people came up out of Jordan on the tenth day of the first month, and encamped in Gilgal, in the east border of Jericho.', '2~05971~ 4~05927~ 7~03383~ 10~06218~ [11] 14~07223~ 15~02320~, 17~02583~ 19~01537~, 22~04217~ 23~07097~ 25~03405~.'),
  (2335, 2, 28, 37, 'And thou shalt put it on a blue lace, that it may be upon the mitre; upon the forefront of the mitre it shall be.', '3~07760~ 7~08504~ 8~06616~, 15~04701~; 18~04136~ 19~06440~ 21~04701~'),
  (8789, 11, 2, 11, 'And the days that David reigned over Israel were forty years: seven years reigned he in Hebron, and thirty and three years reigned he in Jerusalem.', '2~03117~ 4~01732~ 5~04427~ 7~03478~ [8] 9~0705~ 10~08141~: 11~07651~ 12~08141~ 13~04427~ 16~02275~, 18~07970~ 20~07969~ 21~08141~ 22~04427~ 25~03389~.'),
  (7293, 9, 3, 10, 'And the LORD came, and stood, and called as at other times, Samuel, Samuel. Then Samuel answered, Speak; for thy servant heareth.', '2~03068~ 3~0935~, 5~03320~, 7~07121~ 11~06471~, 12~08050~, 13~08050~. 15~08050~ 16~0559~, 17~01696~; 20~05650~ 21~08085~.'),
  (14434, 19, 35, 15, 'But in mine adversity they rejoiced, and gathered themselves together: yea, the abjects gathered themselves together against me, and I knew it not; they did tear me, and ceased not:', '3~06761~ 5~08055~, 9~0622~: [10] 12~05222~ 15~0622~ 20~03045~ [21] 25~07167~ [26] 28~01826~'),
  (30091, 58, 7, 11, 'If therefore perfection were by the Levitical priesthood, (for under it the people received the law,) what further need was there that another priest should rise after the order of Melchisedec, and not be called after the order of Aaron?', '&para; 0~3303~ 1~1487~* 2~3767~ 3~5050~ 4~2258~ 5~1223~ 7~3020~ 8~2420~, 9~1063~* 11~1909~ 12~846~ 14~2992~ 17~3549~,) 18~5101~ 19~2089~ 20~5532~ [21 22] 24~2087~ 25~2409~ 27~450~ 28~2596~ 30~5010~ 32~3198~, 33~2532~ 34~3756~ 36~3004~ 37~2596~ 39~5010~ 41~2~?'),
  (12875, 17, 9, 32, 'And the decree of Esther confirmed these matters of Purim; and it was written in the book.', '2~03982~ 4~0635~ 5~06965~ 7~01697~ 9~06332~; 13~03789~ 16~05612~.'),
  (19380, 24, 17, 14, 'Heal me, O LORD, and I shall be healed; save me, and I shall be saved: for thou art my praise.', '0~07495~ 3~03068~, 8~07495~; 9~03467~ 15~03467~: [18] 20~08416~.'),
  (26573, 43, 11, 35, 'Jesus wept.', '0~2424~ 1~1145~.'),
  (13915, 18, 41, 18, 'By his neesings a light doth shine, and his eyes are like the eyelids of the morning.', '2~05846~ 4~0216~ 6~01984~, 9~05869~ [10] 13~06079~ 16~07837~.'),
  (26547, 43, 11, 9, 'Jesus answered, Are there not twelve hours in the day? If any man walk in the day, he stumbleth not, because he seeth the light of this world.', '0~2424~ 1~611~, 3~1526~ 4~3780~ 5~1427~ 6~5610~ 9~2250~? 10~1437~ 12~5100~ 13~4043~ 14~1722~ 16~2250~, 18~4350~ 19~3756~, 20~3754~ 22~991~ 24~5457~ 26~5127~ 27~2889~.'),
  (19185, 24, 9, 1, 'Oh that my head were waters, and mine eyes a fountain of tears, that I might weep day and night for the slain of the daughter of my people!', '&para; 1~05414~ 3~07218~ 5~04325~, 8~05869~ 10~04726~ 12~01832~, 16~01058~ 17~03119~ 19~03915~ 22~02491~ 25~01323~ 28~05971~!'),
  (4486, 4, 25, 10, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (6903, 7, 13, 12, 'And Manoah said, Now let thy words come to pass. How shall we order the child, and how shall we do unto him?', '1~04495~ 2~0559~, 6~01697~ 9~0935~. 13~04941~ 15~05288~, [17] 20~04639~'),
  (22367, 29, 3, 15, 'The sun and the moon shall be darkened, and the stars shall withdraw their shining.', '1~08121~ 4~03394~ 7~06937~, 10~03556~ 12~0622~ 14~05051~.'),
  (25940, 42, 22, 62, 'And Peter went out, and wept bitterly.', '0~2532~ 1~4074~ 2~1831~ 3~1854~, 5~2799~ 6~4090~.'),
  (16286, 19, 141, 1, 'A Psalm of David. LORD, I cry unto thee: make haste unto me; give ear unto my voice, when I cry unto thee.', '&para; [0 1~04210~ 3] 3~01732~ 4~03068~, 6~07121~ 10~02363~ 14~0238~ 17~06963~, 20~07121~'),
  (19641, 24, 28, 14, 'For thus saith the LORD of hosts, the God of Israel; I have put a yoke of iron upon the neck of all these nations, that they may serve Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon; and they shall serve him: and I have given him the beasts of the field also.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~ 6~06635~, 8~0430~ 10~03478~; 13~05414~ 15~05923~ 17~01270~ 20~06677~ 24~01471~, 28~05647~ 29~05019~ 30~04428~ 32~0894~; 36~05647~ 41~05414~ 44~02416~ 47~07704~'),
  (9134, 11, 11, 18, 'And they arose out of Midian, and came to Paran: and they took men with them out of Paran, and they came to Egypt, unto Pharaoh king of Egypt; which gave him an house, and appointed him victuals, and gave him land.', '2~06965~ 5~04080~, 7~0935~ 9~06290~: 12~03947~ 13~0582~ 18~06290~, 21~0935~ 23~04714~, 25~06547~ 26~04428~ 28~04714~; 30~05414~ 33~01004~, 35~0559~ 37~03899~, 39~05414~ 41~0776~.'),
  (21977, 27, 8, 7, 'And I saw him come close unto the ram, and he was moved with choler against him, and smote the ram, and brake his two horns: and there was no power in the ram to stand before him, but he cast him down to the ground, and stamped upon him: and there was none that could deliver the ram out of his hand.', '2~07200~ 4~05060~ 6~0681~ 8~0352~, 14~04843~ 18~05221~ 20~0352~, 22~07665~ 24~08147~ 25~07161~: 30~03581~ 33~0352~ 35~05975~ 36~06440~ 42~07993~ 45~0776~, 47~07429~ 56~05337~ 58~0352~ 62~03027~.'),
  (27271, 44, 9, 39, 'Then Peter arose and went with them. When he was come, they brought him into the upper chamber: and all the widows stood by him weeping, and shewing the coats and garments which Dorcas made, while she was with them.', '0~1161~ 1~4074~ 2~450~ 5~4905~ 6~846~. 8~3739~ 10~3854~, 13~321~ 14~1519~ 17~5253~: 18~2532~ 19~3956~ 21~5503~ 23~3936~ 24~846~ 25~2799~, 26~2532~ 27~1925~ 29~5509~ 30~2532~ 31~2440~ 32~3745~ 33~1393~ 34~4160~, 37~5607~ 38~3326~ 39~846~.'),
  (24329, 41, 3, 31, 'There came then his brethren and his mother, and, standing without, sent unto him, calling him.', '&para; 1~2064~ 2~3767~ 3~846~ 4~80~ 5~2532~ 7~3384~, 8~2532~, 9~2476~ 10~1854~, 11~649~ 12~4314~ 13~846~, 14~5455~ 15~846~.'),
  (8963, 11, 7, 21, 'And he set up the pillars in the porch of the temple: and he set up the right pillar, and called the name thereof Jachin: and he set up the left pillar, and called the name thereof Boaz.', '3~06965~ 5~05982~ 8~0197~ 11~01964~: 15~06965~ 17~03233~ 18~05982~, 20~07121~ 22~08034~ 24~03199~: 28~06965~ 30~08042~ 31~05982~, 33~07121~ 35~08034~ 37~01162~.'),
  (5222, 5, 11, 8, 'Therefore shall ye keep all the commandments which I command you this day, that ye may be strong, and go in and possess the land, whither ye go to possess it;', '&para; 3~08104~ 6~04687~ 7~0834~ 9~06680~ 12~03117~, 17~02388~, 20~0935~ 22~03423~ 24~0776~, 27~05674~ 29~03423~'),
  (15339, 19, 89, 4, 'Thy seed will I establish for ever, and build up thy throne to all generations. Selah.', '1~02233~ 4~03559~ 5~05704~ 6~05769~, 9~01129~ 11~03678~ 13~01755~ 14~01755~. 15~05542~.'),
  (24610, 41, 10, 11, 'And he saith unto them, Whosoever shall put away his wife, and marry another, committeth adultery against her.', '0~2532~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 5~1437~ 6~3739~ 8~630~ 9~846~ 10~1135~, 11~2532~ 12~1060~ 13~243~, 15~3429~ 16~1909~ 17~846~.'),
  (9228, 11, 14, 2, 'And Jeroboam said to his wife, Arise, I pray thee, and disguise thyself, that thou be not known to be the wife of Jeroboam; and get thee to Shiloh: behold, there is Ahijah the prophet, which told me that I should be king over this people.', '1~03379~ 2~0559~ 5~0802~, 6~06965~, 11~08138~ 17~03045~ 21~0802~ 23~03379~; 25~01980~ 28~07887~: [31] 32~0281~ 34~05030~, 36~01696~ [39 41] 42~04428~ 45~05971~.'),
  (25167, 42, 6, 9, 'Then said Jesus unto them, I will ask you one thing; Is it lawful on the sabbath days to do good, or to do evil? to save life, or to destroy it?', '0~3767~ 1~2036~ 2~2424~ 3~4314~ 4~846~, 7~1905~ 8~5209~ 10~5101~; 13~1832~ 17~4521~ 20~15~, 21~2228~ 24~2554~? 26~4982~ 27~5590~, 28~2228~ 30~622~ [31]'),
  (4845, 4, 34, 23, 'The prince of the children of Joseph, for the tribe of the children of Manasseh, Hanniel the son of Ephod.', '1~05387~ 4~01121~ 6~03130~, 9~04294~ 12~01121~ 14~04519~, 15~02592~ 17~01121~ 19~0641~.'),
  (18763, 23, 56, 1, 'Thus saith the LORD, Keep ye judgment, and do justice: for my salvation is near to come, and my righteousness to be revealed.', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03068~, 4~08104~ 6~04941~, 8~06213~ 9~06666~: 12~03444~ [13] 14~07138~ 16~0935~, 19~06666~ 22~01540~.'),
  (16525, 20, 4, 26, 'Ponder the path of thy feet, and let all thy ways be established.', '0~06424~ 2~04570~ 5~07272~, 10~01870~ 12~03559~.'),
  (22376, 30, 1, 3, 'Thus saith the LORD; For three transgressions of Damascus, and for four, I will not turn away the punishment thereof; because they have threshed Gilead with threshing instruments of iron:', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03068~; 5~07969~ 6~06588~ 8~01834~, 11~0702~, 16~07725~ [17 18] 23~01758~ 24~01568~ 27~02742~ 29~01270~:'),
  (1631, 2, 4, 25, 'Then Zipporah took a sharp stone, and cut off the foreskin of her son, and cast it at his feet, and said, Surely a bloody husband art thou to me.', '1~06855~ 2~03947~ 5~06864~, 8~03772~ 10~06190~ 13~01121~, 15~05060~ [16] 19~07272~, 21~0559~, 24~01818~ 25~02860~ [26]'),
  (3966, 4, 8, 22, 'And after that went the Levites in to do their service in the tabernacle of the congregation before Aaron, and before his sons: as the LORD had commanded Moses concerning the Levites, so did they unto them.', '1~0310~ 3~0935~ 5~03881~ 8~05647~ 10~05656~ 13~0168~ 16~04150~ 17~06440~ 18~0175~, 20~06440~ 22~01121~: 25~03068~ 27~06680~ 28~04872~ 31~03881~, 33~06213~'),
  (12992, 18, 6, 5, 'Doth the wild ass bray when he hath grass? or loweth the ox over his fodder?', '3~06501~ 4~05101~ 8~01877~? 10~01600~ 12~07794~ 15~01098~?'),
  (25808, 42, 20, 15, 'So they cast him out of the vineyard, and killed him. What therefore shall the lord of the vineyard do unto them?', '0~2532~ 2~1544~ 3~846~ 5~1854~ 7~290~, 9~615~ [10] 11~5101~ 12~3767~ 13~4160~ 15~2962~ 18~290~ 19~4160~ 21~846~?'),
  (15866, 19, 116, 9, 'I will walk before the LORD in the land of the living.', '2~01980~ 3~06440~ 5~03068~ 8~0776~ 11~02416~.'),
  (5944, 6, 5, 4, 'And this is the cause why Joshua did circumcise: All the people that came out of Egypt, that were males, even all the men of war, died in the wilderness by the way, after they came out of Egypt.', '[2] 4~01697~ 6~03091~ 8~04135~: 11~05971~ 14~03318~ 16~04714~, [17 18] 19~02145~, [20] 23~0582~ 25~04421~, 26~04191~ 29~04057~ 32~01870~, 36~03318~ 38~04714~.'),
  (12320, 16, 2, 4, 'Then the king said unto me, For what dost thou make request? So I prayed to the God of heaven.', '2~04428~ 3~0559~ 11~01245~? 14~06419~ 17~0430~ 19~08064~.'),
  (29250, 49, 2, 5, 'Even when we were dead in sins, hath quickened us together with Christ, (by grace ye are saved;)', '0~2532~ 2~2248~ 3~5607~ 4~3498~ 6~3900~, 11~4806~ 12~5547~, 14~5485~ 16~2075~ 17~4982~;)'),
  (13240, 18, 15, 28, 'And he dwelleth in desolate cities, and in houses which no man inhabiteth, which are ready to become heaps.', '2~07931~ 4~03582~ 5~05892~, [6] 8~01004~ 12~03427~, 15~06257~ 18~01530~.'),
  (3710, 4, 3, 13, 'Because all the firstborn are mine; for on the day that I smote all the firstborn in the land of Egypt I hallowed unto me all the firstborn in Israel, both man and beast: mine shall they be: I am the LORD.', '3~01060~ [4] [6] 9~03117~ 12~05221~ 15~01060~ 18~0776~ 20~04714~ 22~06942~ 27~01060~ 29~03478~, 31~0120~ 33~0929~: [39] 41~03068~.'),
  (2881, 3, 6, 27, 'Whatsoever shall touch the flesh thereof shall be holy: and when there is sprinkled of the blood thereof upon any garment, thou shalt wash that whereon it was sprinkled in the holy place.', '2~05060~ 4~01320~ 8~06942~: 13~05137~ 16~01818~ 20~0899~, 23~03526~ 28~05137~ 31~06918~ 32~04725~.'),
  (22652, 33, 5, 10, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, saith the LORD, that I will cut off thy horses out of the midst of thee, and I will destroy thy chariots:', '8~03117~, 9~05002~ 11~03068~, 16~03772~ 18~05483~ 22~07130~ 28~06~ 30~04818~:'),
  (6237, 6, 15, 28, 'And Hazarshual, and Beersheba, and Bizjothjah,', '1~02705~, 3~0884~, 5~0964~,'),
  (11247, 14, 3, 10, 'And in the most holy house he made two cherubims of image work, and overlaid them with gold.', '&para; 3~06944~ 4~06944~ 5~01004~ 7~06213~ 8~08147~ 9~03742~ 11~06816~ 12~04639~, 14~06823~ 17~02091~.'),
  (197, 1, 8, 13, 'And it came to pass in the six hundredth and first year, in the first month, the first day of the month, the waters were dried up from off the earth: and Noah removed the covering of the ark, and looked, and, behold, the face of the ground was dry.', '&para; 7~08337~ 8~03967~ 11~08141~, 14~07223~ [15] 17~0259~ [18] 21~02320~, 23~04325~ 26~02717~ 30~0776~: 32~05146~ 33~05493~ 35~04372~ 38~08392~, 40~07200~, 44~06440~ 47~0127~ 49~02717~.'),
  (4550, 4, 26, 55, 'Notwithstanding the land shall be divided by lot: according to the names of the tribes of their fathers they shall inherit.', '2~0776~ 5~02505~ 7~01486~: 11~08034~ 14~04294~ 17~01~ 20~05157~.'),
  (24037, 40, 25, 19, 'After a long time the lord of those servants cometh, and reckoneth with them.', '0~3326~ 1~1161~ 2~4183~ 3~5550~ 5~2962~ 7~1565~ 8~1401~ 9~2064~, 10~2532~ 11~4868~ 12~3056~* 13~3326~ 14~846~.'),
  (11277, 14, 5, 1, 'Thus all the work that Solomon made for the house of the LORD was finished: and Solomon brought in all the things that David his father had dedicated; and the silver, and the gold, and all the instruments, put he among the treasures of the house of God.', '&para; 3~04399~ 5~08010~ 6~06213~ 9~01004~ 12~03068~ 14~07999~: 16~08010~ 17~0935~ [19] 21~06944~ 23~01732~ 25~01~ 27~06944~; 30~03701~, 33~02091~, 37~03627~, 38~05414~ 42~0214~ 45~01004~ 47~0430~.'),
  (8278, 10, 11, 12, 'And David said to Uriah, Tarry here to day also, and to morrow I will let thee depart. So Uriah abode in Jerusalem that day, and the morrow.', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 4~0223~, 5~03427~ 8~03117~ 12~04279~ 17~07971~. 19~0223~ 20~03427~ 22~03389~ 24~03117~, 27~04283~.'),
  (23436, 40, 10, 9, 'Provide neither gold, nor silver, nor brass in your purses,', '0~2932~ 1~3361~ 2~5557~, 3~3366~ 4~696~, 5~3366~ 6~5475~ 7~1519~ 8~5216~ 9~2223~,'),
  (19809, 24, 33, 25, 'Thus saith the LORD; If my covenant be not with day and night, and if I have not appointed the ordinances of heaven and earth;', '1~0559~ 3~03068~; 6~01285~ [7] 10~03119~ 12~03915~, [13 14] 18~07760~ 20~02708~ 22~08064~ 24~0776~;'),
  (21108, 26, 25, 16, 'Therefore thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I will stretch out mine hand upon the Philistines, and I will cut off the Cherethims, and destroy the remnant of the sea coast.', '2~0559~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~; 10~05186~ 12~03027~ 15~06430~, 20~03772~ 22~03774~, 24~06~ 26~07611~ 29~03220~ 30~02348~.'),
  (30252, 58, 12, 24, 'And to Jesus the mediator of the new covenant, and to the blood of sprinkling, that speaketh better things than that of Abel.', '0~2532~ 2~2424~ 4~3316~ 7~3501~ 8~1242~, 9~2532~ 12~129~ 14~4473~, 16~2980~ 18~2909~ 19~3844~ [20 21] 22~6~.'),
  (13333, 18, 19, 27, 'Whom I shall see for myself, and mine eyes shall behold, and not another; though my reins be consumed within me.', '3~02372~ 8~05869~ 10~07200~, 13~02114~; [14] 16~03629~ 18~03615~ 19~02436~'),
  (7312, 9, 4, 8, 'Woe unto us! who shall deliver us out of the hand of these mighty Gods? these are the Gods that smote the Egyptians with all the plagues in the wilderness.', '0~0188~ 5~05337~ 10~03027~ 13~0117~ 14~0430~? [16] 18~0430~ 20~05221~ 22~04714~ 26~04347~ 29~04057~.'),
  (22798, 36, 1, 2, 'I will utterly consume all things from off the land, saith the LORD.', '2~0622~ 3~05486~ [5] 9~0127~ 10~06440~,* 11~05002~ 13~03068~.'),
  (18581, 23, 45, 11, 'Thus saith the LORD, the Holy One of Israel, and his Maker, Ask me of things to come concerning my sons, and concerning the work of my hands command ye me.', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03068~, 6~06918~ 8~03478~, 11~03335~, 12~07592~ 17~0857~ 20~01121~, 24~06467~ 27~03027~ 28~06680~'),
  (2151, 2, 23, 2, 'Thou shalt not follow a multitude to do evil; neither shalt thou speak in a cause to decline after many to wrest judgment:', '3~0310~ 5~07227~ [7] 8~07451~; 12~06030~ 15~07379~ 17~05186~ 18~0310~ 19~07227~ 21~05186~ [22]'),
  (5344, 5, 15, 19, 'All the firstling males that come of thy herd and of thy flock thou shalt sanctify unto the LORD thy God: thou shalt do no work with the firstling of thy bullock, nor shear the firstling of thy sheep.', '&para; 2~01060~ 3~02145~ 5~03205~ 8~01241~ 12~06629~ 15~06942~ 18~03068~ 20~0430~: 25~05647~ 28~01060~ 31~07794~, 33~01494~ 35~01060~ 38~06629~.'),
  (14806, 19, 59, 7, 'Behold, they belch out with their mouth: swords are in their lips: for who, say they, doth hear?', '3~05042~ 6~06310~: 7~02719~ [8] 11~08193~: [14 15] 17~08085~?'),
  (17534, 21, 12, 2, 'While the sun, or the light, or the moon, or the stars, be not darkened, nor the clouds return after the rain:', '2~08121~, 5~0216~, 8~03394~, 11~03556~, 14~02821~, 17~05645~ 18~07725~ 19~0310~ 21~01653~:'),
  (11700, 14, 24, 14, 'And when they had finished it, they brought the rest of the money before the king and Jehoiada, whereof were made vessels for the house of the LORD, even vessels to minister, and to offer withal, and spoons, and vessels of gold and silver. And they offered burnt offerings in the house of the LORD continually all the days of Jehoiada.', '4~03615~ [5] 7~0935~ 9~07605~ 12~03701~ 13~06440~ 15~04428~ 17~03077~, 20~06213~ 21~03627~ 24~01004~ 27~03068~, [28] 29~03627~ 31~08335~, 34~05927~ [35] 37~03709~, 39~03627~ 41~02091~ 43~03701~. 46~05927~ 48~05930~ 51~01004~ 54~03068~ 55~08548~ 58~03117~ 60~03077~.'),
  (13282, 18, 17, 13, 'If I wait, the grave is mine house: I have made my bed in the darkness.', '2~06960~, 4~07585~ [5] 7~01004~: 10~07502~ 12~03326~ 15~02822~.'),
  (27227, 44, 8, 35, 'Then Philip opened his mouth, and began at the same scripture, and preached unto him Jesus.', '0~1161~ 1~5376~ 2~455~ 3~846~ 4~4750~, 5~2532~ 6~756~ 7~575~ 9~5026~ 10~1124~, 12~2097~ 14~846~ 15~2424~.'),
  (9353, 11, 18, 4, 'For it was so, when Jezebel cut off the prophets of the LORD, that Obadiah took an hundred prophets, and hid them by fifty in a cave, and fed them with bread and water.)', '[3] 5~0348~ 7~03772~ 9~05030~ 12~03068~, 14~05662~ 15~03947~ 17~03967~ 18~05030~, 20~02244~ 23~02572~ 24~0376~ 26~04631~, 28~03557~ 31~03899~ 33~04325~)'),
  (30693, 65, 1, 5, 'I will therefore put you in remembrance, though ye once knew this, how that the Lord, having saved the people out of the land of Egypt, afterward destroyed them that believed not.', '1~1014~ 2~1161~ 3~5279~ 4~5209~ 6~5279~, 8~5209~ 9~530~ 10~1492~ 11~5124~, 13~3754~ 15~2962~, 17~4982~ 19~2992~ 21~1537~ 23~1093~ 25~125~, 26~1208~ 27~622~ 30~4100~ 31~3361~.'),
  (28773, 46, 15, 39, 'All flesh is not the same flesh: but there is one kind of flesh of men, another flesh of beasts, another of fishes, and another of birds.', '0~3956~ 1~4561~ [2] 3~3756~ 5~846~ 6~4561~: 7~3303~ [8 8~235~ 9] 10~243~ [11 12] 13~4561~ 15~444~ 16~1161~,* 17~243~ 18~4561~ 20~2934~ 21~1161~,* 22~243~ 24~2486~, [25] 25~1161~ 26~243~ 28~4421~.'),
  (7969, 9, 28, 20, 'Then Saul fell straightway all along on the earth, and was sore afraid, because of the words of Samuel: and there was no strength in him; for he had eaten no bread all the day, nor all the night.', '&para; 1~07586~ 2~05307~ 3~04116~ 4~04393~ 5~06967~ 8~0776~, 11~03966~ 12~03372~, 16~01697~ 18~08050~: 23~03581~ 29~0398~ 31~03899~ 34~03117~, 38~03915~.'),
  (19669, 24, 29, 25, 'Thus speaketh the LORD of hosts, the God of Israel, saying, Because thou hast sent letters in thy name unto all the people that are at Jerusalem, and to Zephaniah the son of Maaseiah the priest, and to all the priests, saying,', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06635~, 7~0430~ 9~03478~, 10~0559~, 14~07971~ 15~05612~ 18~08034~ 22~05971~ [24] 26~03389~, 29~06846~ 31~01121~ 33~04641~ 35~03548~, 40~03548~, 41~0559~,'),
  (18964, 24, 1, 9, 'Then the LORD put forth his hand, and touched my mouth. And the LORD said unto me, Behold, I have put my words in thy mouth.', '2~03068~ 4~07971~ 6~03027~, 8~05060~ 10~06310~. 13~03068~ 14~0559~ 20~05414~ 22~01697~ 25~06310~.'),
  (6931, 7, 14, 15, 'And it came to pass on the seventh day, that they said unto Samson''s wife, Entice thy husband, that he may declare unto us the riddle, lest we burn thee and thy father''s house with fire: have ye called us to take that we have? is it not so?', '7~07637~ 8~03117~, 11~0559~ 13~08123~ 14~0802~, 15~06601~ 17~0376~, 21~05046~ 25~02420~, 28~08313~ 32~01~ 33~01004~ 35~0784~: 38~07121~ 44~03423~? [45 46] [48]'),
  (20281, 24, 51, 60, 'So Jeremiah wrote in a book all the evil that should come upon Babylon, even all these words that are written against Babylon.', '1~03414~ 2~03789~ 4~0259~ 5~05612~ 8~07451~ 11~0935~ 13~0894~, [14] 17~01697~ 20~03789~ 22~0894~.'),
  (28361, 45, 16, 9, 'Salute Urbane, our helper in Christ, and Stachys my beloved.', '0~782~ 1~3773~, 2~2257~ 3~4904~ 4~1722~ 5~5547~, 6~2532~ 7~4720~ 8~3450~ 9~27~.'),
  (16604, 20, 7, 20, 'He hath taken a bag of money with him, and will come home at the day appointed.', '2~03947~ 4~06872~ 6~03701~ 8~03027~, [9] 11~0935~ 12~01004~ 15~03117~ 16~03677~.'),
  (19217, 24, 10, 7, 'Who would not fear thee, O King of nations? for to thee doth it appertain: forasmuch as among all the wise men of the nations, and in all their kingdoms, there is none like unto thee.', '3~03372~ 6~04428~ 8~01471~? 14~02969~: 20~02450~ [21] 24~01471~, 29~04438~, [30 31]'),
  (8546, 10, 19, 27, 'And he hath slandered thy servant unto my lord the king; but my lord the king is as an angel of God: do therefore what is good in thine eyes.', '3~07270~ 5~05650~ 8~0113~ 10~04428~; 13~0113~ 15~04428~ [16] 19~04397~ 21~0430~: 22~06213~ [24 25] 26~02896~ 29~05869~.'),
  (25082, 42, 4, 7, 'If thou therefore wilt worship me, all shall be thine.', '0~1437~ 1~4771~ 2~3767~ 4~4352~ 5~3450~ 6~1799~,* 7~3956~ 9~2071~ 10~4675~.'),
  (23692, 40, 16, 10, 'Neither the seven loaves of the four thousand, and how many baskets ye took up?', '0~3761~ 2~2033~ 3~740~ 7~5070~, 8~2532~ 10~4214~ 11~4711~ 14~2983~?'),
  (4312, 4, 19, 18, 'And a clean person shall take hyssop, and dip it in the water, and sprinkle it upon the tent, and upon all the vessels, and upon the persons that were there, and upon him that touched a bone, or one slain, or one dead, or a grave:', '2~02889~ 3~0376~ 5~03947~ 6~0231~, 8~02881~ [9] 12~04325~, 14~05137~ [15] 18~0168~, 23~03627~, 27~05315~ 35~05060~ 37~06106~, 40~02491~, 43~04191~, 46~06913~:'),
  (5900, 6, 3, 1, 'And Joshua rose early in the morning; and they removed from Shittim, and came to Jordan, he and all the children of Israel, and lodged there before they passed over.', '&para; 1~03091~ 3~07925~ 6~01242~; 9~05265~ 11~07851~, 13~0935~ 15~03383~, 20~01121~ 22~03478~, 24~03885~ 29~05674~.'),
  (14938, 19, 68, 29, 'Because of thy temple at Jerusalem shall kings bring presents unto thee.', '3~01964~ 5~03389~ 7~04428~ 8~02986~ 9~07862~'),
  (21261, 26, 32, 4, 'Then will I leave thee upon the land, I will cast thee forth upon the open field, and will cause all the fowls of the heaven to remain upon thee, and I will fill the beasts of the whole earth with thee.', '3~05203~ 7~0776~, 12~02904~ 15~06440~ 16~07704~, 22~05775~ 25~08064~ 27~07931~ 33~07646~ 35~02416~ 39~0776~'),
  (10310, 13, 1, 50, 'And when Baalhanan was dead, Hadad reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was Pai; and his wife''s name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab.', '2~01177~ 4~04191~, 5~01908~ 6~04427~ 12~08034~ 15~05892~ [16] 17~06464~; 20~0802~ 21~08034~ [22] 23~04105~, 25~01323~ 27~04308~, 29~01323~ 31~04314~.'),
  (30480, 60, 4, 18, 'And if the righteous scarcely be saved, where shall the ungodly and the sinner appear?', '0~2532~ 1~1487~ 3~1342~ 4~3433~ 6~4982~, 7~4226~ 8~5316~ 10~765~ 11~2532~ 13~268~ 14~5316~?'),
  (19093, 24, 5, 26, 'For among my people are found wicked men: they lay wait, as he that setteth snares; they set a trap, they catch men.', '3~05971~ 5~04672~ 6~07563~ [7] 10~07789~, 14~07918~ 15~03353~; 17~05324~ 19~04889~, 21~03920~ 22~0582~.'),
  (13255, 18, 16, 8, 'And thou hast filled me with wrinkles, which is a witness against me: and my leanness rising up in me beareth witness to my face.', '6~07059~, [7] 10~05707~ [11 12] 15~03585~ 17~06965~ 21~06030~ 24~06440~.'),
  (2877, 3, 6, 23, 'For every meat offering for the priest shall be wholly burnt: it shall not be eaten.', '3~04503~ 6~03548~ 10~03632~: 15~0398~.'),
  (7095, 7, 20, 34, 'And there came against Gibeah ten thousand chosen men out of all Israel, and the battle was sore: but they knew not that evil was near them.', '2~0935~ 3~05048~ 4~01390~ 5~06235~ 6~0505~ 7~0977~ 8~0376~ 12~03478~, 15~04421~ 17~03513~: 20~03045~ 23~07451~ [24] 25~05060~'),
  (28358, 45, 16, 6, 'Greet Mary, who bestowed much labour on us.', '0~782~ 1~3137~, 2~3748~ 3~2872~ 4~4183~ 5~2872~ 6~1519~ 7~2248~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (16449, 20, 2, 7, 'He layeth up sound wisdom for the righteous: he is a buckler to them that walk uprightly.', '2~06845~ 4~08454~ 7~03477~: [8 9] 11~04043~ 15~01980~ 16~08537~.'),
  (22679, 33, 7, 6, 'For the son dishonoureth the father, the daughter riseth up against her mother, the daughter in law against her mother in law; a man''s enemies are the men of his own house.', '2~01121~ 3~05034~ 5~01~, 7~01323~ 9~06965~ 12~0517~, 16~03618~ 21~02545~; 23~0376~ 24~0341~ [25] 27~0582~ 31~01004~.'),
  (2546, 2, 35, 10, 'And every wise hearted among you shall come, and make all that the LORD hath commanded;', '2~02450~ 3~03820~ 7~0935~, 9~06213~ 13~03068~ 15~06680~;'),
  (11275, 14, 4, 21, 'And the flowers, and the lamps, and the tongs, made he of gold, and that perfect gold;', '2~06525~, 5~05216~, 8~04457~, [9 11] 12~02091~, [13] 15~04357~ 16~02091~;'),
  (29474, 50, 4, 16, 'For even in Thessalonica ye sent once and again unto my necessity.', '0~3754~ 1~2532~ 2~1722~ 3~2332~ 5~3992~ 6~530~ 7~2532~* 8~2532~ 9~1364~ 10~1519~ 11~3427~ 12~5532~.'),
  (2722, 2, 40, 10, 'And thou shalt anoint the altar of the burnt offering, and all his vessels, and sanctify the altar: and it shall be an altar most holy.', '3~04886~ 5~04196~ 9~05930~, 13~03627~, 15~06942~ 17~04196~: 23~04196~ 24~06944~ 25~06944~.'),
  (6212, 6, 15, 3, 'And it went out to the south side to Maalehacrabbim, and passed along to Zin, and ascended up on the south side unto Kadeshbarnea, and passed along to Hezron, and went up to Adar, and fetched a compass to Karkaa:', '3~03318~ 7~05045~ 9~04610~, 11~05674~ 14~06790~, 17~05927~ 21~05045~ 23~06947~, 25~05674~ 28~02696~, 31~05927~ 33~0146~, 37~05437~ 39~07173~:'),
  (20457, 25, 5, 6, 'We have given the hand to the Egyptians, and to the Assyrians, to be satisfied with bread.', '2~05414~ 4~03027~ [5] 7~04714~, [8 9] 11~0804~, 14~07646~ 16~03899~.'),
  (19644, 24, 28, 17, 'So Hananiah the prophet died the same year in the seventh month.', '1~02608~ 3~05030~ 4~04191~ 7~08141~ 10~07637~ 11~02320~.'),
  (7157, 8, 2, 1, 'And Naomi had a kinsman of her husband''s, a mighty man of wealth, of the family of Elimelech; and his name was Boaz.', '&para; 1~05281~ 4~04129~ 5~03045~* 8~0376~, 10~01368~ 11~0376~ 13~02428~, 16~04940~ 18~0458~; 21~08034~ [22] 23~01162~.'),
  (22991, 38, 8, 6, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; If it be marvellous in the eyes of the remnant of this people in these days, should it also be marvellous in mine eyes? saith the LORD of hosts.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06635~; 9~06381~ 12~05869~ 15~07611~ 18~05971~ 21~03117~, 26~06381~ 29~05869~? 30~05002~ 32~03068~ 34~06635~.'),
  (16549, 20, 5, 23, 'He shall die without instruction; and in the greatness of his folly he shall go astray.', '2~04191~ 4~04148~; 8~07230~ 11~0200~ 15~07686~.'),
  (9114, 11, 10, 27, 'And the king made silver to be in Jerusalem as stones, and cedars made he to be as the sycamore trees that are in the vale, for abundance.', '2~04428~ 3~05414~ 4~03701~ [5 6] 8~03389~ 10~068~, 12~0730~ 13~05414~ [15 16] 20~08256~ [22] 25~08219~, 27~07230~.'),
  (24490, 41, 7, 16, 'If any man have ears to hear, let him hear.', '2~1536~ 3~2192~ 4~3775~ 6~191~, 9~191~.'),
  (17701, 23, 2, 7, 'Their land also is full of silver and gold, neither is there any end of their treasures; their land is also full of horses, neither is there any end of their chariots:', '1~0776~ 4~04390~ 6~03701~ 8~02091~, [10 12] 13~07097~ 16~0214~; 18~0776~ 21~04390~ 23~05483~, [25 27] 28~07097~ 31~04818~:'),
  (568, 1, 22, 17, 'That in blessing I will bless thee, and in multiplying I will multiply thy seed as the stars of the heaven, and as the sand which is upon the sea shore; and thy seed shall possess the gate of his enemies;', '2~01288~ 5~01288~ 9~07235~ 12~07235~ 14~02233~ 17~03556~ 20~08064~, 24~02344~ [26] 29~03220~ 30~08193~; 33~02233~ 35~03423~ 37~08179~ 40~0341~;'),
  (20546, 26, 4, 8, 'And, behold, I will lay bands upon thee, and thou shalt not turn thee from one side to another, till thou hast ended the days of thy siege.', '4~05414~ 5~05688~ 12~02015~ 16~06654~ 18~06654~, 22~03615~ 24~03117~ 27~04692~.'),
  (16855, 20, 16, 6, 'By mercy and truth iniquity is purged: and by the fear of the LORD men depart from evil.', '&para; 1~02617~ 3~0571~ 4~05771~ 6~03722~: 10~03374~ 13~03068~ [14] 15~05493~ 17~07451~.'),
  (17526, 21, 11, 4, 'He that observeth the wind shall not sow; and he that regardeth the clouds shall not reap.', '2~08104~ 4~07307~ 7~02232~; 11~07200~ 13~05645~ 16~07114~.'),
  (20988, 26, 22, 3, 'Then say thou, Thus saith the Lord GOD, The city sheddeth blood in the midst of it, that her time may come, and maketh idols against herself to defile herself.', '1~0559~ 4~0559~ 6~0136~ 7~03069~, 9~05892~ 10~08210~ 11~01818~ 14~08432~ 19~06256~ 21~0935~, 23~06213~ 24~01544~ 28~02930~'),
  (21079, 26, 24, 14, 'I the LORD have spoken it: it shall come to pass, and I will do it; I will not go back, neither will I spare, neither will I repent; according to thy ways, and according to thy doings, shall they judge thee, saith the Lord GOD.', '2~03068~ 4~01696~ [5] 10~0935~, 14~06213~ [15] 20~06544~, 24~02347~, 28~05162~; 32~01870~, 37~05949~, 40~08199~ 42~05002~ 44~0136~ 45~03069~.'),
  (26175, 43, 4, 4, 'And he must needs go through Samaria.', '&para; 0~1161~ 3~1163~ 4~1330~ 5~1223~ 6~4540~.'),
  (6830, 7, 10, 12, 'The Zidonians also, and the Amalekites, and the Maonites, did oppress you; and ye cried to me, and I delivered you out of their hand.', '1~06722~ 5~06002~, 8~04584~, 10~03905~ 14~06817~ 19~03467~ 24~03027~.'),
  (30312, 59, 2, 3, 'And ye have respect to him that weareth the gay clothing, and say unto him, Sit thou here in a good place; and say to the poor, Stand thou there, or sit here under my footstool:', '0~2532~ 3~1914~ 4~1909~ 7~5409~ 9~2986~ 10~2066~, 11~2532~ 12~2036~ 14~846~, 15~2521~ 16~4771~ 17~5602~ 21~2573~; 22~2532~ 23~2036~ 26~4434~, 27~2476~ 28~4771~ 29~1563~, 30~2228~ 31~2521~ 32~5602~ 33~5259~ 34~3450~ 35~5286~:'),
  (22856, 37, 1, 7, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; Consider your ways.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06635~; 6~07760~ 7~03824~* 9~01870~.'),
  (21494, 26, 40, 8, 'He measured also the porch of the gate within, one reed.', '1~04058~ 4~0197~ 7~08179~ 8~01004~, 9~0259~ 10~07070~.'),
  (5085, 5, 5, 26, 'For who is there of all flesh, that hath heard the voice of the living God speaking out of the midst of the fire, as we have, and lived?', '[2 4] 6~01320~, 9~08085~ 11~06963~ 14~02416~ 15~0430~ 16~01696~ 20~08432~ 23~0784~, [26] 28~02421~?'),
  (8793, 11, 2, 15, 'And he said, Thou knowest that the kingdom was mine, and that all Israel set their faces on me, that I should reign: howbeit the kingdom is turned about, and is become my brother''s: for it was his from the LORD.', '2~0559~, 4~03045~ 7~04410~ [11] 13~03478~ 14~07760~ 16~06440~ 22~04427~: 25~04410~ 28~05437~, 33~0251~: 40~03068~.'),
  (4200, 4, 16, 1, 'Now Korah, the son of Izhar, the son of Kohath, the son of Levi, and Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab, and On, the son of Peleth, sons of Reuben, took men:', '&para; 1~07141~, 3~01121~ 5~03324~, 7~01121~ 9~06955~, 11~01121~ 13~03878~, 15~01885~ 17~048~, 19~01121~ 21~0446~, 23~0203~, 25~01121~ 27~06431~, 28~01121~ 30~07205~, 31~03947~ [32]'),
  (530, 1, 21, 13, 'And also of the son of the bondwoman will I make a nation, because he is thy seed.', '4~01121~ 7~0519~ 10~07760~ 12~01471~, [15] 17~02233~.'),
  (5356, 5, 16, 8, 'Six days thou shalt eat unleavened bread: and on the seventh day shall be a solemn assembly to the LORD thy God: thou shalt do no work therein.', '0~08337~ 1~03117~ 4~0398~ 6~04682~: 10~07637~ 11~03117~ [12 13] 16~06116~ 19~03068~ 21~0430~: 24~06213~ 26~04399~ [27]'),
  (24211, 40, 28, 6, 'He is not here: for he is risen, as he said. Come, see the place where the Lord lay.', '1~2076~ 2~3756~ 3~5602~: 4~1063~ 7~1453~, 8~2531~ 10~2036~. 11~1205~, 12~1492~ 14~5117~ 15~3699~ 17~2962~ 18~2749~.'),
  (27524, 44, 16, 25, 'And at midnight Paul and Silas prayed, and sang praises unto God: and the prisoners heard them.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~2596~ 2~3317~ 3~3972~ 4~2532~ 5~4609~ 6~4336~, 9~5214~ 11~2316~: 12~1161~ 14~1198~ 15~1874~ 16~846~.'),
  (1119, 1, 37, 31, 'And they took Joseph''s coat, and killed a kid of the goats, and dipped the coat in the blood;', '&para; 2~03947~ 3~03130~ 4~03801~, 6~07819~ 8~08163~ 11~05795~, 13~02881~ 15~03801~ 18~01818~;'),
  (2292, 2, 27, 15, 'And on the other side shall be hangings fifteen cubits: their pillars three, and their sockets three.', '3~08145~ 4~03802~ [5 6] 7~07050~ 8~06240~ [9] 9~02568~: 11~05982~ 12~07969~, 15~0134~ 16~07969~.'),
  (5785, 5, 32, 21, 'They have moved me to jealousy with that which is not God; they have provoked me to anger with their vanities: and I will move them to jealousy with those which are not a people; I will provoke them to anger with a foolish nation.', '5~07065~ [7 9] 10~03808~ 11~0410~; 17~03707~ 20~01892~: 27~07065~ [29 31] 34~05971~; 40~03707~ 43~05036~ 44~01471~.'),
  (14147, 19, 18, 20, 'The LORD rewarded me according to my righteousness; according to the cleanness of my hands hath he recompensed me.', '&para; 1~03068~ 2~01580~ 7~06664~; 11~01252~ 14~03027~ 17~07725~'),
  (16827, 20, 15, 11, 'Hell and destruction are before the LORD: how much more then the hearts of the children of men?', '&para; 0~07585~ 2~011~ [3] 6~03068~: 12~03826~ 15~01121~ 17~0120~?'),
  (9287, 11, 15, 30, 'Because of the sins of Jeroboam which he sinned, and which he made Israel sin, by his provocation wherewith he provoked the LORD God of Israel to anger.', '3~02403~ 5~03379~ 8~02398~, 13~03478~ 14~02398~, 17~03708~ 22~03068~ 23~0430~ 25~03478~ 27~03707~.'),
  (20721, 26, 13, 4, 'O Israel, thy prophets are like the foxes in the deserts.', '1~03478~, 3~05030~ 7~07776~ 10~02723~.'),
  (14122, 19, 17, 10, 'They are enclosed in their own fat: with their mouth they speak proudly.', '2~05462~ 6~02459~: 9~06310~ 11~01696~ 12~01348~.'),
  (10418, 13, 4, 25, 'Shallum his son, Mibsam his son, Mishma his son.', '0~07967~ 2~01121~, 3~04017~ 5~01121~, 6~04927~ 8~01121~.'),
  (8333, 10, 13, 9, 'And she took a pan, and poured them out before him; but he refused to eat. And Amnon said, Have out all men from me. And they went out every man from him.', '2~03947~ 4~04958~, [7] 8~03332~ 9~06440~ 13~03985~ 15~0398~. 17~0550~ 18~0559~, 20~03318~ 22~0376~ 28~03318~ 30~0376~'),
  (5783, 5, 32, 19, 'And when the LORD saw it, he abhorred them, because of the provoking of his sons, and of his daughters.', '&para; 3~03068~ 4~07200~ [5] 7~05006~ [8] 12~03708~ 15~01121~, 19~01323~.'),
  (14117, 19, 17, 5, 'Hold up my goings in thy paths, that my footsteps slip not.', '1~08551~ 3~0838~ 6~04570~, [7] 9~06471~ 10~04131~'),
  (3680, 4, 2, 17, 'Then the tabernacle of the congregation shall set forward with the camp of the Levites in the midst of the camp: as they encamp, so shall they set forward, every man in his place by their standards.', '2~0168~ 5~04150~ 8~05265~ 11~04264~ 14~03881~ 17~08432~ 20~04264~: 23~02583~, 28~05265~, 30~0376~ 33~03027~ 36~01714~.'),
  (20284, 24, 51, 63, 'And it shall be, when thou hast made an end of reading this book, that thou shalt bind a stone to it, and cast it into the midst of Euphrates:', '9~03615~ 11~07121~ 13~05612~, [14] 17~07194~ 19~068~ 23~07993~ 27~08432~ 29~06578~:'),
  (1157, 1, 39, 3, 'And his master saw that the LORD was with him, and that the LORD made all that he did to prosper in his hand.', '2~0113~ 3~07200~ 6~03068~ [7] 13~03068~ 18~06213~ 20~06743~ 23~03027~.'),
  (27025, 44, 3, 13, 'The God of Abraham, and of Isaac, and of Jacob, the God of our fathers, hath glorified his Son Jesus; whom ye delivered up, and denied him in the presence of Pilate, when he was determined to let him go.', '1~2316~ 3~11~, 4~2532~ 6~2464~, 7~2532~ 9~2384~, 11~2316~ 13~2257~ 14~3962~, 16~1392~ 17~846~ 18~3816~ 19~2424~; 20~3739~ 21~5210~ 23~3860~, 24~2532~ 25~720~ 26~846~ 27~2596~ 29~4383~ 31~4091~, 35~2919~ 37~630~ [38] 38~1565~ 39~630~.'),
  (20173, 24, 49, 37, 'For I will cause Elam to be dismayed before their enemies, and before them that seek their life: and I will bring evil upon them, even my fierce anger, saith the LORD; and I will send the sword after them, till I have consumed them:', '4~05867~ 7~02865~ 8~06440~ 10~0341~, 12~06440~ 15~01245~ 17~05315~: 21~0935~ 22~07451~ [25] 27~02740~ 28~0639~, 29~05002~ 31~03068~; 35~07971~ 37~02719~ 38~0310~ 43~03615~'),
  (11335, 14, 7, 3, 'And when all the children of Israel saw how the fire came down, and the glory of the LORD upon the house, they bowed themselves with their faces to the ground upon the pavement, and worshipped, and praised the LORD, saying, For he is good; for his mercy endureth for ever.', '4~01121~ 6~03478~ 7~07200~ 10~0784~ 12~03381~, 15~03519~ 18~03068~ 21~01004~, 23~03766~ 27~0639~ 30~0776~ 33~07531~, 35~07812~, 37~03034~ 39~03068~, [40] [42 43] 44~02896~; 47~02617~ [48] 50~05769~.'),
  (4133, 4, 14, 20, 'And the LORD said, I have pardoned according to thy word:', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~, 6~05545~ 10~01697~:'),
  (27436, 44, 14, 6, 'They were ware of it, and fled unto Lystra and Derbe, cities of Lycaonia, and unto the region that lieth round about:', '2~4894~ [4] 6~2703~ 7~1519~ 8~3082~ 9~2532~ 10~1191~, 11~4172~ 13~3071~, 14~2532~ 21~4066~:'),
  (2537, 2, 35, 1, 'And Moses gathered all the congregation of the children of Israel together, and said unto them, These are the words which the LORD hath commanded, that ye should do them.', '&para; 1~04872~ 2~06950~ 5~05712~ 8~01121~ 10~03478~ 11~06950~, 13~0559~ [17] 19~01697~ 22~03068~ 24~06680~, [26] 28~06213~'),
  (340, 1, 13, 18, 'Then Abram removed his tent, and came and dwelt in the plain of Mamre, which is in Hebron, and built there an altar unto the LORD.', '1~087~ [3] 4~0167~, 6~0935~ 8~03427~ 11~0436~ 13~04471~, [15] 17~02275~, 19~01129~ 22~04196~ 25~03068~.'),
  (26437, 43, 8, 41, 'Ye do the deeds of your father. Then said they to him, We be not born of fornication; we have one Father, even God.', '0~5210~ 1~4160~ 3~2041~ 5~5216~ 6~3962~. 7~3767~ 9~2036~ 11~846~, 12~2249~ 13~1080~ 14~3756~ 15~1080~ 16~1537~ 17~4202~; 19~2192~ 20~1520~ 21~3962~, [22] 23~2316~.'),
  (17584, 22, 3, 4, 'It was but a little that I passed from them, but I found him whom my soul loveth: I held him, and would not let him go, until I had brought him into my mother''s house, and into the chamber of her that conceived me.', '[0 1] 4~04592~ 7~05674~ 12~04672~ 16~05315~ 17~0157~: 19~0270~ 26~07503~, 30~0935~ 34~0517~ 35~01004~, 39~02315~ 43~02029~'),
  (2687, 2, 39, 18, 'And the two ends of the two wreathen chains they fastened in the two ouches, and put them on the shoulderpieces of the ephod, before it.', '2~08147~ 3~07098~ 6~08147~ 7~05688~ 8~05688~ 10~05414~ 13~08147~ 14~04865~, 16~05414~ 20~03802~ 23~0646~, 24~06440~ 25~04136~.'),
  (9395, 11, 18, 46, 'And the hand of the LORD was on Elijah; and he girded up his loins, and ran before Ahab to the entrance of Jezreel.', '2~03027~ 5~03068~ 8~0452~; 12~08151~ 14~04975~, 16~07323~ 17~06440~ 18~0256~ 21~0935~ 23~03157~.'),
  (30221, 58, 11, 33, 'Who through faith subdued kingdoms, wrought righteousness, obtained promises, stopped the mouths of lions,', '0~3739~ 1~1223~ 2~4102~ 3~2610~ 4~932~, 5~2038~ 6~1343~, 7~2013~ 8~1860~, 9~5420~ 11~4750~ 13~3023~,'),
  (3580, 3, 27, 5, 'And if it be from five years old even unto twenty years old, then thy estimation shall be of the male twenty shekels, and for the female ten shekels.', '[2 3] 5~02568~ 6~08141~ 7~01121~ 10~06242~ 11~08141~ 12~01121~, 15~06187~ 20~02145~ 21~06242~ 22~08255~, 26~05347~ 27~06235~ 28~08255~.'),
  (14853, 19, 63, 5, 'My soul shall be satisfied as with marrow and fatness; and my mouth shall praise thee with joyful lips:', '1~05315~ 4~07646~ [6] 7~02459~ 9~01880~; 12~06310~ 14~01984~ [15] 17~07445~ 18~08193~:'),
  (10131, 12, 21, 4, 'And he built altars in the house of the LORD, of which the LORD said, In Jerusalem will I put my name.', '2~01129~ 3~04196~ 6~01004~ 9~03068~, 13~03068~ 14~0559~, 16~03389~ 19~07760~ 21~08034~.'),
  (11224, 14, 2, 5, 'And the house which I build is great: for great is our God above all gods.', '2~01004~ 5~01129~ [6] 7~01419~: 9~01419~ [10] 12~0430~ 15~0430~.'),
  (3443, 3, 23, 36, 'Seven days ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the LORD: on the eighth day shall be an holy convocation unto you; and ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the LORD: it is a solemn assembly; and ye shall do no servile work therein.', '0~07651~ 1~03117~ 4~07126~ 9~0801~ 12~03068~: 15~08066~ 16~03117~ 20~06944~ 21~04744~ 27~07126~ 32~0801~ 35~03068~: [37] 40~06116~; [41] 44~06213~ 46~05656~ 47~04399~ [48]'),
  (3583, 3, 27, 8, 'But if he be poorer than thy estimation, then he shall present himself before the priest, and the priest shall value him; according to his ability that vowed shall the priest value him.', '4~04134~ 7~06187~, 11~05975~ 13~06440~ 15~03548~, 18~03548~ 20~06186~ 23~06310~ 25~05381~ 26~03027~* 28~05087~ 31~03548~ 32~06186~'),
  (19281, 24, 13, 6, 'And it came to pass after many days, that the LORD said unto me, Arise, go to Euphrates, and take the girdle from thence, which I commanded thee to hide there.', '5~07093~ 6~07227~ 7~03117~, 10~03068~ 11~0559~ 14~06965~, 15~03212~ 17~06578~, 19~03947~ 21~0232~ 26~06680~ 29~02934~'),
  (11450, 14, 12, 4, 'And he took the fenced cities which pertained to Judah, and came to Jerusalem.', '2~03920~ 4~04694~ 5~05892~ [7] 9~03063~, 11~0935~ 13~03389~.'),
  (20328, 25, 1, 9, 'Her filthiness is in her skirts; she remembereth not her last end; therefore she came down wonderfully: she had no comforter. O LORD, behold my affliction: for the enemy hath magnified himself.', '1~02932~ [2] 5~07757~; 7~02142~ 11~0319~; 15~03381~ 16~06382~: 20~05162~. 22~03068~, 23~07200~ 25~06040~: 28~0341~ 30~01431~ [31]'),
  (16818, 20, 15, 2, 'The tongue of the wise useth knowledge aright: but the mouth of fools poureth out foolishness.', '&para; 1~03956~ 4~02450~ 6~01847~ 7~03190~: 10~06310~ 12~03684~ 14~05042~ 15~0200~.'),
  (17705, 23, 2, 11, 'The lofty looks of man shall be humbled, and the haughtiness of men shall be bowed down, and the LORD alone shall be exalted in that day.', '1~01365~ 2~05869~ 4~0120~ 7~08213~, 10~07312~ 12~0582~ 16~07817~, 19~03068~ 23~07682~ 26~03117~.'),
  (1152, 1, 38, 28, 'And it came to pass, when she travailed, that the one put out his hand: and the midwife took and bound upon his hand a scarlet thread, saying, This came out first.', '7~03205~, [9 10] 12~05414~ [13] 14~03027~: 17~03205~ 18~03947~ 20~07194~ 23~03027~ 26~08144~, 27~0559~, 30~03318~ 31~07223~.'),
  (18151, 23, 26, 12, 'LORD, thou wilt ordain peace for us: for thou also hast wrought all our works in us.', '&para; 0~03068~, 3~08239~ 4~07965~ 11~06466~ 14~04639~'),
  (30196, 58, 11, 8, 'By faith Abraham, when he was called to go out into a place which he should after receive for an inheritance, obeyed; and he went out, not knowing whither he went.', '1~4102~ 2~11~, 6~2564~ 9~1831~ 10~1519~ 12~5117~ 13~3739~ 16~3195~ 17~2983~ 18~1519~ 20~2817~, 21~5219~; 22~2532~ 25~1831~, 26~3361~ 27~1987~ 28~4226~ 30~2064~.'),
  (23721, 40, 17, 11, 'And Jesus answered and said unto them, Elias truly shall first come, and restore all things.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 4~2036~ 6~846~, 7~2243~ 8~3303~ 10~4412~ 11~2064~, 12~2532~ 13~600~ 15~3956~.'),
  (25486, 42, 12, 14, 'And he said unto him, Man, who made me a judge or a divider over you?', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~444~, 6~5101~ 7~2525~ 8~3165~ 10~1348~ 11~2228~ 13~3312~ 14~1909~ 15~5209~?'),
  (16578, 20, 6, 29, 'So he that goeth in to his neighbour''s wife; whosoever toucheth her shall not be innocent.', '4~0935~ 7~07453~ 8~0802~; 10~05060~ 15~05352~.'),
  (8190, 10, 7, 3, 'And Nathan said to the king, Go, do all that is in thine heart; for the LORD is with thee.', '1~05416~ 2~0559~ 5~04428~, 6~03212~, 7~06213~ [10] 13~03824~; 16~03068~ [17]'),
  (16705, 20, 11, 8, 'The righteous is delivered out of trouble, and the wicked cometh in his stead.', '&para; 1~06662~ 4~02502~ 6~06869~, 9~07563~ 10~0935~'),
  (3277, 3, 18, 21, 'And thou shalt not let any of thy seed pass through the fire to Molech, neither shalt thou profane the name of thy God: I am the LORD.', '3~05414~ 8~02233~ 9~05674~ [11 12] 14~04432~, 18~02490~ 20~08034~ 23~0430~: [25] 27~03068~.'),
  (24809, 41, 14, 44, 'And he that betrayed him had given them a token, saying, Whomsoever I shall kiss, that same is he; take him, and lead him away safely.', '0~1161~ 3~3860~ 4~846~ 6~1325~ 7~846~ 9~4953~, 10~3004~, 11~302~ 12~3739~ 14~5368~, 16~846~ 18~2076~; 19~2902~ 20~846~, 21~2532~ [23] 24~520~ 25~806~.'),
  (29533, 51, 2, 23, 'Which things have indeed a shew of wisdom in will worship, and humility, and neglecting of the body; not in any honour to the satisfying of the flesh.', '1~3748~ 2~2192~ 3~3303~ 5~2076~ 6~3056~* 8~4678~ 9~1722~ 11~1479~, 12~2532~ 13~5012~, 14~2532~ 15~857~ 18~4983~; 19~3756~ 20~1722~ 21~5100~ 22~5092~ 23~4314~ 25~4140~ 28~4561~.'),
  (30752, 66, 2, 19, 'I know thy works, and charity, and service, and faith, and thy patience, and thy works; and the last to be more than the first.', '1~1492~ 2~4675~ 3~2041~, 4~2532~ 5~26~, 6~2532~ 7~1248~, 8~2532~ 9~4102~, 10~2532~ 11~4675~ 12~5281~, 13~2532~ 14~4675~ 15~2041~; 16~2532~ 18~2078~ [19 20] 22~4119~ 24~4413~.'),
  (1217, 1, 41, 17, 'And Pharaoh said unto Joseph, In my dream, behold, I stood upon the bank of the river:', '&para; 1~06547~ 2~01696~ 4~03130~, 7~02472~, 10~05975~ 13~08193~ 16~02975~:'),
  (3118, 3, 14, 2, 'This shall be the law of the leper in the day of his cleansing: He shall be brought unto the priest:', '4~08451~ 7~06879~ 10~03117~ 13~02893~: 17~0935~ 20~03548~:'),
  (24004, 40, 24, 37, 'But as the days of Noe were, so shall also the coming of the Son of man be.', '0~1161~ 1~5618~ 3~2250~ 5~3575~ [6] 7~3779~ 8~2071~ 9~2532~ 11~3952~ 14~5207~ 16~444~ 17~2071~.'),
  (15715, 19, 107, 7, 'And he led them forth by the right way, that they might go to a city of habitation.', '4~01869~ 7~03477~ 8~01870~, 12~03212~ 15~05892~ 17~04186~.'),
  (11869, 14, 31, 6, 'And concerning the children of Israel and Judah, that dwelt in the cities of Judah, they also brought in the tithe of oxen and sheep, and the tithe of holy things which were consecrated unto the LORD their God, and laid them by heaps.', '[1] 3~01121~ 5~03478~ 7~03063~, 9~03427~ 12~05892~ 14~03063~, 18~0935~ 20~04643~ 22~01241~ 24~06629~, 27~04643~ 30~06944~ 33~06942~ 36~03068~ 38~0430~, 40~05414~ [41] 43~06194~ 44~06194~.*'),
  (29225, 49, 1, 3, 'Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who hath blessed us with all spiritual blessings in heavenly places in Christ:', '&para; 0~2128~ [1] 3~2316~ 4~2532~ 5~3962~ 7~2257~ 8~2962~ 9~2424~ 10~5547~, 11~3588~ 13~2127~ 14~2248~ 15~1722~ 16~3956~ 17~4152~ 18~2129~ 19~1722~ 20~2032~ [21] 22~1722~ 23~5547~:'),
  (14087, 19, 13, 4, 'Lest mine enemy say, I have prevailed against him; and those that trouble me rejoice when I am moved.', '2~0341~ 3~0559~, 6~03201~ [9] 12~06862~ 14~01523~ 18~04131~.'),
  (16015, 19, 119, 108, 'Accept, I beseech thee, the freewill offerings of my mouth, O LORD, and teach me thy judgments.', '&para; 0~07521~, 6~05071~ 9~06310~, 11~03068~, 13~03925~ 16~04941~.'),
  (24007, 40, 24, 40, 'Then shall two be in the field; the one shall be taken, and the other left.', '0~5119~ 1~2071~ 2~1417~ 3~2071~ 4~1722~ 6~68~; 8~1520~ 11~3880~, 12~2532~ 14~1520~ 15~863~.'),
  (11926, 14, 33, 9, 'So Manasseh made Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem to err, and to do worse than the heathen, whom the LORD had destroyed before the children of Israel.', '1~04519~ 2~08582~ 3~03063~ 6~03427~ 8~03389~ 10~08582~, [11] 13~06213~ 14~07451~ 17~01471~, 20~03068~ 22~08045~ 23~06440~ 25~01121~ 27~03478~.'),
  (1496, 1, 49, 18, 'I have waited for thy salvation, O LORD.', '3~06960~ 5~03444~, 7~03068~.'),
  (14881, 19, 65, 12, 'They drop upon the pastures of the wilderness: and the little hills rejoice on every side.', '1~07491~ [2] 4~04999~ 7~04057~: 11~01389~ 12~01524~ 15~02296~.'),
  (7863, 9, 24, 17, 'And he said to David, Thou art more righteous than I: for thou hast rewarded me good, whereas I have rewarded thee evil.', '2~0559~ 4~01732~, [6] 8~06662~ 14~01580~ 16~02896~, 20~01580~ 22~07451~.'),
  (10366, 13, 2, 52, 'And Shobal the father of Kirjathjearim had sons; Haroeh, and half of the Manahethites.', '1~07732~ 3~01~ 5~07157~ 7~01121~; 8~07204~, [9] 10~02677~ 13~02679~.'),
  (30338, 59, 3, 3, 'Behold, we put bits in the horses'' mouths, that they may obey us; and we turn about their whole body.', '0~2400~, 2~906~ 3~5469~ 4~1519~ 6~2462~ 7~4750~, 8~4314~ 9~846~ 11~3982~ 12~2254~; 13~2532~ 16~3329~ 17~846~ 18~3650~ 19~4983~.'),
  (22962, 38, 6, 6, 'The black horses which are therein go forth into the north country; and the white go forth after them; and the grisled go forth toward the south country.', '1~07838~ 2~05483~ [4] 7~03318~ 10~06828~ 11~0776~; 14~03836~ 16~03318~ 17~0310~ 21~01261~ 23~03318~ 26~08486~ 27~0776~.'),
  (22269, 28, 12, 8, 'And Ephraim said, Yet I am become rich, I have found me out substance: in all my labours they shall find none iniquity in me that were sin.', '1~0669~ 2~0559~, 7~06238~, 12~04672~ 13~0202~: [14] 17~03018~ 20~04672~ 22~05771~ [26] 27~02399~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (17403, 21, 4, 13, 'Better is a poor and a wise child than an old and foolish king, who will no more be admonished.', '&para; 0~02896~ [1] 3~04542~ 6~02450~ 7~03206~ 10~02205~ 12~03684~ 13~04428~, 15~03045~ 19~02094~.'),
  (5321, 5, 14, 25, 'Then shalt thou turn it into money, and bind up the money in thine hand, and shalt go unto the place which the LORD thy God shall choose:', '3~05414~ [4] 6~03701~, 9~06696~ 11~03701~ 14~03027~, 17~01980~ 20~04725~ 23~03068~ 25~0430~ 27~0977~:'),
  (28301, 45, 14, 5, 'One man esteemeth one day above another: another esteemeth every day alike. Let every man be fully persuaded in his own mind.', '0~3303~ 1~3739~ 2~2919~ 4~2250~ 5~3844~ 6~2250~ 7~1161~:* 8~3739~ 9~2919~ 10~3956~ 11~2250~ [12] 13~4135~ 15~1538~ 18~4135~ 19~1722~ 21~2398~ 22~3563~.'),
  (17737, 23, 3, 21, 'The rings, and nose jewels,', '1~02885~, 3~0639~ 4~05141~,'),
  (9598, 12, 3, 14, 'And Elisha said, As the LORD of hosts liveth, before whom I stand, surely, were it not that I regard the presence of Jehoshaphat the king of Judah, I would not look toward thee, nor see thee.', '1~0477~ 2~0559~, [3] 5~03068~ 7~06635~ 8~02416~, 9~06440~ 12~05975~, 17~03884~ 19~05375~ 21~06440~ 23~03092~ 25~04428~ 27~03063~, 31~05027~ 35~07200~'),
  (18, 1, 1, 18, 'And to rule over the day and over the night, and to divide the light from the darkness: and God saw that it was good.', '2~04910~ 5~03117~ 9~03915~, 12~0914~ 14~0216~ 17~02822~: 19~0430~ 20~07200~ [22 23] 24~02896~.'),
  (25736, 42, 18, 34, 'And they understood none of these things: and this saying was hid from them, neither knew they the things which were spoken.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~4920~ 3~3762~ 6~5130~: 7~2532~ 8~5124~ 9~4487~ 10~2258~ 11~2928~ 12~575~ 13~846~ 14~2532~,* 15~3756~ 17~1097~ 22~3004~.'),
  (12062, 15, 2, 26, 'The children of Ramah and Gaba, six hundred twenty and one.', '1~01121~ 3~07414~ 5~01387~, 6~08337~ 7~03967~ 8~06242~ 10~0259~.'),
  (28040, 45, 4, 2, 'For if Abraham were justified by works, he hath whereof to glory; but not before God.', '0~1063~ 1~1487~ 2~11~ 4~1344~ 5~1537~ 6~2041~, 8~2192~ [9] 11~2745~; 12~235~ 13~3756~ 14~4314~ 15~2316~.'),
  (8185, 10, 6, 21, 'And David said unto Michal, It was before the LORD, which chose me before thy father, and before all his house, to appoint me ruler over the people of the LORD, over Israel: therefore will I play before the LORD.', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 4~04324~, [5 6] 7~06440~ 9~03068~, 11~0977~ 15~01~, 20~01004~, 22~06680~ 24~05057~ 27~05971~ 30~03068~, 32~03478~: 36~07832~ 37~06440~ 39~03068~.'),
  (30224, 58, 11, 36, 'And others had trial of cruel mockings and scourgings, yea, moreover of bonds and imprisonment:', '0~1161~ 1~2087~ 2~2983~ 3~3984~ [5] 6~1701~ 7~2532~ 8~3148~, 9~1161~, 10~2089~ 12~1199~ 13~2532~ 14~5438~:'),
  (21487, 26, 40, 1, 'In the five and twentieth year of our captivity, in the beginning of the year, in the tenth day of the month, in the fourteenth year after that the city was smitten, in the selfsame day the hand of the LORD was upon me, and brought me thither.', '&para; 2~02568~ 4~06242~ 5~08141~ 8~01546~, 11~07218~ 14~08141~, 17~06218~ [18] 21~02320~, 24~06240~ 25~0702~* 26~08141~ 27~0310~ 30~05892~ 32~05221~, 35~06106~ 36~03117~ 38~03027~ 41~03068~ 46~0935~'),
  (26390, 43, 7, 47, 'Then answered them the Pharisees, Are ye also deceived?', '0~3767~ 1~611~ 2~846~ 4~5330~, 5~4105~ 6~5210~ 7~2532~ 8~4105~ 9~3361~?*'),
  (14597, 19, 44, 17, 'All this is come upon us; yet have we not forgotten thee, neither have we dealt falsely in thy covenant.', '&para; 3~0935~ 10~07911~ 16~08266~ 19~01285~.'),
  (7289, 9, 3, 6, 'And the LORD called yet again, Samuel. And Samuel arose and went to Eli, and said, Here am I; for thou didst call me. And he answered, I called not, my son; lie down again.', '2~03068~ 3~07121~ 5~03254~, 6~08050~. 8~08050~ 9~06965~ 11~03212~ 13~05941~, 15~0559~, [17] 22~07121~ 26~0559~, 28~07121~ 31~01121~; 33~07901~ 34~07725~.'),
  (1195, 1, 40, 18, 'And Joseph answered and said, This is the interpretation thereof: The three baskets are three days:', '1~03130~ 2~06030~ 4~0559~, [6] 8~06623~ 11~07969~ 12~05536~ [13] 14~07969~ 15~03117~:'),
  (22451, 30, 5, 19, 'As if a man did flee from a lion, and a bear met him; or went into the house, and leaned his hand on the wall, and a serpent bit him.', '3~0376~ 5~05127~ 6~06440~ 8~0738~, 11~01677~ 12~06293~ 15~0935~ 18~01004~, 20~05564~ 22~03027~ 25~07023~, 28~05175~ 29~05391~'),
  (27607, 44, 19, 6, 'And when Paul had laid his hands upon them, the Holy Ghost came on them; and they spake with tongues, and prophesied.', '0~2532~ 2~3972~ 4~2007~ [5] 6~5495~ 7~2007~ 8~846~, 10~40~ 11~4151~ 12~2064~ 13~1909~ 14~846~; 15~5037~ 17~2980~ 19~1100~, 20~2532~ 21~4395~.'),
  (27634, 44, 19, 33, 'And they drew Alexander out of the multitude, the Jews putting him forward. And Alexander beckoned with the hand, and would have made his defence unto the people.', '0~1161~ 2~4264~ 3~223~ 5~1537~ 7~3793~, 9~2453~ 10~4261~ 11~846~ 12~4261~ 13~1161~ 14~223~ 15~2678~ 18~5495~, 20~2309~ 24~626~ 27~1218~.'),
  (26524, 43, 10, 28, 'And I give unto them eternal life; and they shall never perish, neither shall any man pluck them out of my hand.', '1~2504~ 2~1325~ 4~846~ 5~166~ 6~2222~; 7~2532~ 9~622~ 10~165~ 11~3364~* 12~1519~* 13~622~, 14~3756~ 15~2532~* 16~726~ 17~5100~ [18] 19~726~ 20~846~ 22~1537~ 23~3450~ 24~5495~.'),
  (7952, 9, 28, 3, 'Now Samuel was dead, and all Israel had lamented him, and buried him in Ramah, even in his own city. And Saul had put away those that had familiar spirits, and the wizards, out of the land.', '1~08050~ 3~04191~, 6~03478~ 8~05594~ 11~06912~ 14~07414~, 19~05892~. 21~07586~ 24~05493~ 29~0178~, 32~03049~, 36~0776~.'),
  (5838, 5, 33, 22, 'And of Dan he said, Dan is a lion''s whelp: he shall leap from Bashan.', '&para; 2~01835~ 4~0559~, 5~01835~ [6] 8~0738~ 9~01482~: 12~02187~ 14~01316~.'),
  (3195, 3, 15, 22, 'And whosoever toucheth any thing that she sat upon shall wash his clothes, and bathe himself in water, and be unclean until the even.', '2~05060~ 4~03627~ 7~03427~ 10~03526~ 12~0899~, 14~07364~ [15] 17~04325~, 20~02930~ 23~06153~.'),
  (22846, 36, 3, 17, 'The LORD thy God in the midst of thee is mighty; he will save, he will rejoice over thee with joy; he will rest in his love, he will joy over thee with singing.', '1~03068~ 3~0430~ 6~07130~ [9] 10~01368~; 13~03467~, 16~07797~ 20~08057~; 23~02790~ 26~0160~, 29~01523~ 33~07440~.'),
  (27828, 44, 25, 16, 'To whom I answered, It is not the manner of the Romans to deliver any man to die, before that he which is accused have the accusers face to face, and have licence to answer for himself concerning the crime laid against him.', '0~4314~ 1~3739~ 3~611~ 4~3754~,* 6~2076~ 7~3756~ 9~1485~ 12~4514~ 14~5483~ 15~5100~ 16~444~ 17~1519~ 18~684~, 19~4250~ 20~2228~ 24~2723~ 25~2192~ 27~2725~ 30~4383~ 31~2596~* 32~5037~,* 34~2983~ 35~5117~ 39~627~ 40~4012~ 45~1462~.'),
  (18631, 23, 48, 8, 'Yea, thou heardest not; yea, thou knewest not; yea, from that time that thine ear was not opened: for I knew that thou wouldest deal very treacherously, and wast called a transgressor from the womb.', '2~08085~ 6~03045~ [12] 14~0241~ 17~06605~: 20~03045~ 25~0898~ 26~0898~, 29~07121~ 31~06586~ 34~0990~.'),
  (297, 1, 11, 28, 'And Haran died before his father Terah in the land of his nativity, in Ur of the Chaldees.', '1~02039~ 2~04191~ 3~06440~ 5~01~ 6~08646~ 9~0776~ 12~04138~, 14~0218~ 17~03778~.'),
  (1550, 2, 1, 13, 'And the Egyptians made the children of Israel to serve with rigour:', '2~04714~ 3~05647~ 5~01121~ 7~03478~ 9~05647~ 11~06531~:'),
  (26056, 42, 24, 51, 'And it came to pass, while he blessed them, he was parted from them, and carried up into heaven.', '0~2532~ 4~1096~, 5~1722~ 6~846~ 7~2127~ 8~846~, 11~1339~ 12~575~ 13~846~, 14~2532~ 16~399~ 17~1519~ 18~3772~.'),
  (17427, 21, 6, 1, 'There is an evil which I have seen under the sun, and it is common among men:', '&para; 1~03426~ 3~07451~ 7~07200~ 10~08121~, [13] 14~07227~ 16~0120~:'),
  (10156, 12, 22, 3, 'And it came to pass in the eighteenth year of king Josiah, that the king sent Shaphan the son of Azaliah, the son of Meshullam, the scribe, to the house of the LORD, saying,', '7~06240~ 8~08083~* 9~08141~ 11~04428~ 12~02977~, [13] 15~04428~ 16~07971~ 17~08227~ 19~01121~ 21~0683~, 23~01121~ 25~04918~, 27~05608~, 30~01004~ 33~03068~, 34~0559~,'),
  (11810, 14, 29, 10, 'Now it is in mine heart to make a covenant with the LORD God of Israel, that his fierce wrath may turn away from us.', '[1 2] 5~03824~ 7~03772~ 9~01285~ 12~03068~ 13~0430~ 15~03478~, 18~02740~ 19~0639~ 22~07725~'),
  (12951, 18, 4, 12, 'Now a thing was secretly brought to me, and mine ear received a little thereof.', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~01589~ 10~0241~ 11~03947~ 13~08102~'),
  (22264, 28, 12, 3, 'He took his brother by the heel in the womb, and by his strength he had power with God:', '3~0251~ 6~06117~ 9~0990~, 13~0202~ 16~08280~ 18~0430~:'),
  (7153, 8, 1, 19, 'So they two went until they came to Bethlehem. And it came to pass, when they were come to Bethlehem, that all the city was moved about them, and they said, Is this Naomi?', '&para; 2~08147~ 3~03212~ 6~0935~ 8~01035~. 17~0935~ 19~01035~, 23~05892~ 25~01949~ 30~0559~, [31] 33~05281~?'),
  (9518, 11, 22, 30, 'And the king of Israel said unto Jehoshaphat, I will disguise myself, and enter into the battle; but put thou on thy robes. And the king of Israel disguised himself, and went into the battle.', '2~04428~ 4~03478~ 5~0559~ 7~03092~, 10~02664~ 13~0935~ 16~04421~; 20~03847~ 22~0899~. 25~04428~ 27~03478~ 28~02664~ 31~0935~ 34~04421~.'),
  (28102, 45, 6, 18, 'Being then made free from sin, ye became the servants of righteousness.', '0~1659~ 1~1161~ 3~1659~ 4~575~ 5~266~, 9~1402~ 11~1343~.'),
  (19676, 24, 29, 32, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD; Behold, I will punish Shemaiah the Nehelamite, and his seed: he shall not have a man to dwell among this people; neither shall he behold the good that I will do for my people, saith the LORD; because he hath taught rebellion against the LORD.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~; 8~06485~ 9~08098~ 11~05161~, 14~02233~: 20~0376~ 22~03427~ 23~08432~ 25~05971~; 29~07200~ 31~02896~ 35~06213~ 38~05971~, 39~05002~ 41~03068~; 45~01696~ 46~05627~ 49~03068~.'),
  (4283, 4, 18, 21, 'And, behold, I have given the children of Levi all the tenth in Israel for an inheritance, for their service which they serve, even the service of the tabernacle of the congregation.', '4~05414~ 6~01121~ 8~03878~ 11~04643~ 13~03478~ 16~05159~, 17~02500~ 19~05656~ 22~05647~, [23] 25~05656~ 28~0168~ 31~04150~.'),
  (25831, 42, 20, 38, 'For he is not a God of the dead, but of the living: for all live unto him.', '0~1161~ 2~2076~ 3~3756~ 5~2316~ 8~3498~, 9~235~ 12~2198~: 13~1063~ 14~3956~ 15~2198~ 17~846~.'),
  (16184, 19, 134, 3, 'The LORD that made heaven and earth bless thee out of Zion.', '1~03068~ 3~06213~ 4~08064~ 6~0776~ 7~01288~ 11~06726~.'),
  (21112, 26, 26, 3, 'Therefore thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I am against thee, O Tyrus, and will cause many nations to come up against thee, as the sea causeth his waves to come up.', '2~0559~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~; [8] 12~06865~, 16~07227~ 17~01471~ 20~05927~ 25~03220~ 28~01530~ 31~05927~.'),
  (16378, 19, 147, 18, 'He sendeth out his word, and melteth them: he causeth his wind to blow, and the waters flow.', '2~07971~ 4~01697~, 6~04529~ 11~07307~ 13~05380~, [14] 16~04325~ 17~05140~.'),
  (18962, 24, 1, 7, 'But the LORD said unto me, Say not, I am a child: for thou shalt go to all that I shall send thee, and whatsoever I command thee thou shalt speak.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 6~0559~ [9] 11~05288~: 15~03212~ 21~07971~ 26~06680~ 30~01696~.'),
  (16474, 20, 3, 10, 'So shall thy barns be filled with plenty, and thy presses shall burst out with new wine.', '3~0618~ 5~04390~ 7~07647~, 10~03342~ 13~06555~ 16~08492~.'),
  (4184, 4, 15, 26, 'And it shall be forgiven all the congregation of the children of Israel, and the stranger that sojourneth among them; seeing all the people were in ignorance.', '4~05545~ 7~05712~ 10~01121~ 12~03478~, 15~01616~ 17~01481~ 18~08432~ 23~05971~ [24] 26~07684~.'),
  (1752, 2, 9, 5, 'And the LORD appointed a set time, saying, To morrow the LORD shall do this thing in the land.', '2~03068~ 3~07760~ 6~04150~, 7~0559~, 9~04279~ 11~03068~ 13~06213~ 15~01697~ 18~0776~.'),
  (8064, 10, 2, 8, 'But Abner the son of Ner, captain of Saul''s host, took Ishbosheth the son of Saul, and brought him over to Mahanaim;', '&para; 1~074~ 3~01121~ 5~05369~, 6~08269~ 8~07586~ 9~06635~, 10~03947~ 11~0378~ 13~01121~ 15~07586~, 19~05674~ 21~04266~;'),
  (26993, 44, 2, 28, 'Thou hast made known to me the ways of life; thou shalt make me full of joy with thy countenance.', '3~1107~ 5~3427~ 7~3598~ 9~2222~; 12~4137~ 13~3165~ 14~4137~ 16~2167~ 17~3326~ 18~4675~ 19~4383~.'),
  (8545, 10, 19, 26, 'And he answered, My lord, O king, my servant deceived me: for thy servant said, I will saddle me an ass, that I may ride thereon, and go to the king; because thy servant is lame.', '2~0559~, 4~0113~, 6~04428~, 8~05650~ 9~07411~ 13~05650~ 14~0559~, 17~02280~ 20~02543~, 24~07392~ 27~03212~ 30~04428~; 33~05650~ [34] 35~06455~.'),
  (21541, 26, 41, 6, 'And the side chambers were three, one over another, and thirty in order; and they entered into the wall which was of the house for the side chambers round about, that they might have hold, but they had not hold in the wall of the house.', '2~06763~ 3~06763~ [4] 5~07969~, 8~06763~, 10~07970~ 12~06471~; 15~0935~ 18~07023~ [20] 23~01004~ 27~06763~ 29~05439~, 34~0270~, 39~0270~ 42~07023~ 45~01004~.'),
  (14879, 19, 65, 10, 'Thou waterest the ridges thereof abundantly: thou settlest the furrows thereof: thou makest it soft with showers: thou blessest the springing thereof.', '1~07301~ 3~08525~ 5~07301~: 7~05181~ 9~01417~ 10~01418~* 15~04127~ 17~07241~: 19~01288~ 21~06780~'),
  (28595, 46, 10, 12, 'Wherefore let him that thinketh he standeth take heed lest he fall.', '0~5620~ 1~991~ 4~1380~ 6~2476~ 8~991~ 9~3361~ 11~4098~.'),
  (28934, 47, 7, 2, 'Receive us; we have wronged no man, we have corrupted no man, we have defrauded no man.', '0~5562~ 1~2248~; 4~91~ 6~3762~, 9~5351~ 11~3762~, 14~4122~ 16~3762~.'),
  (12925, 18, 3, 12, 'Why did the knees prevent me? or why the breasts that I should suck?', '3~01290~ 4~06923~ 9~07699~ 13~03243~?'),
  (11875, 14, 31, 12, 'And brought in the offerings and the tithes and the dedicated things faithfully: over which Cononiah the Levite was ruler, and Shimei his brother was the next.', '2~0935~ 4~08641~ 7~04643~ 10~06944~ [11] 12~0530~: 15~03562~ 17~03881~ [18] 19~05057~, 21~08096~ 23~0251~ [24] 26~04932~.'),
  (3752, 4, 4, 4, 'This shall be the service of the sons of Kohath in the tabernacle of the congregation, about the most holy things:', '[1 2] 4~05656~ 7~01121~ 9~06955~ 12~0168~ 15~04150~, [16] 18~06944~ 20~06944~:'),
  (18487, 23, 41, 27, 'The first shall say to Zion, Behold, behold them: and I will give to Jerusalem one that bringeth good tidings.', '1~07223~ [2 3] 5~06726~, 6~02009~, 7~02009~ 12~05414~ 14~03389~ 19~01319~.'),
  (57, 1, 3, 1, 'Now the serpent was more subtle than any beast of the field which the LORD God had made. And he said unto the woman, Yea, hath God said, Ye shall not eat of every tree of the garden?', '&para; 2~05175~ 3~01961~ 5~06175~ 8~02416~ 11~07704~ 14~03068~ 15~0430~ 17~06213~. 20~0559~ 23~0802~, 24~0637~, 26~0430~ 27~0559~, 31~0398~ 34~06086~ 37~01588~?'),
  (15078, 19, 74, 21, 'O let not the oppressed return ashamed: let the poor and needy praise thy name.', '4~01790~ 5~07725~ 6~03637~: 9~06041~ 11~034~ 12~01984~ 14~08034~.'),
  (10546, 13, 7, 3, 'And the sons of Uzzi; Izrahiah: and the sons of Izrahiah; Michael, and Obadiah, and Joel, Ishiah, five: all of them chief men.', '2~01121~ 4~05813~; 5~03156~: 8~01121~ 10~03156~; 11~04317~, 13~05662~, 15~03100~, 16~03449~, 17~02568~: 22~07218~.'),
  (13689, 18, 33, 30, 'To bring back his soul from the pit, to be enlightened with the light of the living.', '2~07725~ 4~05315~ 7~07845~, 10~0215~ 13~0216~ 16~02416~.'),
  (6575, 7, 2, 23, 'Therefore the LORD left those nations, without driving them out hastily; neither delivered he them into the hand of Joshua.', '2~03068~ 3~03240~ 5~01471~, 6~01115~ 9~03423~ 10~04118~; 12~05414~ 17~03027~ 19~03091~.'),
  (30077, 58, 6, 17, 'Wherein God, willing more abundantly to shew unto the heirs of promise the immutability of his counsel, confirmed it by an oath:', '0~3739~ 1~1722~* 2~2316~, 3~1014~ 5~4054~ 7~1925~ 10~2818~ 12~1860~ 14~276~ 16~846~ 17~1012~, 18~3315~ [19] 22~3727~:'),
  (9160, 11, 12, 1, 'And Rehoboam went to Shechem: for all Israel were come to Shechem to make him king.', '&para; 1~07346~ 2~03212~ 4~07927~: 7~03478~ 9~0935~ 11~07927~ 15~04427~.'),
  (17457, 21, 7, 19, 'Wisdom strengtheneth the wise more than ten mighty men which are in the city.', '0~02451~ 1~05810~ 3~02450~ 6~06235~ 7~07989~ [8] 13~05892~.'),
  (7888, 9, 25, 20, 'And it was so, as she rode on the ass, that she came down by the covert on the hill, and, behold, David and his men came down against her; and she met them.', '[3 4] 6~07392~ 9~02543~, 13~03381~ 16~05643~ 19~02022~, 22~01732~ 25~0582~ 27~03381~ 28~07125~ 32~06298~'),
  (23041, 38, 11, 4, 'Thus saith the LORD my God; Feed the flock of the slaughter;', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~0430~; 6~07462~ 8~06629~ 11~02028~;'),
  (12981, 18, 5, 21, 'Thou shalt be hid from the scourge of the tongue: neither shalt thou be afraid of destruction when it cometh.', '3~02244~ 6~07752~ 9~03956~: 14~03372~ 16~07701~ 19~0935~.'),
  (5669, 5, 28, 52, 'And he shall besiege thee in all thy gates, until thy high and fenced walls come down, wherein thou trustedst, throughout all thy land: and he shall besiege thee in all thy gates throughout all thy land, which the LORD thy God hath given thee.', '3~06887~ 8~08179~, 11~01364~ 13~01219~ 14~02346~ 16~03381~, 17~02004~ 19~0982~, 23~0776~: 27~06887~ 32~08179~ 36~0776~, 39~03068~ 41~0430~ 43~05414~'),
  (6743, 7, 8, 17, 'And he beat down the tower of Penuel, and slew the men of the city.', '3~05422~ 5~04026~ 7~06439~, 9~02026~ 11~0582~ 14~05892~.'),
  (28873, 47, 3, 16, 'Nevertheless when it shall turn to the Lord, the veil shall be taken away.', '0~1161~ 1~2259~ 2~302~ 4~1994~ 5~4314~ 7~2962~, 9~2571~ 13~4014~.'),
  (11899, 14, 32, 15, 'Now therefore let not Hezekiah deceive you, nor persuade you on this manner, neither yet believe him: for no god of any nation or kingdom was able to deliver his people out of mine hand, and out of the hand of my fathers: how much less shall your God deliver you out of mine hand?', '3~03808~ 4~02396~ 5~05377~ 8~05496~ 15~0539~ 19~0433~ 22~01471~ 24~04467~ 26~03201~ 28~05337~ 30~05971~ 34~03027~, 39~03027~ 42~01~: 48~0430~ 49~05337~ 54~03027~?'),
  (12240, 15, 8, 30, 'So took the priests and the Levites the weight of the silver, and the gold, and the vessels, to bring them to Jerusalem unto the house of our God.', '1~06901~ 3~03548~ 6~03881~ 8~04948~ 11~03701~, 14~02091~, 17~03627~, 19~0935~ [20] 22~03389~ 25~01004~ 28~0430~.'),
  (26718, 43, 15, 4, 'Abide in me, and I in you. As the branch cannot bear fruit of itself, except it abide in the vine; no more can ye, except ye abide in me.', '0~3306~ 1~1722~ 2~1698~, 4~2504~ 5~1722~ 6~5213~. 7~2531~ 9~2814~ 10~1410~ 11~3756~* 12~5342~ 13~2590~ 14~575~ 15~1438~, 16~3362~ 18~3306~ 19~1722~ 21~288~; 23~3779~ 24~3761~ 25~5210~, 26~3362~ 28~3306~ 29~1722~ 30~1698~.'),
  (9604, 12, 3, 20, 'And it came to pass in the morning, when the meat offering was offered, that, behold, there came water by the way of Edom, and the country was filled with water.', '&para; 7~01242~, 11~04503~ 13~05927~, 17~0935~ 18~04325~ 21~01870~ 23~0123~, 26~0776~ 28~04390~ 30~04325~.'),
  (1859, 2, 12, 38, 'And a mixed multitude went up also with them; and flocks, and herds, even very much cattle.', '2~06154~ 3~07227~ 5~05927~ 10~06629~, 12~01241~, [13] 14~03966~ 15~03515~ 16~04735~.'),
  (22936, 38, 4, 5, 'Then the angel that talked with me answered and said unto me, Knowest thou not what these be? And I said, No, my lord.', '2~04397~ 4~01696~ 7~06030~ 9~0559~ 12~03045~ 20~0559~, 23~0113~.'),
  (14036, 19, 9, 6, 'O thou enemy, destructions are come to a perpetual end: and thou hast destroyed cities; their memorial is perished with them.', '2~0341~, 3~02723~ 8~05331~ 9~08552~: 13~05428~ 14~06145~ 15~05892~;* 17~02143~ 19~06~ 21~01992~.'),
  (28164, 45, 8, 32, 'He that spared not his own Son, but delivered him up for us all, how shall he not with him also freely give us all things?', '1~1065~ 2~3739~* 3~5339~ 4~3756~ 6~2398~ 7~5207~, 8~235~ 9~3860~ 10~846~ 11~3860~ 12~5228~ 13~2257~ 14~3956~, 15~4459~ 17~5483~ 18~3780~ 19~4862~ 20~846~ 21~2532~ 23~5483~ 24~2254~ 26~3956~?'),
  (17868, 23, 10, 9, 'Is not Calno as Carchemish? is not Hamath as Arpad? is not Samaria as Damascus?', '[0] 2~03641~ 4~03751~? [5] 7~02574~ 9~0774~? [10] 12~08111~ 14~01834~?'),
  (24334, 41, 4, 1, 'And he began again to teach by the sea side: and there was gathered unto him a great multitude, so that he entered into a ship, and sat in the sea; and the whole multitude was by the sea on the land.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~756~ 3~3825~ 5~1321~ 6~3844~ 9~2281~: 10~2532~ 13~4863~ 14~4314~ 15~846~ 17~4183~ 18~3793~, 20~5620~ 21~846~ 22~1684~ 23~1519~ 25~4143~, 27~2521~ 28~1722~ 30~2281~; 31~2532~ 33~3956~ 34~3793~ 35~2258~ 36~4314~ 38~2281~ 39~1909~ 41~1093~.'),
  (17112, 20, 24, 24, 'He that saith unto the wicked, Thou art righteous; him shall the people curse, nations shall abhor him:', '2~0559~ 5~07563~, [7] 8~06662~; 12~05971~ 13~05344~, 14~03816~ 16~02194~'),
  (23413, 40, 9, 24, 'He said unto them, Give place: for the maid is not dead, but sleepeth. And they laughed him to scorn.', '1~3004~ 3~846~, 5~402~: 6~1063~ 8~2877~ 9~599~ 10~3756~ 11~599~, 12~235~ 13~2518~. 14~2532~ 16~2606~ 17~846~ 19~2606~.'),
  (9142, 11, 11, 26, 'And Jeroboam the son of Nebat, an Ephrathite of Zereda, Solomon''s servant, whose mother''s name was Zeruah, a widow woman, even he lifted up his hand against the king.', '&para; 1~03379~ 3~01121~ 5~05028~, 7~0673~ 9~06868~, 10~08010~ 11~05650~, 13~0517~ 14~08034~ [15] 16~06871~, 18~0490~ 19~0802~, 23~07311~ [24] 25~03027~ 28~04428~.'),
  (27440, 44, 14, 10, 'Said with a loud voice, Stand upright on thy feet. And he leaped and walked.', '0~2036~ 3~3173~ 4~5456~, 5~450~ 6~3717~ 7~1909~ 8~4675~ 9~4228~. 10~2532~ 12~242~ 13~2532~ 14~4043~.'),
  (24323, 41, 3, 25, 'And if a house be divided against itself, that house cannot stand.', '0~2532~ 1~1437~ 3~3614~ 5~3307~ 6~1909~ 7~1438~, 8~1565~ 9~3614~ 10~1410~ 11~3756~* 12~2476~.'),
  (14767, 19, 56, 3, 'What time I am afraid, I will trust in thee.', '1~03117~ 4~03372~, 7~0982~'),
  (25655, 42, 16, 21, 'And desiring to be fed with the crumbs which fell from the rich man''s table: moreover the dogs came and licked his sores.', '0~2532~ 1~1937~ 4~5526~ 5~575~ 7~5589~ 8~3588~ 9~4098~ 10~575~ 13~4145~ 14~5132~: 15~2532~ 16~235~ 17~2965~ 18~2064~ 20~621~ 21~846~ 22~1668~.'),
  (3368, 3, 21, 18, 'For whatsoever man he be that hath a blemish, he shall not approach: a blind man, or a lame, or he that hath a flat nose, or any thing superfluous,', '2~0376~ [3 4] 8~03971~, 12~07126~: 14~05787~ 15~0376~, 18~06455~, 25~02763~, 29~08311~,'),
  (7717, 9, 19, 4, 'And Jonathan spake good of David unto Saul his father, and said unto him, Let not the king sin against his servant, against David; because he hath not sinned against thee, and because his works have been to thee-ward very good:', '1~03083~ 2~01696~ 3~02896~ 5~01732~ 7~07586~ 9~01~, 11~0559~ 17~04428~ 18~02398~ 21~05650~, 23~01732~; 28~02398~ 34~04639~ [35 36] 39~03966~ 40~02896~:'),
  (25249, 42, 7, 42, 'And when they had nothing to pay, he frankly forgave them both. Tell me therefore, which of them will love him most?', '0~1161~ 2~846~ 3~2192~ 4~3361~ 6~591~, 9~5483~ 11~297~. 13~2036~ 14~3767~, 15~5101~ 17~846~ 19~25~ 20~846~ 21~4119~?'),
  (21105, 26, 25, 13, 'Therefore thus saith the Lord GOD; I will also stretch out mine hand upon Edom, and will cut off man and beast from it; and I will make it desolate from Teman; and they of Dedan shall fall by the sword.', '2~0559~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~; 10~05186~ 12~03027~ 14~0123~, 18~03772~ 19~0120~ 21~0929~ 27~05414~ 29~02723~ 31~08487~; 35~01719~ 37~05307~ 40~02719~.'),
  (10742, 13, 12, 14, 'These were of the sons of Gad, captains of the host: one of the least was over an hundred, and the greatest over a thousand.', '[1] 4~01121~ 6~01410~, 7~07218~ 10~06635~: 11~0259~ 14~06996~ [15] 18~03967~, 21~01419~ 24~0505~.'),
  (24039, 40, 25, 21, 'His lord said unto him, Well done, thou good and faithful servant: thou hast been faithful over a few things, I will make thee ruler over many things: enter thou into the joy of thy lord.', '0~1161~* 1~846~ 2~2962~ 3~5346~ 5~846~, 7~2095~, [8] 9~18~ 10~2532~ 11~4103~ 12~1401~: 15~2258~ 16~4103~ 17~1909~ 20~3641~, 23~2525~ 24~4571~ 25~2525~ 26~1909~ 28~4183~: 30~1525~ 31~1519~ 33~5479~ 35~4675~ 36~2962~.'),
  (10563, 13, 7, 20, 'And the sons of Ephraim; Shuthelah, and Bered his son, and Tahath his son, and Eladah his son, and Tahath his son,', '&para; 2~01121~ 4~0669~; 5~07803~, 7~01260~ 9~01121~, 11~08480~ 13~01121~, 15~0497~ 17~01121~, 19~08480~ 21~01121~,'),
  (30555, 61, 3, 17, 'Ye therefore, beloved, seeing ye know these things before, beware lest ye also, being led away with the error of the wicked, fall from your own stedfastness.', '0~5210~ 1~3767~, 2~27~, [6 7] 8~4267~, 9~5442~ 10~3363~ 12~1601~, 15~4879~ 18~4106~ 21~113~, 23~1601~ 25~2398~ 26~4740~.'),
  (10536, 13, 6, 74, 'And out of the tribe of Asher; Mashal with her suburbs, and Abdon with her suburbs,', '4~04294~ 6~0836~; 7~04913~ 10~04054~, 12~05658~ 15~04054~,'),
  (4515, 4, 26, 21, 'And the sons of Pharez were; of Hezron, the family of the Hezronites: of Hamul, the family of the Hamulites.', '2~01121~ 4~06557~ 7~02696~, 9~04940~ 12~02697~: 14~02538~, 16~04940~ 19~02539~.'),
  (17971, 23, 15, 2, 'He is gone up to Bajith, and to Dibon, the high places, to weep: Moab shall howl over Nebo, and over Medeba: on all their heads shall be baldness, and every beard cut off.', '3~05927~ 5~01006~, 8~01769~, 11~01116~, 13~01065~: 14~04124~ 16~03213~ 18~05015~, 21~04311~: 25~07218~ [26 27] 28~07144~, [29] 31~02206~ 33~01438~.');
